Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.00,0:00:13.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,片名：胡佛
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.48,0:00:26.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,這麼跟你說吧\N{\rENG}Let me tell you something.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.98,0:00:30.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,南方基督教領袖會議和共產主義有直接聯繫\N{\rENG}The SCLC has direct Communist ties.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.61,0:00:33.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,最偉大的人也有腐壞的可能 不是嗎？\N{\rENG}Even great men can be corrupted, can't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.45,0:00:36.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,共產主義並不是政治黨派的一種 這是瘟疫\N{\rENG}Communism is not a political party. It is a disease.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.16,0:00:39.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,它會腐蝕靈魂 把最紳士的人們...\N{\rENG}It corrupts the soul, turning even the gentlest of men...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.95,0:00:43.16,CHT,,0,0,0,,...變成惡毒、邪惡的暴君\N{\rENG}...into vicious, evil tyrants.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.33,0:00:46.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們所見到的全是 對法律和指令的不屑一顧\N{\rENG}What we are seeing is a pervasive contempt for law and order.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.92,0:00:48.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,犯罪率激增\N{\rENG}Crime rates are soaring.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.17,0:00:50.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,廣泛、公然地蔑視我們的權威...\N{\rENG}There's widespread, open defiance of our authority...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.05,0:00:53.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,...記住我這句話 倘若此事不被及時遏制\N{\rENG}...and, mark my words, if this goes unchecked...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.72,0:00:58.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,它會把我們國家再次 拉向無政府狀態的深淵\N{\rENG}...it will once again plunge our nation into the depths of anarchy.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.47,0:01:01.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,一切的開始總是平靜的 不是嗎，埃爾文先生？\N{\rENG}It all starts out peacefully, doesn't it, Mr. lrwin?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.47,0:01:03.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,你必須接受這個事實...\N{\rENG}You have to live with the fact...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.18,0:01:06.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,...那就是你本可以幫著避免 爆炸案和暴力事件的發生\N{\rENG}...that you could've helped prevent the bombings and the violence.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.27,0:01:08.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,我更感興趣的是 它是如何描述您和您掌管的聯邦調查局\N{\rENG}I'm more interested in what this says about your FBl.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.98,0:01:11.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,我辛苦工作了這麼長時間 真的不能就這樣退居幕後...\N{\rENG}I have worked too long and hard to just sit back...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.52,0:01:15.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,...來眼睜睜地看著壞人再次吸引 大家的眼球 不是嗎？\N{\rENG}...and watch the bad guys capture the spotlight again, haven't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.49,0:01:17.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,關於臭名昭著這件事 有件有趣的事實...\N{\rENG}The funny thing about notoriety...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.36,0:01:21.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,...尤其是當它的來源是崇拜 或是名望...\N{\rENG}...especially the kind that needs adoration, fame for fame's sake...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.99,0:01:24.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,...如果不加以控制 將不可避免地變成壞事\N{\rENG}...if unchecked, it inevitably leads to villainy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.41,0:01:27.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,我建議您好好看看 這次爭辯的真正目的...\N{\rENG}I suggest you look at what this squabble is really about...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.83,0:01:31.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,...在徹底毀掉您最心愛的事情的名聲之前 我們都知道那是什麼\N{\rENG}...before you destroy the reputation of the thing we both know you love most.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.64,0:01:43.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,[對講機響]
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.35,0:01:48.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,[海倫]來自《犯罪紀實》的作者到了\N{\rENG}Sir, the writer's here from Crime Records...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.15,0:01:50.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,...公關辦公室找來的\N{\rENG}...the PR Department.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.36,0:01:53.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,把他安排在我外面的辦公室 帶上打字機\N{\rENG}Set him up with a typewriter in my outer office.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.53,0:01:56.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,甘迪小姐 是時候讓這代人 知道我這版本的故事了\N{\rENG}Miss Gandy, it's time this generation learn my side of the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.15,0:01:59.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,- [海倫]馬上就好 - 謝謝\N{\rENG}- Right away. - Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.74,0:02:03.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,那是1919年，史密斯調查員...\N{\rENG}In 1919, Agent Smith...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.24,0:02:05.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,我在司法部的第一任上司...\N{\rENG}...my first boss here at the Department of Justice...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.87,0:02:08.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,是總檢察長A·米切爾·帕爾默\N{\rENG}...was Attorney General A. Mitchell Palmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.08,0:02:10.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,他是貴格會信仰者 （貴格會，基督教信教的一個派別）\N{\rENG}He was a Quaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.42,0:02:15.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,他不信奉戰爭 但他理解力量和決斷的必要性\N{\rENG}He didn't believe in war, but he understood the necessity of strength and resolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.55,0:02:17.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,你們從史學家那裡瞭解到的...\N{\rENG}Believe what you will from historians...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.55,0:02:21.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,...通常都是從現在的角度來看 疏忽了前後關係\N{\rENG}...most write from a present perspective, forgetting context.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.64,0:02:24.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,米切爾·帕爾默是個英雄人物\N{\rENG}Mitchell Palmer was a hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.09,0:02:58.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 你沒事吧？ - 嗯\N{\rENG}- Are you all right? - Unh.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.09,0:03:01.18,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 沒事吧？ - 我想是的，是的\N{\rENG}- Are you all right? - Yes. I think. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.11,0:03:22.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒事了 來\N{\rENG}It's all right. Come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.45,0:03:25.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 沒事了 沒事了 - 沒事了\N{\rENG}- It's all right, it's all right. - No, it's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.12,0:03:28.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,還好嗎？已經沒事了\N{\rENG}Are you okay? It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.83,0:03:34.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,還好吧？\N{\rENG}Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.78,0:04:02.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,你看 帕爾默和激進者的鬥爭 正和我一樣\N{\rENG}You see, Palmer fought the radicals, just as I have.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.15,0:04:07.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,同樣的 他也是目標 他並不是唯一一個\N{\rENG}And just as I have, he was targeted. He wasn't alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.78,0:04:12.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,那一晚全國各地一共 有8枚炸彈爆炸 全都是在晚上11點\N{\rENG}Across the country that night, eight bombs exploded, all at 11 p.m.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.83,0:04:14.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,兩位國家參議員\N{\rENG}Two United States senators...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.50,0:04:17.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,四位內閣成員 一位最高法院法官\N{\rENG}...four cabinet members, a Supreme Court justice...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.17,0:04:19.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,約翰·D·洛克菲勒，J·P·摩根... （洛克菲勒，美國實業家，標準石油創辦人；摩根，美國銀行家）\N{\rENG}...John D. Rockefeller, J.P. Morgan...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.00,0:04:23.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們都成了 布爾什維克共產主義分子的目標\N{\rENG}...all of them targeted by Bolshevik Communists.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.51,0:04:25.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,是啊 整棟樓都晃了\N{\rENG}Yeah, it shook the whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.68,0:04:32.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,對我而言 激進者的炸彈襲擊事件 過去得太快了\N{\rENG}It was clear to me the radical's bomb went off too soon...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.73,0:04:35.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,只在路中間留下了他的血跡\N{\rENG}...leaving only his blood in the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.69,0:04:40.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,但是檢察人員用桶子來收拾殘局 而不是收集證據\N{\rENG}But the inspectors used buckets to clean up the mess instead of collecting it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.48,0:04:43.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們丟掉了他的槍 而不是保存指紋\N{\rENG}They discarded his gun instead of preserving its prints.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.03,0:04:46.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,但是你也看得到 這不算什麼愚蠢的員警的行為\N{\rENG}But you see, this wasn't clumsy police work.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.36,0:04:49.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,在那個時候 這是正常的程式\N{\rENG}In those times, it was normal procedure.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.66,0:04:52.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,這個國家或許就要完了 德懷特\N{\rENG}This may be the end of days for this country, Dwight.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.38,0:05:01.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,那是1919年 還沒人正視過犯罪科學...\N{\rENG}it was 1919, before anyone respected criminal science...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.71,0:05:04.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,還沒有聯邦權利機構 沒有聯邦調查局\N{\rENG}...before federal powers, before the FBl.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.55,0:05:10.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,就是那晚我的眼界被打開了 就是那一晚\N{\rENG}It was that night my eyes were opened. That very night.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.22,0:05:12.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,他是你的鄰居嗎？\N{\rENG}Is he a neighbor, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.27,0:05:15.18,CHT,,0,0,0,,不 他在我辦公室工作\N{\rENG}No. He works in my office.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.35,0:05:21.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,“會有一次謀殺行動 我們殺戮因為它必須存在”\N{\rENG}- "There will have to be murder. - We will kill because it is necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.07,0:05:25.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,“我們以毀滅來擺脫 你們這個獨裁主義的國家”\N{\rENG}We will destroy to rid the world of your tyrannical institutions."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.25,0:05:36.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,你那晚在帕爾默檢察長的家裡？\N{\rENG}You were at Attorney General Palmer's home that night?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.87,0:05:39.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們把這一點 留給讀者想像吧\N{\rENG}Well, let's leave that to the reader's imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.67,0:05:43.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,你看 我們賦予主角一些神秘感 還是很重要的\N{\rENG}You see, it's important we give our protagonist a bit of mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.76,0:05:46.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,我可以暗示是一個 您提到過的年輕人\N{\rENG}I could allude to a young man who matches your description.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.88,0:05:48.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,對兩邊都好\N{\rENG}The best of both worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.51,0:05:50.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,你的法學文憑是哪裡的？\N{\rENG}Where did you get your law degree?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.89,0:05:53.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,喬治華盛頓大學 我是本地人\N{\rENG}George Washington. I grew up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.22,0:05:55.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,我需要照顧家母 所以不敢遠遊\N{\rENG}I had a mom to take care of, so I stayed close.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.68,0:05:57.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,我在這學校還取得了英語專業文憑\N{\rENG}I received an English degree there also.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.77,0:06:02.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,那就不需要我來告訴你 決定一個人的遺產的關鍵...\N{\rENG}Then I don't need to tell you that what determines a man's legacy...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.11,0:06:05.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,通常都是眼睛所不能看見的\N{\rENG}...is often what isn't seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.69,0:06:07.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在的重點是\N{\rENG}What's critical at this moment is...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.20,0:06:12.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們要重申 惡棍和英雄的區別\N{\rENG}...that we re-clarify the difference between villain and hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.95,0:06:16.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,你覺得這區別 和今天的標準相比呢？\N{\rENG}How do you think that compares with today?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.62,0:06:20.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,我也不確定 我想要知道更多\N{\rENG}I'm not sure, sir. I'd like to hear more.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.58,0:06:22.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,我可以明天再來\N{\rENG}I could come back tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.29,0:06:26.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,好 但這些寫好的得留下\N{\rENG}Fine. But the pages stay here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.76,0:06:28.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,當然\N{\rENG}Of course, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.97,0:06:31.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,再會 史密斯調查員\N{\rENG}Agent Smith.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.30,0:06:32.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝您\N{\rENG}Thank you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.65,0:06:42.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,太大聲說話總是不好的\N{\rENG}Never a good idea to talk too loud.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.32,0:06:50.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,早上好 約翰\N{\rENG}Good morning, John.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.78,0:06:53.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,帕爾默先生讓你參與今天的緊急會議\N{\rENG}Mr. Palmer has asked that you attend the emergency meeting today.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.03,0:06:55.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,格萊德維爾小姐 請記住...\N{\rENG}Miss Gladwell, please remember...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.91,0:06:58.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,叫我 胡佛先生\N{\rENG}...it's Mr. Hoover.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.58,0:07:00.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,兩點鐘\N{\rENG}Two o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.67,0:07:04.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,這次別去太早 跟遲到一樣無禮\N{\rENG}Don't be too early this time. It's as rude as being tardy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.17,0:07:08.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,這位秘書處新來的美麗女士又是？\N{\rENG}And who is this lovely addition to the secretarial pool?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.80,0:07:13.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,海倫 自我介紹一下\N{\rENG}Helen, introduce yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.10,0:07:15.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,噢\N{\rENG}Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.30,0:07:18.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,很高興見到你 胡佛先生 我叫海倫·甘迪\N{\rENG}Pleased to meet you, Mr. Hoover. I'm Helen Gandy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.31,0:07:21.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,也很高興見到你 歡迎來司法部\N{\rENG}Pleased to meet you. Welcome to the Department of Justice.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.85,0:07:25.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,你可以告知帕爾默先生我會出席\N{\rENG}You can notify Mr. Palmer that I will attend.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.19,0:07:27.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,當然\N{\rENG}Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.36,0:07:33.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,他總是這麼迷人 我做事不會太認真的\N{\rENG}- He's always a charmer. - I wouldn't take anything very seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.71,0:07:44.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,傑瑞米 我需要你的説明\N{\rENG}Jeremy, I need your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.67,0:07:46.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,我需要...幫助\N{\rENG}I need, uh... Uh, help.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.50,0:07:47.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,我需要你的説明\N{\rENG}I need your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.19,0:08:07.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,晚上好 母親\N{\rENG}Good evening, Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.07,0:08:12.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,愛德格\N{\rENG}Edgar.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.07,0:08:16.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,瑪西亞夫人今早給我算了一卦\N{\rENG}Madame Marcia held court this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.53,0:08:20.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,她預感說 我應該買條裙子\N{\rENG}I should buy a dress.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.25,0:08:23.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,她說你的父親不久就要死了\N{\rENG}She says your father will die soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.67,0:08:29.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,他死後 你會成為這個國家最有權勢的人\N{\rENG}And when he does, you will rise to be the most powerful man in the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.47,0:08:35.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,你的哥哥是個好人 愛德格...\N{\rENG}Your brother's a good man, Edgar...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.93,0:08:39.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,但是你會讓我們家族復興\N{\rENG}...but you will restore our family to greatness.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.73,0:08:43.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,愛德格？\N{\rENG}Edgar?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.94,0:08:46.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,愛德格？我煩到你了嗎？\N{\rENG}Edgar? Am I boring you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.60,0:08:49.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,我在聽著呢 媽媽 你解雇了女傭\N{\rENG}I'm listening, Mother. You fired the maid.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.11,0:08:52.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,我告訴她幹完活 就可以自己走人了\N{\rENG}I told her when she was through, she could quit.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.49,0:08:56.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不會再為她的肆無忌憚付工錢 整個黑人階級都要公開造反了\N{\rENG}I'm not paying for her impudence. The whole Negro race is in open revolt.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.11,0:08:59.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 我可以開展調查 - 日子過得太舒服了\N{\rENG}- I could open an investigation. - Gotten too comfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.45,0:09:02.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,你聽見我剛才說的了嗎？ 我說 我可以開展調查了\N{\rENG}Did you hear what I said? I said I could open an investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.58,0:09:03.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,直說吧什麼意思\N{\rENG}Say what you mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.29,0:09:08.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,帕爾默先生今天叫我參與了一個會議 和布爾什維克的戰爭已經開始了\N{\rENG}Mr. Palmer called me into a meeting today. The war against the Bolsheviks has begun.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.42,0:09:11.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,他堅持讓我領導 一個新的反激進分子的部門\N{\rENG}He's insisted that I lead a new anti-radical division.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.80,0:09:13.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,你是不是像條小狗一樣歡呼雀躍了？\N{\rENG}Did you leap like a dog?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.01,0:09:17.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,我告訴他 這是我們國家面臨過的最大威脅...\N{\rENG}I told him this is the greatest threat our nation has ever faced...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.30,0:09:21.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,我在感覺到自己會有所成效之前 是不會接受這份工作的\N{\rENG}...and I cannot take the job unless I feel certain I can be effective.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.31,0:09:23.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,漂亮 但你還是會接受的\N{\rENG}Well done. But you'll take it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.93,0:09:25.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,年薪有三千呢 媽\N{\rENG}Three thousand a year, Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.98,0:09:28.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,我得給你買點新衣服 你不能再穿成這樣了\N{\rENG}I've got to get new clothes. You can't look like that anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.23,0:09:34.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,僅僅4小時之後 我就掌握了40個激進分子的名單\N{\rENG}I have 40 names of suspected radicals already in only four hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.94,0:09:36.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,月底之前應該會有一萬個\N{\rENG}I should have 10,000 by end of the month.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.99,0:09:41.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,我還有自己的員工 可以信任的調查員們\N{\rENG}And I have my own staff, trusted agents.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.95,0:09:44.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,愛德格 你在抽煙？\N{\rENG}Edgar, are you smoking?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.29,0:09:48.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 不會自覺去抽的 媽 - 聽醫生的話\N{\rENG}- Doesn't come naturally, Mother. - Listen to the doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.83,0:09:52.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,有它分散一下 你的勇氣會更迸發出來\N{\rENG}With this new burden, your nerves could get the better of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.01,0:09:57.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,你不會想落得跟你爸一樣的下場吧\N{\rENG}You don't want to end up like your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.13,0:10:00.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在就去抽根煙 把你爸扶到房間去\N{\rENG}Go and try one now. You can put your father in his room.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.85,0:10:02.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,我得準備一下去吃晚飯\N{\rENG}I have to get ready for dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.68,0:10:06.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,今晚你要拋下我？\N{\rENG}Are you abandoning me tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.64,0:10:10.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,是和一位打字員 她很有條理\N{\rENG}It's with a typist. She's very organized.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.40,0:10:12.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是個約會？\N{\rENG}Is it a date?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.61,0:10:14.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,我想是的\N{\rENG}I think so. I think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.82,0:10:19.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,我會給她展示我在國會圖書館的 卡片編目系統\N{\rENG}I'm gonna show her my old card catalog system at the Library of Congress.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.45,0:10:21.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,給她製造點浪漫\N{\rENG}Romance her.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.03,0:10:23.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,戴藍色的領帶\N{\rENG}Wear a blue tie.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.58,0:10:26.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,你戴藍色領帶特別帥\N{\rENG}You look so handsome in your blue tie.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.72,0:10:38.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,看天花板\N{\rENG}Look at the ceiling.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.88,0:10:40.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,真不可思議\N{\rENG}It's incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.72,0:10:47.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,我還從沒來過這裡\N{\rENG}I've never been here before.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.98,0:10:56.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,我幫忙整編好了這些\N{\rENG}I helped organize it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.53,0:10:59.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,看 每件物品都有它 自己的索引卡片\N{\rENG}See, every item is assigned its own index card...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.24,0:11:00.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,有著自己特有的編碼\N{\rENG}...with its own unique code...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.16,0:11:05.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,標明了標題 作者 位置 主題\N{\rENG}...indicating the title, author, location, and topic.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.28,0:11:09.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,過去需要好幾天時間來找的東西 現在只需要幾分鐘\N{\rENG}What used to take days to locate now only takes a matter of minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.83,0:11:13.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,來吧 說個作者或者題目 隨便什麼\N{\rENG}Go on. Give me an author or a topic. Anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.17,0:11:15.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,“不檢點行為”\N{\rENG}Indiscretion.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.38,0:11:16.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,什麼年代？\N{\rENG}What era?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.84,0:11:17.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,現代\N{\rENG}Present day.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.05,0:11:20.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,好 幫我計時\N{\rENG}Good. Time me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.16,0:11:48.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,嗯...\N{\rENG}Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.96,0:11:53.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,Heh.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.50,0:11:57.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,差不多找到了\N{\rENG}Almost there, heh.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.17,0:12:04.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,你怎麼知道我不是在說 “政治不檢點”？\N{\rENG}How do you know I didn't mean political indiscretion?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.68,0:12:08.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果你喜歡呢 我可以重找一次\N{\rENG}Well, if you'd like, I can start all over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.43,0:12:09.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,這個就好了\N{\rENG}This will do.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.77,0:12:11.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,我花了多長時間？\N{\rENG}How long did I take?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.64,0:12:13.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,一分鐘 零10秒\N{\rENG}One minute, 10 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.98,0:12:17.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,想像一下 如果這個國家的每個公民 都可以如此唯一可識別...\N{\rENG}Now imagine if every citizen in this country were uniquely identifiable...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.77,0:12:21.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,通過他們自己的卡片和編號 比如說 指紋圖案\N{\rENG}...by their own card and number, say, the pattern on their fingers.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.99,0:12:27.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,想想看 如果他們犯了罪 我們可以多麼迅速地抓到他們\N{\rENG}Imagine how quickly we could find them if they committed a crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.49,0:12:29.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,這一切都太棒了 約翰\N{\rENG}It's all very impressive, John.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.66,0:12:34.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,你想要繼續呆在這裡 還是想去別的地方？\N{\rENG}Well, would you like to stay here or would you like to go somewhere else?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.79,0:12:37.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,由你決定\N{\rENG}It's up to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.88,0:12:42.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,胡佛先生\N{\rENG}Mr. Hoover.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.51,0:12:48.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不確定你想讓事情如何發展\N{\rENG}I'm not sure where you think this is headed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.60,0:12:50.18,CHT,,0,0,0,,噢 當然\N{\rENG}Right, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.68,0:12:53.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,甘迪小姐\N{\rENG}Miss Gandy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.73,0:12:59.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,我知道我們倆只是認識了很短的時間\N{\rENG}I know we've only known each other a brief time...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.19,0:13:01.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,但我肯定你會是最好的伴侶\N{\rENG}...but you would make the finest of companions.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.69,0:13:05.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,你的力量 人格 還有教育\N{\rENG}Your strength, your character, your education.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.32,0:13:07.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,你是在取笑我嗎？\N{\rENG}Are you poking fun at me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.95,0:13:10.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,不 不 不 不 當然不是\N{\rENG}No. No, no, no. No, no, of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.74,0:13:14.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,那胡佛先生 請站起來說吧\N{\rENG}Then please, Mr. Hoover, stand up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.13,0:13:21.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,我會非常感激 假如你不會把這些...\N{\rENG}I'd appreciate it if you wouldn't share this...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.88,0:13:24.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,告訴任何你的打字員同事\N{\rENG}...with any of the other women in the typing pool.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.05,0:13:26.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,當然不會\N{\rENG}No, of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.72,0:13:29.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,好吧 能否問問...\N{\rENG}All right. May I ask what... What...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.14,0:13:33.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,你覺得我的人格有什麼缺陷嗎？\N{\rENG}What particular flaw you seem to find in my character?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.43,0:13:36.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,不 我們才剛認識\N{\rENG}No. We just met.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.56,0:13:37.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,當然\N{\rENG}Right, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.90,0:13:40.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,但我相信我在判斷人格方面 又快又准\N{\rENG}But I believe that I am a fast and accurate judge of character.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.07,0:13:43.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們已經約會三次 但我已不需要更多了\N{\rENG}We've gone out three times, but I don't need more.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.57,0:13:47.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,大多數人還需要 但我不用 我能一眼看穿別人是怎樣的人\N{\rENG}Most people do, but I don't. I see people right off for what they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.20,0:13:50.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,還有 請叫我愛德格 我母親就是這樣叫我\N{\rENG}And please, call me Edgar. It's what my mother uses.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.74,0:13:52.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 愛德格？ - 嗯\N{\rENG}- Edgar? - Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.83,0:13:55.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,你能保守一個秘密嗎？\N{\rENG}Can you keep a secret?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.87,0:13:58.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,當然 說到做到\N{\rENG}Yes. Of course. You have my word.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.42,0:14:04.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,我對結婚沒有興趣 工作才是第一位\N{\rENG}I'm not interested in getting married. My work comes first.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.13,0:14:07.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,嗯...\N{\rENG}Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.88,0:14:14.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,那或許你可以考慮 做我的私人秘書\N{\rENG}Then perhaps you would consider a position as my personal secretary.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.40,0:14:21.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,好的\N{\rENG}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.44,0:14:23.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們走吧？\N{\rENG}Shall we?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.69,0:14:26.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,那本書\N{\rENG}The book.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.32,0:14:27.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,對\N{\rENG}Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.61,0:14:30.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,你先請\N{\rENG}After you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.28,0:14:35.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,我正如那個圖書館一樣 規整了調查局\N{\rENG}I helped organize that library just as I did this Bureau.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.79,0:14:38.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,很多人說其實二者都不需要這樣做\N{\rENG}And many said we didn't need either.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.29,0:14:41.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,你看 創新者總是不受待見\N{\rENG}You see, innovators aren't often celebrated.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.13,0:14:43.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,那只是一開始不受待見\N{\rENG}Not at first.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.80,0:14:56.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,甘迪小姐\N{\rENG}Miss Gandy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.93,0:15:01.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,甘迺迪家那個蠢孩子 又呼我了\N{\rENG}The nitwit Kennedy child rang his baby buzzer again.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.81,0:15:03.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,或許他需要換尿布了吧\N{\rENG}Perhaps he'd like a fresh diaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.56,0:15:05.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是不是該看看總檢察長 需要些什麼？\N{\rENG}Should I find out what the Attorney General needs?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.11,0:15:09.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,不 我需要洛杉磯那邊錄音的 完全副本\N{\rENG}No, I want the completed transcripts of the Los Angeles recordings.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.99,0:15:12.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,我收到了那些以後 才會回復他的呼叫\N{\rENG}When I receive those, then we'll answer his buzzer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.99,0:15:14.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,很好\N{\rENG}Very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.20,0:15:17.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,愛德格 史密斯調查員回來了\N{\rENG}Edgar, Agent Smith is back.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.83,0:15:20.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,他對於帕爾默襲擊案還有些問題\N{\rENG}He, uh, has some questions about the Palmer Raids.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.08,0:15:23.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,我讓他走？\N{\rENG}Should I tell him to go?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.50,0:15:26.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,海倫 你喜歡他嗎？\N{\rENG}Helen, do you like him?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.84,0:15:29.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,我對他還沒有什麼看法\N{\rENG}I don't have an opinion of him yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.72,0:15:31.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,嗯...\N{\rENG}Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.47,0:15:33.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,我喜歡他 我信任他\N{\rENG}Well, I like him. I trust him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.93,0:15:37.85,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 那我把他安排到你外面的辦公室 - 不 不 不\N{\rENG}- I'll set him up in your outer office. - No. No, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.02,0:15:40.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,搬個桌子讓他到裡面來\N{\rENG}Bring him a desk in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.77,0:15:45.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,但是在1920年 我該如何保護我們機構不受任何人影響？\N{\rENG}But in 1920, how could I protect us from anyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.81,0:15:48.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,我搬來這個辦公室之前 我們毫無權力\N{\rENG}Before I moved to this office, we were powerless.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.90,0:15:51.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們受制幾條聯邦法律 無權攜帶軍火...\N{\rENG}We had few federal laws, no right to carry firearms...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.82,0:15:53.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,國會也喜歡這樣\N{\rENG}...and Congress liked it that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.16,0:15:58.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,犯罪者被釋放 但也沒有法律禁制我們追蹤他們\N{\rENG}Criminals ran free, but there was no law against keeping track of them...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.58,0:16:00.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,所以我自己做了個決定\N{\rENG}...so I made a decision on my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.91,0:16:03.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,我彙編了超過5000個名字的卡片\N{\rENG}I compiled note cards and over five thousand names...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.62,0:16:05.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,然後聯繫了華盛頓的一個部門...\N{\rENG}...and called the one department in Washington...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.04,0:16:08.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們仍有一小部分 未經檢驗的權力\N{\rENG}...that still held a small piece of untested power.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.88,0:16:12.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,是勞工部嗎？ 是不是他們有驅逐出境的權利？\N{\rENG}Was that the Department of Labor? The power to deport, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.72,0:16:15.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,但他們只驅逐 滿足以下兩個條件的人\N{\rENG}But only to deport those who checked two boxes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.43,0:16:20.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,必須是外國人 必須是他們的工作會損害我們國家的利益\N{\rENG}They had to be foreign citizens and they had to be working to harm our country.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.43,0:16:22.18,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們和您合作了嗎？\N{\rENG}And they cooperated with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.35,0:16:23.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,當然沒有\N{\rENG}Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.14,0:16:28.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,在華盛頓 沒人會就這樣跟你 分享他們的權力 史密斯調查員\N{\rENG}No one freely shares power in Washington, D.C., Agent Smith.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.48,0:16:31.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,你還是沒有可依據的法律 來授權...\N{\rENG}There is no law under which you can issue a warrant...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.40,0:16:33.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,來逮捕一個外國人...\N{\rENG}...for the arrest of an alien...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.40,0:16:36.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,而我已經證明了他可以被驅逐出境\N{\rENG}...when I have certified that he is subject to deportation?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.24,0:16:38.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒有任何證據的情況下 不行 檢察官\N{\rENG}Without any evidence, Mr. Attorney General, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.16,0:16:41.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 應該遵循正當法律程式 - 正當法律程式？\N{\rENG}- There exists a due process of law. - Due process of law?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.16,0:16:45.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 他們對我們國家有威脅啊？ - 或許是有...\N{\rENG}- What about the threat? - There might be a threat...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.87,0:16:47.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,或許？\N{\rENG}Might be?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.17,0:16:49.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,好吧 確實對我們國家有威脅\N{\rENG}Fine. There is a threat to our country.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.05,0:16:53.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,但沒有犯罪的證據 我們就沒有理由將其驅逐出境\N{\rENG}But with no proof of a crime, there's no cause for deportation.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.63,0:16:55.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,走著瞧吧\N{\rENG}We'll see about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.76,0:16:57.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,我會聯繫你的\N{\rENG}You'll be hearing from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.43,0:17:01.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,但他們的領導之一是 卡密內蒂先生\N{\rENG}But one of their heads was a Mr. Caminetti.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.10,0:17:06.85,CHT,,0,0,0,,他厭煩了我們的司法部 但他更加討厭的是另一個人\N{\rENG}He was weary of our Justice Department, but he hated one person even more.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.02,0:17:10.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是個天生的革命家...\N{\rENG}I am a revolutionist by nature...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.36,0:17:11.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,在這裡\N{\rENG}...and as such...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.61,0:17:15.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,我要呼籲反對和抵抗 侵略的權利\N{\rENG}...l claim the right to rebel and resist invasion...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.95,0:17:19.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,使用一切手段 包括暴力\N{\rENG}...by all means, force included.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.62,0:17:22.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,艾瑪·古德曼 她是激進運動的英雄人物\N{\rENG}Emma Goldman. She was the hero of the radical movement.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.08,0:17:27.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果我們可以把她交給卡密內蒂 他會毫不猶豫地將她驅逐出境\N{\rENG}If I could hand Caminetti Emma Goldman, he would deport her without a thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.75,0:17:30.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,但她是美國公民\N{\rENG}But she was a citizen.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.63,0:17:34.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,您需要休息一下嗎？\N{\rENG}Would you like to stop, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.05,0:17:40.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,不\N{\rENG}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.72,0:17:44.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,我知道今天的你想像這些很難 但曾經...\N{\rENG}I know it's hard for you to imagine today, but there was a time...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.39,0:17:49.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,普通的美國公民會擔心 他們的安全和生活 史密斯調查員\N{\rENG}...when the average American feared for their safety and survival, Agent Smith.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.90,0:17:54.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,在芝加哥 由共產主義勞工發起的 煤礦罷工造成了大面積停電\N{\rENG}In Chicago, a coal strike started by communist labor shut off all the power.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.03,0:17:56.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,接著就是騷亂\N{\rENG}Riots followed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.49,0:17:59.16,CHT,,0,0,0,,然後在停戰紀念日那天 華盛頓州的森特勒利亞...\N{\rENG}And on Armistice Day in Centralia, Washington...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.32,0:18:02.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,剛從戰場載譽歸來的老兵 被激進主義分子暗殺\N{\rENG}...veterans fresh back from the war were murdered by radicals.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.20,0:18:07.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,紅色革命的火焰 已經蔓延到了我們國家\N{\rENG}The red revolution had arrived on our soil.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.42,0:18:16.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,不 我們不能逐個擊破\N{\rENG}No, no. We can't take them down one by one.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.67,0:18:20.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,那樣他們會轉移到地下 那每個參議員的信箱裡都會有炸彈的危險\N{\rENG}They'll go underground and we'll have a bomb inside every senator's mailbox.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.72,0:18:23.85,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們需要同一時間的突襲 把他們一網打盡\N{\rENG}We need to have a simultaneous raid, hitting all of them at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.01,0:18:26.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,- “他們”又是誰？ - 你就是來解決這個問題的\N{\rENG}- Who are "they"? - You're here to find out.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.31,0:18:30.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,聽著 我需要我們國家每個激進分子 都有一張卡片來代表\N{\rENG}Now listen, I want a card on every radical person in this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.23,0:18:31.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,靠牆放 先生們\N{\rENG}Against the wall, gentlemen.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.15,0:18:35.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,我要知道他們是誰 從哪裡來 隸屬什麼組織 有什麼計畫\N{\rENG}I wanna know who, where they're from, what group, what they say.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.48,0:18:37.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,那些已經有犯罪記錄的人？\N{\rENG}Who have already committed crimes?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.24,0:18:41.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,我更關心的是他們是否有犯罪的打算 請靠牆放 謝謝\N{\rENG}I care more whether they intend to. Against the wall, gentlemen, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.95,0:18:44.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 我們有多少人？ - 現在只有你們四個\N{\rENG}- How many are on our team? - Only you four for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.87,0:18:46.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,我會把鎖安上\N{\rENG}I'll have locks installed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.83,0:18:49.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,不 甘迪小姐 那會吸引過多的注意\N{\rENG}No, Miss Gandy. That would bring too much attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.71,0:18:51.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,任何東西都不許按字母順序排列\N{\rENG}Nothing is to be alphabetically ordered.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.88,0:18:54.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,我要這些卡片以主題和類型分類\N{\rENG}I want the cards to be broken down into subjects and categories.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.96,0:18:57.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,這個系統應該簡潔明瞭\N{\rENG}Now, this system should be easy enough if explained.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.55,0:19:00.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果不是  找到特定的資訊就變得沒有可能\N{\rENG}If not, finding information should prove impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.30,0:19:05.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,不要相信任何人 甚至我們的同事探員\N{\rENG}And trust no one, not even our fellow agents.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.56,0:19:08.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,這裡半數的工作人員 還另有兼職\N{\rENG}Half our colleagues are on both sides of the payroll.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.56,0:19:11.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,但我們調查的犯罪並不是犯罪 只是犯罪的想法\N{\rENG}But the crimes we're investigating aren't crimes, they're ideas.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.69,0:19:12.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果你的這個想法...\N{\rENG}Well, if your idea...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.15,0:19:15.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,靠牆放 謝謝\N{\rENG}Against the wall, gentlemen. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.48,0:19:19.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,假如你的想法是來我們國家 圖謀推翻政權...\N{\rENG}If your idea is to come into our country and plot the overthrow of our government...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.74,0:19:21.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,那麼當然 這就是犯罪\N{\rENG}...then, yes, indeed, that is a crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.70,0:19:24.16,CHT,,0,0,0,,古德曼女士嫁給了一位美國公民\N{\rENG}Mrs. Goldman married a U.S. citizen.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.08,0:19:28.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,她嫁給的這個男人從未探監過她 但是這個男人...\N{\rENG}The man she married hasn't visited her once in prison, yet this man...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.75,0:19:31.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,自從婚禮以來就一直和此人同居的 他每晚都拜訪\N{\rENG}...the man she's lived with since her wedding, he visits nightly.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.92,0:19:34.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,假如你突襲了這群人 但毫無斬獲呢？\N{\rENG}What happens when we raid this list of yours and find nothing?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.13,0:19:38.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒有槍支 沒有炸彈 只是驅逐了無辜的人\N{\rENG}No guns, no bombs, just innocent people deported.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.63,0:19:41.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,這個國家的每個角落 都有美國公民...\N{\rENG}From every corner of this nation, the American people...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.93,0:19:45.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,敦促總檢察長有所行動\N{\rENG}...have urged the Attorney General to do something about this...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.18,0:19:47.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,還美國一份和平\N{\rENG}...and return the United States back to peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.51,0:19:50.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在我很樂意向帕爾默先生 傳達你的異議\N{\rENG}Now, I'm happy to send your objections to Mr. Palmer himself...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.60,0:19:53.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,但同時 要揭發古德曼小姐令人不齒的婚姻\N{\rENG}...but, in the meantime, expose Miss Goldman's sham marriage...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.85,0:19:57.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,你還得把你的衣服給換了\N{\rENG}...and you will change that suit of yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.27,0:19:59.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 你說什麼 約翰？ - 你的西服\N{\rENG}- Pardon me, John? - Your suit, sir, your suit.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.53,0:20:00.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,這裡不是酒吧\N{\rENG}This isn't a saloon.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.74,0:20:03.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,要尊重自己 更重要的是...\N{\rENG}Have respect for yourself, but, more importantly...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.28,0:20:04.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,尊重我們部門\N{\rENG}...have respect for this department.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.12,0:20:06.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,甘迪小姐？\N{\rENG}Miss Gandy?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.71,0:20:15.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,古德曼小姐 你是否是無政府主義者？\N{\rENG}Miss Goldman, are you an anarchist?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.63,0:20:17.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,我拒絕回答\N{\rENG}I decline to answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.21,0:20:19.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,那麼你否認自己是無政府主義者？\N{\rENG}Do you deny that you are an anarchist?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.46,0:20:21.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,我拒絕回答\N{\rENG}I decline to answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.63,0:20:25.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,你是否堅信應該推翻 美國政府的統治？\N{\rENG}Do you believe in the overthrow of the government of the United States?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.39,0:20:26.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,我拒絕回答\N{\rENG}I refuse to answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.05,0:20:29.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,你是否主張 暗殺公共官員？\N{\rENG}Do you advocate the assassination of public officials?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.72,0:20:32.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,我拒絕回答\N{\rENG}I refuse to answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.77,0:20:39.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,這位外國公民拒絕回答任何 這份法庭令中要求的問題\N{\rENG}This alien has refused to answer questions pertaining to the charges in the warrant...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.98,0:20:43.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,雖然我們已經給了她一切機會\N{\rENG}...notwithstanding the fact that every opportunity was afforded her.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.40,0:20:45.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,我的提議是驅逐出境\N{\rENG}I recommend deportation.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.62,0:20:50.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,就這樣 我們有了一個先例\N{\rENG}And just like that, we had our precedent.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.00,0:20:57.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,愛德格 我現在安排一下 情人節我們去派特森的出行？\N{\rENG}Edgar, should I arrange our travel to Paterson on Valentine's Day?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.17,0:21:00.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,當然 甘迪小姐\N{\rENG}Yes, of course, Miss Gandy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.18,0:21:09.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,2月14日 我乘坐火車 去了新澤西州的派特森\N{\rENG}I took the train to Paterson, New Jersey, on February 14th.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.64,0:21:11.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果我能抓住這些激進分子 哪怕他們只是犯了輕罪\N{\rENG}If I could catch these radicals red-handed...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.06,0:21:15.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,勞工部就必須把他們送上 回家的客船\N{\rENG}...then the Labor Department would have to put them all on boats back home.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.89,0:21:18.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,所以調查局的探員們 還有當地警力...\N{\rENG}So agents of the Bureau, alongside local police...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.61,0:21:22.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,開始在已知有共產主義激進分子的地方 集聚起來準備突襲\N{\rENG}...began raiding gathering places of known communist radicals...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.86,0:21:25.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,全國上下都是\N{\rENG}...all across this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.86,0:21:28.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,這些人持械 行為暴力\N{\rENG}These people are armed and violent.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.82,0:21:31.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,這些人為了拘捕可以大開殺戒\N{\rENG}They're prepared to kill to avoid capture.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.62,0:21:34.16,CHT,,0,0,0,,拿一支 去吧\N{\rENG}Take one. Go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.71,0:21:37.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 我們允許用這個嗎？ - 這些算是禮物\N{\rENG}- Are we allowed to use these, sir? - These are gifts.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.29,0:21:40.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒有法律可以阻止我們使用自己的武器\N{\rENG}There is no law that prevents us from using our own weapons.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.21,0:21:42.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,先生們 拿好自己的槍\N{\rENG}Gentlemen, grab your guns.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.72,0:21:47.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,動作快\N{\rENG}Gentlemen, quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.39,0:21:52.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,行動\N{\rENG}Let's move.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.90,0:22:06.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,員警！這是突擊檢查！\N{\rENG}Police! This is a raid!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.46,0:22:19.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,他要從窗子逃走了 快阻止！\N{\rENG}He's going for the window, stop him!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.32,0:22:52.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,夠了！\N{\rENG}That's enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.84,0:23:15.85,CHT,,0,0,0,,傳單內容完全吻合\N{\rENG}The leaflets matched exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.18,0:23:18.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們破了爆炸案\N{\rENG}We'd solved the bombings.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.02,0:23:23.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,最終 我們逮捕了將近 4000名共產主義激進分子\N{\rENG}And, in the end, we arrested nearly 4000 communist radicals...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.56,0:23:25.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,驅逐出境了500多人\N{\rENG}...and deported over 500 of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.15,0:23:31.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,任務完成得很靠運氣 也冒著巨大的個人風險\N{\rENG}It was accomplished against great odds and at great personal peril.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.28,0:23:39.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們發現了假冒的記者 五支手槍 兩支自動槍\N{\rENG}They found the counterfeiting press, five pistols, two automatics.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.54,0:23:43.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,在特雷敦 他們找到了火藥 銅 銅絲 還有電池\N{\rENG}And in Trenton, they found gunpowder, copper, brass wire, and batteries.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.08,0:23:46.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 一個軍工廠 - 是\N{\rENG}- A bomb factory. - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.50,0:23:52.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,底特律逮捕了120人 費城有41人 這裡目前有17人\N{\rENG}One hundred and twenty arrests in Detroit, 41 in Philadelphia, and 17 here so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.01,0:23:56.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,但調查局裡和此事有關的人 都丟了飯碗 是嗎？\N{\rENG}But everyone in the Bureau involved lost theirjob, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.30,0:23:57.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,甚至帕爾默他自己？\N{\rENG}Even Palmer himself?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.85,0:23:59.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,有些確實 但也算是教訓\N{\rENG}Some did, and there's the lesson.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.14,0:24:02.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,你可以看到 爆炸案停止了 恢復了和平\N{\rENG}You see, the bombs stopped, and peace came.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.81,0:24:05.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,美國人民逐漸忘記了 曾經有如此一種威脅\N{\rENG}The American people had forgotten there ever was a threat.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.02,0:24:08.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,所以當政治對手們 攻擊帕爾默的時候...\N{\rENG}So when political adversaries attacked Palmer...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.03,0:24:11.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,聲稱保護國家不受共產主義侵蝕...\N{\rENG}...for trying to protect this nation from communism...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.86,0:24:13.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們的同胞們就這樣熟視無睹\N{\rENG}...our countrymen allowed it to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.66,0:24:19.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,因為就像今天 他們已經忘記了 那些炸彈 那些流血犧牲 那些恐懼\N{\rENG}Because like today, they've forgotten the bombs, the blood, the fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.74,0:24:22.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,但為什麼是帕爾默而不是你 因為其實是你安排了那些突襲\N{\rENG}But why Palmer and not you, if you orchestrated the raids?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.92,0:24:28.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,我當時只有24歲 只是服從命令\N{\rENG}I was 24 years old, Agent Smith. I was just following orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.50,0:24:29.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,我明白\N{\rENG}I understand, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.09,0:24:34.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果沒有這次行動 你很有可能就出生在一個共產主義的國家\N{\rENG}And if we hadn't, you may very well have been born into a communist state...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.51,0:24:37.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,而不是你今天如此熱愛的祖國\N{\rENG}...rather than the country you love today.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.39,0:24:39.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 我說的對嗎？ - 當然\N{\rENG}- Am I right? - Of course, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.47,0:24:40.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,嗯\N{\rENG}Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.68,0:24:41.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,愛德格？\N{\rENG}Edgar?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.14,0:24:44.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,別管他\N{\rENG}Ignore him.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.85,0:24:45.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,愛德格？\N{\rENG}Edgar?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.61,0:24:49.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,我正在開會 托爾森 馬上就出去\N{\rENG}I am in a meeting, Mr. Tolson. I'll be out in a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.07,0:24:53.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,不要忘記跟檢察官的會面 愛德格\N{\rENG}Don't forget about your appointment with the Attorney General, Edgar.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.57,0:24:58.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,文件還沒準備好 托爾森 你走吧\N{\rENG}Files are not yet completed, Mr. Tolson. Please go away.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.91,0:25:00.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝\N{\rENG}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.91,0:25:07.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝您 抱歉 我今晚就會寫好這一章\N{\rENG}Thank you, sir. I apologize. I'll finish this chapter tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.04,0:25:10.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,很好 史密斯調查員\N{\rENG}Very well, Agent Smith.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.10,0:25:23.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,在學校 他們有提起 我是如何做到這個位置的嗎？\N{\rENG}In the Academy, do they tell the story of how I got here?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.77,0:25:26.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的 你被新的檢察官 叫到他的辦公室...\N{\rENG}Yes, sir. Uh, you were called into the new Attorney General's office...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.15,0:25:30.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 哈蘭·菲斯克·斯通 - 是的，斯通總檢察長\N{\rENG}- Harlan Fiske Stone. - Yes, sir, Attorney General Stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.44,0:25:33.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,他讓你去他的辦公室  讓你坐下\N{\rENG}He called you into his office and told you to sit down, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.40,0:25:35.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,芝加哥有十多個空缺職位\N{\rENG}Sir, there are over a dozen vacancies in Chicago.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.99,0:25:39.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,搶劫率正在攀升 或許對調查局有利的是...\N{\rENG}And with the robbery rates rising, it would profit the Bureau...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.20,0:25:41.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們開始填補這些空缺 努力復蘇\N{\rENG}...to start filling vacancies and make recoveries.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.62,0:25:46.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,我有整理潛在犯罪嫌疑人的資料 經過國會的聽證會...\N{\rENG}I have files on potential suspects, and with a congressional hearing...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.16,0:25:50.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,別激動 孩子 不是你叫我來開會的 是我叫你 坐下吧\N{\rENG}Lower the treble, son. You didn't call this meeting, I did. Sit down.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.63,0:25:52.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,是\N{\rENG}Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.63,0:25:57.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,這裡每個和你共事過的人都離開了 而且事出有因\N{\rENG}Everyone you've worked with here is gone. And there's a reason for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.01,0:26:03.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,調查局充斥著惡劣的氛圍 你也同意吧？\N{\rENG}This Bureau is of exceedingly bad odor. Would you agree?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.02,0:26:05.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rENG}Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.10,0:26:08.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,並無冒犯之意 你似乎也沒有什麼社交\N{\rENG}And, no offense, you seem to have no social life.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.56,0:26:13.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒有老婆 沒有女友 據我所知 甚至朋友都沒有\N{\rENG}No wife, no girlfriend. As far as I can tell, no pals at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.53,0:26:18.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,確實是這樣\N{\rENG}That is accurate, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.24,0:26:22.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,你還旁若無人地癡迷著 那亂七八糟的指紋系統\N{\rENG}And you're shamelessly distracted by this hodgepodge fingerprinting affair.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.58,0:26:27.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,假如我們可以將所有指紋都集中到這裡 這絕不會是亂七八糟的事 我可以保證\N{\rENG}Sir, it wouldn't be hodgepodge if we could centralize the prints here, I assure you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.66,0:26:29.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,這最多也就是一種投機學\N{\rENG}It's a speculative science at best.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.42,0:26:32.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rENG}Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.25,0:26:35.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們為什麼都叫你“飛毛腿”？\N{\rENG}And why do they call you Speed?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.38,0:26:37.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,誰這麼叫我了？\N{\rENG}Who calls me that?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.59,0:26:40.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們都這樣 不過很明顯是在你背後\N{\rENG}They all do, behind your back, evidently.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.18,0:26:47.18,CHT,,0,0,0,,我10歲的時候給雜貨店送外賣 積攢了這個名聲\N{\rENG}I gained a reputation for delivering groceries when I was 10 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.35,0:26:51.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,我在我們街坊是速度最快的 這只是個外號\N{\rENG}I was the fastest in the neighborhood. It was just a nickname.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.27,0:26:53.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,你確定他們不是在說你說話的方式？\N{\rENG}You sure it's not for the way you talk?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.15,0:26:56.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,大概吧\N{\rENG}Perhaps, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.82,0:27:04.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,年輕人 我希望你出任 調查局的局長\N{\rENG}Young man, I want you to be acting director of the Bureau of investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.08,0:27:11.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,我會接受這個職務 斯通先生 但有一些條件\N{\rENG}I will take the job, Mr. Stone, but only on certain conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.59,0:27:15.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,什麼條件？\N{\rENG}What are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.25,0:27:21.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,這個調查局必須和政治獨立開 不能成為政治的代言人\N{\rENG}The Bureau must be divorced from politics and not be a catchall for political hacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.89,0:27:25.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,新人必須有大學文憑\N{\rENG}Recruits must be college-educated.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.35,0:27:28.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,任用的人必須體面\N{\rENG}Appointments must be based on merit.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.22,0:27:32.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,得到升職的人必須有嫺熟的工作能力\N{\rENG}Promotions will be made on proven ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.48,0:27:36.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,還有 這個調查局僅由您一人負責\N{\rENG}And, well, the Bureau will be responsible only to you, sir...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.57,0:27:38.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,總檢察長\N{\rENG}...the Attorney General.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.03,0:27:44.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,換做其他條件 我也不會給你這份工作\N{\rENG}I wouldn't give you the job under any other conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.70,0:27:48.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,就這樣了 日安\N{\rENG}That's all. Good day.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.54,0:27:52.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝您\N{\rENG}Well, thank you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.87,0:27:56.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,我已決定 會從調查局剔除那些...\N{\rENG}I am determined to summarily dismiss from this Bureau...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.09,0:28:00.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,沉迷於酒精的人\N{\rENG}...any employee whom I find indulging in the use of intoxicants.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.01,0:28:04.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,我相信 當一個人成為調查局的一份子...\N{\rENG}It is my belief that when a man becomes a part of this Bureau...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.93,0:28:10.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,他必須規範自己的行為 不管官方還是非官方\N{\rENG}...he must so conduct himself, both officially and unofficially...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.27,0:28:13.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,以消除可能存在的 哪怕最小的批判聲\N{\rENG}...as to eliminate even the slightest possibility of criticism...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.94,0:28:15.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,批判他品行的聲音\N{\rENG}...as to his conduct.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.15,0:28:20.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 你叫什麼名字？ - 威廉姆斯 先生\N{\rENG}- And what is your name, sir? - Agent Williams, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.11,0:28:23.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 很高興見到你 威廉姆斯探員 - 您也是\N{\rENG}- Pleasure to meet you, Agent Williams. - You too, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.95,0:28:27.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,你的名字呢？\N{\rENG}And your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.24,0:28:28.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,卡福利探員\N{\rENG}Agent Caffrey, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.95,0:28:31.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 你的任務是？ - 我正要前往坎薩斯城\N{\rENG}- Your assignment? - I'm headed to Kansas City...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.45,0:28:34.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,協助調查銀行搶劫犯弗蘭克·納什\N{\rENG}...to aid in the search for bank robber Frank Nash, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.42,0:28:36.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是一項危險的任務 你回來以後...\N{\rENG}Mm, that is dangerous work, and when you return...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.67,0:28:39.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,你會因你的努力工作得到嘉獎\N{\rENG}...you will be rewarded for your service.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.97,0:28:47.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,斯托克斯探員 你還是很喜歡留鬍子嘛？\N{\rENG}You still fancy facial hair, Agent Stokes?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.18,0:28:50.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 女士們喜歡 - 嗯\N{\rENG}- The ladies appreciate it. - Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.85,0:28:54.18,CHT,,0,0,0,,那我是不是可以認為 女士們的意見比調查局的意見更重要？\N{\rENG}And I suppose the ladies' opinions are more important than the Bureau's?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.35,0:28:55.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,不\N{\rENG}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.56,0:28:57.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,長官\N{\rENG}Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.81,0:29:00.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,或許你在警察局工作更合適...\N{\rENG}Perhaps you are better suited for the police force...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.44,0:29:02.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,相比在調查局\N{\rENG}...than the Bureau of investigations.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.70,0:29:06.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,我已經為司法部和調查局效力了7年\N{\rENG}I've been with the Department and the Bureau for seven years.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.66,0:29:07.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,幾乎跟你一樣長時間\N{\rENG}Almost as long as you.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.62,0:29:09.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,不\N{\rENG}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.20,0:29:14.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,你在舊的調查局工作了7年 那個舊的已經不復存在了\N{\rENG}You were with the old Bureau seven years, and that Bureau is now gone, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.46,0:29:16.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,你也是一樣\N{\rENG}And so are you.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.00,0:29:21.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,我很快就解雇了所有 不符合我要求的探員\N{\rENG}I quickly dismissed all agents
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.30,0:29:23.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,教育背景 身體條件...\N{\rENG}Education, physical fitness...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.09,0:29:26.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,最重要的是 忠誠\N{\rENG}...but, above all, loyalty.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.64,0:29:34.18,CHT,,0,0,0,,我做了兩套 一樣的裁剪 不同花紋\N{\rENG}I've had two made. Same cut, different pattern.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.19,0:29:39.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,還有給你的兩套西裝 禮拜五就送來了\N{\rENG}And two suits for you. They'll be delivered on Friday.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.19,0:29:40.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝 母親\N{\rENG}Thank you, Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.11,0:29:46.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是鉑金的...\N{\rENG}It's platinum...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.66,0:29:51.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,六顆鑽石 一顆星光藍寶石\N{\rENG}...six diamonds and a star sapphire.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.37,0:29:56.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,真是太美了 母親\N{\rENG}- Heh. - It's absolutely beautiful, Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.21,0:29:57.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝\N{\rENG}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.21,0:30:03.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,我跟整個街坊鄰居都說起了你 他們都知道了\N{\rENG}I've told the whole neighborhood about you. They all know.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.88,0:30:07.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,不 我不該吃 我已經在增重了\N{\rENG}No, I shouldn't, I've been gaining weight, Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.72,0:30:11.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,那是結實的體重 一個男人結結實實長點肉沒錯\N{\rENG}It's solid weight. There's nothing wrong with solid weight on a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.39,0:30:15.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 好吧 - 我真是太為你驕傲了 愛德格\N{\rENG}- All right. - I'm so incredibly proud of you, Edgar.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.27,0:30:24.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,我開始為你做一個冊子了\N{\rENG}I'm starting an album for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.40,0:30:28.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,我會把所有材料都收集進去 這只是個開始\N{\rENG}I'm gonna put everything in it. This is just the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.74,0:30:35.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,“約翰·胡佛被任命為 調查局的局長”\N{\rENG}"Johnny Hoover appointed acting director of the Bureau of investigations."
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.29,0:30:36.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,你能讀讀這個嗎？\N{\rENG}Can you read that?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.42,0:30:43.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,為叔叔自豪嗎？\N{\rENG}You proud of your uncle?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.27,0:31:00.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,先生們\N{\rENG}Gentlemen.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.23,0:31:06.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,我想介紹一下你 跟我來\N{\rENG}I want to introduce you. Come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.07,0:31:10.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,愛德格 很高興見到你\N{\rENG}Edgar, good to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.91,0:31:12.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,很高興見到你 勞倫斯\N{\rENG}Good to see you, Lawrence.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.45,0:31:14.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,我想向你介紹克萊德·托爾森先生\N{\rENG}I'd like to introduce you to Mr. Clyde Tolson.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.12,0:31:17.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,今晚剛從喬治華盛頓大學的法學院畢業\N{\rENG}Graduated from George Washington University tonight with a law degree.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.08,0:31:19.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,嗯\N{\rENG}Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.29,0:31:20.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,祝賀你 托爾森先生\N{\rENG}Congratulations, Mr. Tolson.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.79,0:31:24.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝你 胡佛先生 我想你應該是我校最傑出的校友之一了\N{\rENG}Thank you, Mr. Hoover. I believe you are one of our most distinguished alumni.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.96,0:31:28.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,噢 是的 我確實是從同個學校畢業的\N{\rENG}I did, yes. L, uh, do have a degree from the school, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.09,0:31:34.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,我很喜歡你的西服 托爾森先生 羅倫斯 你該學著點\N{\rENG}I was admiring your suit, Mr. Tolson. You should take a lesson, Lawrence.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.72,0:31:37.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝 這是在加芬克爾百貨商店定制的\N{\rENG}Thank you, sir. It's a custom cut, from Garfinkel's department store.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.64,0:31:39.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,這樣\N{\rENG}Ah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.60,0:31:43.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,你有名片嗎 托爾森先生？\N{\rENG}Do you have a card, Mr. Tolson?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.81,0:31:46.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,當然 我有\N{\rENG}I do, yes, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.44,0:31:48.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是我的\N{\rENG}Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.82,0:31:50.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,很高興見到你 勞倫斯\N{\rENG}Good to see you, Lawrence.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.61,0:31:52.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝您\N{\rENG}Thank you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.20,0:32:00.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,“良好的教育，被高度推薦 可以保證五年的工作時間”\N{\rENG}"Well-educated, highly recommended, willing to guarantee five years service.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.87,0:32:03.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,“家人在紐約 有剛出生的孩子”\N{\rENG}Has a family in New York and a new baby."
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.71,0:32:04.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,這個不用面試\N{\rENG}No interview.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.38,0:32:07.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,是因為紐約的家人還是剛出生的孩子？\N{\rENG}The family in New York or the baby?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.67,0:32:11.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,甘迪小姐 五年是不夠的 我們需要一個願意奉獻一生的人\N{\rENG}Miss Gandy, five years is not enough. We need men willing to dedicate their lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.63,0:32:13.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在有多少個了？\N{\rENG}How many is that so far?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.30,0:32:18.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 320個被拒 21個面試者 - 嗯\N{\rENG}- That's 320 denied and 21 interviews. - Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.72,0:32:22.85,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們有收到一份 來自托爾森先生的申請嗎？\N{\rENG}Did we receive an application from a Mr. Tolson?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.02,0:32:25.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,有\N{\rENG}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.52,0:32:31.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,這裡 他的報告陳述道 他自信 優雅...\N{\rENG}Yes, his report states he has confidence, poise...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.32,0:32:33.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,用詞精准\N{\rENG}...his diction is excellent.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.91,0:32:38.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,雖然身體條件沒問題 但並不希望做棘手的工作\N{\rENG}But although physically fitted for it, might be displeased with rugged work.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.58,0:32:42.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,他只是想為自己的個人法律實踐 積攢一些經驗\N{\rENG}His only interest is to gain experience that would benefit a private law practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.04,0:32:46.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,他也沒有說起 願意在這裡工作多長時間...\N{\rENG}And he has no interest in being here for any period of time...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.79,0:32:49.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,那只會讓就業更加投機\N{\rENG}...which would render employment speculative.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.46,0:32:51.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,恩\N{\rENG}Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.05,0:32:54.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,他有一封推薦信...\N{\rENG}He did receive a letter of recommendation...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.93,0:32:58.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,來自戰爭部長的行政助理\N{\rENG}...from the executive assistant of the Secretary of War.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.06,0:33:01.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,這很好嘛\N{\rENG}That's fantastic, Miss Gandy.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.18,0:33:08.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,信裡提到托爾森先生... 對女人沒有特別的興趣\N{\rENG}Yes. It mentions here that Mr. Tolson showed no particular interest in women.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.73,0:33:16.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,再一次地 我們最好的一些探員 之所以如此優秀 是因為他們沒有家庭的負擔\N{\rENG}Then again, some of our best agents excel because they have no family encumbrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.24,0:33:20.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的 你是對的 安排面試\N{\rENG}Yes, you're right. Set up an interview.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.54,0:33:25.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,你知道問題是什麼嗎 甘迪？\N{\rENG}You know what the problem is, Miss Gandy?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.75,0:33:28.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,這些人 他們並不... 並不崇拜我\N{\rENG}These men, they don't... They don't look up to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.88,0:33:30.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們當然崇拜你\N{\rENG}Of course they do.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.21,0:33:35.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,我這並不是比喻 我就是說 他們不崇拜我\N{\rENG}I don't mean figuratively. I mean they don't look up to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.30,0:33:39.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,假如你可以坐在桌子後面 來進行面試...\N{\rENG}Well, if you could conduct the entire interview from behind your desk...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.43,0:33:44.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,而不是在辦公室走來走去 我可以讓他們崇拜你\N{\rENG}...instead of walking about the office, I could correct that.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.81,0:33:46.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,那確實是\N{\rENG}Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.73,0:33:52.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,甘迪 假如我有某位當權人士的 秘密資料...\N{\rENG}Miss Gandy, suppose I had information on someone in a position of power...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.11,0:33:56.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,有害的信息\N{\rENG}...harmful information.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.11,0:33:59.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,毀滅這些資料有悖我的意圖...\N{\rENG}It goes against my nature to destroy such information...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.87,0:34:02.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,但我也不放心放在一般的資料一起\N{\rENG}...but I don't trust it in the general files either.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.95,0:34:06.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,我能拜託你嗎？\N{\rENG}Could I trust it with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.79,0:34:10.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們或許可以保存一些絕密資料？\N{\rENG}If we were to create a confidential file?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.79,0:34:13.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,當然 愛德格\N{\rENG}Of course, Edgar.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.67,0:34:16.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝你 甘迪\N{\rENG}Thank you, Miss Gandy.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.89,0:34:23.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,資訊就是力量\N{\rENG}Information is power.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.26,0:34:26.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,資訊保護我們1919年 不受共產主義分子危害\N{\rENG}It protected us from the communists in 1919...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.39,0:34:30.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,自那以後 就由聯邦調查局 小心地收集 整理  維護\N{\rENG}...and since has been vigilantly collected, organized, and maintained by our FBl.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.73,0:34:35.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,甘迺迪總檢察長辦公室\N{\rENG}Attorney General Kennedy's Office.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.74,0:34:44.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,你一直都有這個壁爐嗎 還是後來安的？\N{\rENG}Did you always have this fireplace or did you have it put in?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.54,0:34:45.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,後來安的\N{\rENG}It was put in.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.75,0:34:48.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,你在那間屋子裝竊聽器是做什麼？\N{\rENG}What were you doing with wiretaps in that house?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.54,0:34:53.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,是你讓我追查這些犯罪線索的 甘迺迪先生\N{\rENG}You asked that I pursue this organized crime element, Mr. Kennedy...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.67,0:34:56.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,我也照做了 勤勤懇懇\N{\rENG}...and I did so, sir, with diligence.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.84,0:34:59.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 你會用這個壁爐嗎？ - 很少\N{\rENG}- Do you use the fireplace? - Rarely.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.30,0:35:00.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,還有誰聽過這個錄音？\N{\rENG}Who else has heard the recording?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.84,0:35:05.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,我已經將資料封為 個人的 高度機密的\N{\rENG}I have filed the matter personal and confidential.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.68,0:35:07.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,只有我才能取得這些資料\N{\rENG}I'm the only person with access to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.23,0:35:11.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,胡佛先生 我是讓你追查 真正的威脅\N{\rENG}Mr. Hoover, I asked you to pursue a real threat.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.06,0:35:15.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,相反地 你公然否認 有組織的犯罪的存在\N{\rENG}Instead, you've publicly denied the existence of organized crime...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.86,0:35:18.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在還有這重大的恐嚇\N{\rENG}...and now this gross display of intimidation.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.36,0:35:22.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,檢察官  我只是服從命令\N{\rENG}Mr. Attorney General, I was only following orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.20,0:35:24.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們竊聽了洛杉磯 一幢房子的地下室\N{\rENG}We bugged the basement of a home in Los Angeles...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.62,0:35:27.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,那是一群違法犯罪者聚會的地方\N{\rENG}...that was a known gathering place for lawbreakers.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.70,0:35:32.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,我怎麼知道一個東德的共產主義分子 會在那裡...\N{\rENG}How was I to know that an East German communist would be down there...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.29,0:35:36.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,會在那裡跟你的哥哥 也就是美國總統 上床？\N{\rENG}...having sex with your brother, the President of the United States?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.05,0:35:40.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,不要射殺那些探員 我是來保護你們倆的\N{\rENG}Do not shoot the messenger, sir. I am here to protect you both.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.80,0:35:42.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,記住這一點\N{\rENG}Remember that.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.43,0:35:47.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,你想讓我怎樣？\N{\rENG}What do you want from me?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.06,0:35:52.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果這段資料公開...\N{\rENG}If this information were to go public...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.90,0:35:57.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,會造成對你們兄弟倆領導能力 大面積的質疑\N{\rENG}...it would create widespread distrust in your brother's leadership capabilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.19,0:36:01.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,不僅這些 我還掌控我們國家最高的福利\N{\rENG}And above all else, I hold the well-being of our country paramount.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.90,0:36:04.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,那我該怎麼做呢 胡佛先生？\N{\rENG}So how may I help you, Mr. Hoover?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.70,0:36:09.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,倘若我得幫你追查 你認為是威脅的東西\N{\rENG}Well, if I am to pursue the elements that you consider a threat...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.75,0:36:13.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,我想要您允許我有同樣的權力...\N{\rENG}...l humbly request that you allow me the same power and access...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.58,0:36:16.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,來追查我認為有重大威脅的人\N{\rENG}...to follow the groups that I see as an immediate threat.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.59,0:36:18.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,這已經不是1920年了\N{\rENG}It's not 1920 anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.72,0:36:22.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,你知道斯坦利·列維森是誰嗎？\N{\rENG}You know who Stanley Levinson is, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.39,0:36:25.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,一個律師\N{\rENG}A lawyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.10,0:36:30.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,一個白人 共產主義律師 組織著最高層...\N{\rENG}A white, communist lawyer organizing at the highest levels...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.27,0:36:32.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,包括南方基督教領袖會議\N{\rENG}...including the SCLC.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.19,0:36:33.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在他們的群體正在壯大\N{\rENG}Now, their group is growing.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.10,0:36:36.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們完全自給自足...\N{\rENG}They are entirely self-serving...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.52,0:36:40.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們的領導權已經公然 危及到我們的部門\N{\rENG}...and their leadership is openly critical of this department here.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.28,0:36:42.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,你看了我發過來的備忘嗎？\N{\rENG}Did you read the memos that I sent?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.20,0:36:44.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,不 還沒有\N{\rENG}No, no, I can't say that I have.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.45,0:36:48.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,甘迺迪先生 我在這裡寫了\N{\rENG}It says right here, Mr. Kennedy.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.62,0:36:50.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們宣稱我們是...\N{\rENG}They claim we are...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.45,0:36:53.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,“不能給哪怕最滔天最極惡的犯罪定罪”\N{\rENG}..."unable to get convictions in even the worst, most heinous crimes..."
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.08,0:36:57.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們還“在壓力下動搖”\N{\rENG}...and that we have "faltered under the pressure, complexities...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.38,0:36:59.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,“因為部門的複雜性和義務” 白紙黑字印出來\N{\rENG}...and responsibilities of our office," in print.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.84,0:37:03.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 就在這《華盛頓郵報》上 - 你就受不了一點點的批評？\N{\rENG}- Right here in "The Washington Post." - You can't bear a little criticism?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.72,0:37:05.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,這取決於批評的目的了\N{\rENG}Well, it depends on what their aim is.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.14,0:37:08.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們正在聚集一股很客觀的力量\N{\rENG}They are gaining considerable power.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.47,0:37:11.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們有優先權 單單關注自己的事\N{\rENG}Their priorities are singularly focused on their own issues.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.52,0:37:13.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們在試圖煽動叛亂\N{\rENG}They are trying to incite revolt.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.64,0:37:17.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,顯然 他們看上去更多的批評你的部門 而不是我的\N{\rENG}Frankly, they sound more critical of your office than mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.19,0:37:21.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,共產主義有了新的局面了 愛德格 這件事不是的\N{\rENG}There's a new face to communism, Edgar, and this isn't it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.15,0:37:25.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,共產主義更多地是海外的威脅 不是國內的\N{\rENG}Communism is a foreign threat now, not domestic.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.16,0:37:31.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,甘迺迪先生 遠在你出生以前...\N{\rENG}Mr. Kennedy, before you were even born...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.83,0:37:36.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,我從一位叫米切爾·帕爾默先生口中 聽到了一模一樣的說辭\N{\rENG}...l heard that very same argument from a Mr. Mitchell Palmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.33,0:37:39.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,你知道最後是什麼 讓他改變自己的想法嗎？\N{\rENG}Do you know what it took to change his mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.17,0:37:41.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,一枚炸彈\N{\rENG}A bomb.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.84,0:37:45.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,假如他在1919年的那天 在他的椅子上多坐五分鐘\N{\rENG}If he would have sat in his rocking chair five more minutes in 1919...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.59,0:37:49.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們就只能發現他的手指頭了\N{\rENG}...we'd have been lucky enough to find an intact index finger.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.76,0:37:53.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在 我不想讓這些事 發生在你和你哥哥身上\N{\rENG}Now, I do not want that to happen to you or your brother, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.02,0:37:57.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒理由 讓我們都得不到我們想要的\N{\rENG}There's no reason we both can't get what we want.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.35,0:38:01.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們可以在兩個前線都發動戰爭 你明白我的意思嗎？\N{\rENG}We can wage a war on two fronts, sir. You understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.90,0:38:06.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,你可以走了 胡佛先生\N{\rENG}You can go now, Mr. Hoover.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.70,0:38:10.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,是\N{\rENG}Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.12,0:38:14.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,把副本留下給我\N{\rENG}Please leave the transcripts here with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.75,0:38:18.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,是\N{\rENG}Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.80,0:38:26.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,噢 也可以讓你哥哥看看這些\N{\rENG}Oh, and feel free and share them with your brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.88,0:38:33.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,讓他知道 我自己也留了一份存檔\N{\rENG}Oh, and let him know that I have a copy of my own in safekeeping.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.87,0:38:52.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,您4點的面試者到了\N{\rENG}- Unh. - Your 4:00 is here, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.12,0:38:55.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝你 甘迪 讓他進來吧\N{\rENG}Thank you, Miss Gandy. Send him right in, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.87,0:39:03.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,請坐吧 托爾森先生\N{\rENG}Please, have a seat, Mr. Tolson.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.38,0:39:07.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 胡佛先生 謝謝您給我這次機會 - 請吧\N{\rENG}- Mr. Hoover, thank you for this opportunity. - Yes. Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.26,0:39:09.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 請坐 - 謝謝\N{\rENG}- Have a seat. - Thank you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.76,0:39:13.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,你的申請材料有幾個問題 托爾森先生\N{\rENG}There were several problems with your application, Mr. Tolson...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.39,0:39:16.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,且不提其實你並不...\N{\rENG}...not the least of which is the fact that you did not show...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.47,0:39:18.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,符合調查局的條件...\N{\rENG}...the proper requirement to the Bureau...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.44,0:39:24.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,也沒有要保護美國人民的忠心...\N{\rENG}...nor the proper dedication to protecting the American people...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.23,0:39:25.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,以美國自己的方式\N{\rENG}...and the American way.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.44,0:39:27.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,我必須告訴你的是\N{\rENG}May I remind you that this is not a platform...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.03,0:39:31.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,這裡不是給你的個人法律實踐 發工資的地方 托爾森先生\N{\rENG}...to a fatter paycheck in private practice, Mr. Tolson?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.45,0:39:38.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,有什麼問題嗎 托爾森先生？\N{\rENG}Is there something the matter, Mr. Tolson?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.45,0:39:40.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,不\N{\rENG}No, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.62,0:39:43.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,這鍛煉是所有探員都要求的嗎？\N{\rENG}Ls exercise a requirement for all agents, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.88,0:39:49.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的 我們所有的探員 都需要有最好的身體條件\N{\rENG}Yes. All our agents need to be in top physical condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.97,0:39:54.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們必須對公眾之敵百發百中\N{\rENG}We must outsmart and outmatch the public enemy at every turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.47,0:39:56.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,當然\N{\rENG}Yes, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.18,0:39:59.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,所以您經常做什麼來健身？\N{\rENG}So, uh, what routine do you do, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.64,0:40:03.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,俯臥撐 仰臥起坐 還有下蹲運動\N{\rENG}Push-ups, sit-ups, and squatting.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.48,0:40:05.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,這樣\N{\rENG}I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.94,0:40:07.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,我來幫你整理一下窗簾吧？\N{\rENG}Would you like me to fix the curtain?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.40,0:40:09.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,或許可以開點窗\N{\rENG}Or perhaps I could open a window.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.15,0:40:12.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,運動之後我喜歡來一些新鮮空氣\N{\rENG}I always prefer a little bit of air after exercise.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.78,0:40:14.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,你呢？\N{\rENG}Don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.49,0:40:16.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果你喜歡的話\N{\rENG}If it would please you.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.12,0:40:21.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,我或許在簡歷方面不如他人...\N{\rENG}And, sir, where I may fall short in terms of resume...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.12,0:40:25.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,但其他方面  我的忠誠度遠遠超過他們\N{\rENG}...l apparently far exceed the rest in terms of honesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.92,0:40:28.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,我並未因為這個工作而說謊\N{\rENG}I didn't lie to get this appointment, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.75,0:40:31.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,不像其他人 是的 我希望做法律實踐...\N{\rENG}Like the rest, yes, I would like to start a practice...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.38,0:40:37.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,但我也可以做其他事 倘若有不錯的機會\N{\rENG}...but I could be persuaded otherwise if the right opportunities were to arise.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.51,0:40:40.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,嗯\N{\rENG}Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.56,0:40:44.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,有道理 托爾森先生\N{\rENG}Fair enough, Mr. Tolson.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.19,0:40:47.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,有道理\N{\rENG}Fair enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.29,0:41:02.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,這袖子看上去長度正好\N{\rENG}These sleeves seem to be the correct length.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.46,0:41:04.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,我找到兩條領帶給你選\N{\rENG}I found you two tie options.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.17,0:41:06.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,這條更加時髦...\N{\rENG}This one is a bit more fashion-forward...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.54,0:41:09.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,更好的搭配這套西服 包括剪裁和材質\N{\rENG}...but it would complement this suit and cut and fabric.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.25,0:41:10.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,你不覺得有點太扎眼嗎？\N{\rENG}It's too loud, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.96,0:41:13.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,太扎眼？好吧 所以我還給你找了個後備\N{\rENG}Too loud? Okay, which is why I found this one, the backup.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.84,0:41:18.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 這條更有領導人氣質 更... - 更含蓄些 我同意\N{\rENG}- It's a bit more directorial, a little bit more... - It's a little bit more reserved, I agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.72,0:41:22.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們留著這條作候補吧 謝謝你 克萊德\N{\rENG}Let's keep this as a second option, please. Thank you, Clyde.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.73,0:41:26.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,你是約翰·胡佛先生嗎？\N{\rENG}Are you Mr. John Hoover?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.90,0:41:28.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,是我 有問題嗎？\N{\rENG}I am. Is there a problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.36,0:41:32.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,似乎有位約翰·胡佛先生 在我們這裡信用度很差\N{\rENG}It seems there's a Mr. John Hoover whose credit has gone bad with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.65,0:41:34.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,看上去就是你了\N{\rENG}That would appear to be you.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.36,0:41:36.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,肯定不是我 我保證\N{\rENG}That is not me, sir, on my word.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.16,0:41:41.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,我母親叫我愛德格 我侄女叫我J.E. 我簽名都簽約翰·E 而不是約翰\N{\rENG}My mother calls me Edgar, my niece calls me J.E., and I sign John E., not John.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.12,0:41:45.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,假如您是托爾森先生的朋友...\N{\rENG}Well, sir, if you're a friend of Mr. Tolson's...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.04,0:41:49.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,就再選一個名字 重新申請一次\N{\rENG}...just choose one name and reapply.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.75,0:41:51.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\rENG}All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.21,0:41:53.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,非常感謝\N{\rENG}Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.89,0:42:04.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,早上好 甘迪小姐\N{\rENG}Morning, Miss Gandy.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.64,0:42:07.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,怎麼？你不喜歡嗎？\N{\rENG}What? You don't like it?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.06,0:42:12.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,胡佛先生 坎薩斯城發生了一起慘案\N{\rENG}Mr. Hoover, there's been a massacre in Kansas City.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.03,0:42:16.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,有我們自己的人？\N{\rENG}One of our own?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.74,0:42:20.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,卡福利探員？\N{\rENG}Special Agent Caffrey?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.33,0:42:22.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,讓他來！\N{\rENG}Let him have it!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.29,0:42:26.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,1930年 共產主義分子危機捲土重來\N{\rENG}By 1930, the communist threat had been beaten back...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.37,0:42:30.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,但同時有大蕭條的影響 產生新的威脅\N{\rENG}...but the Depression had hit and there was a new threat.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.79,0:42:33.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,銀行搶劫 盜車 綁架\N{\rENG}The bank robber, the car thief, and the kidnapper.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.67,0:42:38.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,但不幸的是 對於共產主義 美國並未打壓\N{\rENG}But, unfortunately, as with communism, America didn't react with scorn.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.13,0:42:42.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們激發出了美國黑幫\N{\rENG}They gave the American gangster admiration.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.39,0:42:44.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,這些窮凶極惡的 持械的犯罪分子\N{\rENG}And the defiance by desperate, armed criminals...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.06,0:42:49.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,對社會和文明力量的挑戰 不會再得到縱容\N{\rENG}...of the forces of society and civilization can no longer be ignored.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.35,0:42:53.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,“瘋狂莫蘭”和阿爾·卡彭是我們的頭號公敵 （前者是禁酒令時期芝加哥的黑幫 後者是義大利裔美國黑幫）\N{\rENG}Bugs Moran and Al Capone top the list of public enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.40,0:42:56.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,看看你們周圍 他們無處不在\N{\rENG}Look around you. They could be anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.69,0:43:01.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,我必須重申 調查局會是大家的保護傘\N{\rENG}May I remind you that the Bureau of Investigation seeks to be your protector.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.45,0:43:04.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,它屬於人民 它就和家裡的電話一樣就在你們身邊\N{\rENG}It belongs to you. It is as close to you as your nearest telephone.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.04,0:43:07.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,有了你們的幫助...\N{\rENG}And with your help...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.29,0:43:11.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,華納兄弟影業為大家呈現有聲電影\N{\rENG}Warner Bros. Presents
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.63,0:43:13.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,"The Public Enemy."
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.04,0:43:17.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯·卡格尼飾演頭號公敵\N{\rENG}James Cagney plays public enemy number one.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.01,0:43:20.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 為什麼 你... - 啊！\N{\rENG}- Why, you. - Aah!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.22,0:43:24.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,你又開始說那些願望了\N{\rENG}There you go with that wishing stuff again.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.43,0:43:26.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,或許你可以找到你更喜歡的人\N{\rENG}Maybe you found someone you like better.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.18,0:43:31.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,即將登陸各大院線\N{\rENG}Coming soon to your neighborhood theater.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.81,0:43:33.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,真棒\N{\rENG}Fantastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.73,0:43:39.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,那個夏天 一場犯罪 讓一切都步入了正軌\N{\rENG}That summer, a single crime opened the door to set things right.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.07,0:43:42.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,你知道是哪件事嗎 鐘斯先生？\N{\rENG}Do you know what that was, Mr. Jones?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.99,0:43:44.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,抱歉 是什麼事？\N{\rENG}Sorry, sir, what was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.49,0:43:47.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,目前為止 誰是20世紀最有名的人？\N{\rENG}Who is the most famous man of the 20th Century thus far?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.83,0:43:50.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,喬·麥卡錫？ （約瑟夫·雷蒙德·麥卡錫，美國政治家，反共產主義者）\N{\rENG}Joe McCarthy, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.58,0:43:54.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,麥卡錫就是個機會主義者...\N{\rENG}Mr. McCarthy was an opportunist...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.09,0:43:57.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,並不是個愛國者 鐘斯先生\N{\rENG}...not a patriot, Mr. Jones.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.88,0:44:04.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,目前為止  誰是20世紀最有名的人？\N{\rENG}Who is the most famous man of the 20th Century thus far?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.47,0:44:07.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,最有名？\N{\rENG}The most famous?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.77,0:44:09.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,那是不是您？\N{\rENG}Ls that you, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.40,0:44:20.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,我覺得他的惡名 取決於他是什麼行業的\N{\rENG}Well, I suppose his notoriety depends on the field that he is in.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.90,0:44:24.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,天上飛的那種\N{\rENG}His field was in the clouds.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.24,0:44:27.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,那就是查理斯·林德伯格了 （美國飛行員 首個單人不著陸飛越大西洋的人）\N{\rENG}Well, then Charles Lindbergh, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.51,0:44:41.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,喂？\N{\rENG}Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.72,0:44:44.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,查理斯·林德伯格的小孩 被人從家中綁架了\N{\rENG}Charles Lindbergh's baby has been kidnapped from his home.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.84,0:44:48.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,從特雷敦派警官過去 我會乘頭班火車趕到\N{\rENG}Send officers from Trenton. I'll be on the first train.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.56,0:44:54.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,什麼事？\N{\rENG}What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.77,0:45:00.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,查理斯·林德伯格... 他的孩子被綁架了\N{\rENG}Charles Lindbergh... Lindbergh's baby's been kidnapped.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.61,0:45:03.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,你得找到他\N{\rENG}You've got to find him.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.07,0:45:07.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,你得把孩子安全帶回來\N{\rENG}He has to be brought home alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.20,0:45:10.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的 母親\N{\rENG}Yes, Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.58,0:45:15.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的 母親 我明白\N{\rENG}Yes, Mother, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.21,0:45:22.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,當1932年的那個早晨 我們到達林德伯格家的時候\N{\rENG}When we arrived at Mr. Lindbergh's home that morning in 1932...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.09,0:45:26.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們正開始一項 即將永遠改變調查局的案件\N{\rENG}...we began an investigation that would forever change our Bureau.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.59,0:45:29.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,今天早上我們收到來自賓州鐵路的 威爾·羅傑斯的消息...\N{\rENG}This morning we've heard from the Pennsylvania Railroad, Will Rogers...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.06,0:45:32.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,胡佛總統 羅斯福州長 海關...\N{\rENG}...President Hoover, Governor Roosevelt, Customs...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.14,0:45:34.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,還有美國郵政 和童子軍\N{\rENG}...the U.S. Mail, and the Boy Scouts.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.06,0:45:36.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,你們所有人 趕緊離開那泥地\N{\rENG}All of you. Get off of that dirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.81,0:45:39.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,你們這是踩踏證據 快！走開！\N{\rENG}You're trampling evidence. Immediately! Get off!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.65,0:45:42.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,那裡什麼都沒有 我們檢查過了 沒有可以辨認的腳印\N{\rENG}There's nothing there. We checked. No defined footprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.78,0:45:44.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,似乎罪犯在鞋子上綁了布\N{\rENG}It appears he was wearing fabric on his shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.15,0:45:47.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,那你不覺得印記的大小 也會有點價值嗎？\N{\rENG}You don't think the size could've held some value?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.99,0:45:51.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,他是怎麼爬上去的？ 窗子和牆上是不是也有證據？\N{\rENG}How did he get up there? Are there marks on the window and wall as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.49,0:45:53.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們在100碼之外發現了梯子\N{\rENG}A ladder. We found it 100 yards away.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.62,0:45:55.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們把它放進去了\N{\rENG}We moved it inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.25,0:45:56.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,你動過它了？\N{\rENG}You moved it?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.58,0:45:58.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,是啊 安全保管起見\N{\rENG}Yes, for safekeeping.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.33,0:46:02.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,恭喜你啊 施瓦茲科夫先生 你徹徹底底污染了這個犯罪現場\N{\rENG}Congratulations, Mr. Schwarzkopf. You have contaminated the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.50,0:46:04.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,你現在可以高抬貴腳趕緊走了\N{\rENG}Now, get your boots off this property.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.76,0:46:07.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,你有什麼權利來這裡？ 你叫...\N{\rENG}And what right do you have to be here, Mister, uh...?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.22,0:46:09.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,J·愛德格·胡佛 調查局局長\N{\rENG}J. Edgar Hoover, director of the Bureau of investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.01,0:46:13.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們由胡佛總統指派 來保障這次調查\N{\rENG}We've been sent by President Hoover to ensure the investigation...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.18,0:46:16.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,總統已經授權我們可以 查看所有的檔和證據\N{\rENG}The president has authorized access to all documents and evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.44,0:46:20.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,胡佛先生 你看看沒問題 但新澤西可不是總統的私人領土\N{\rENG}Mr. Hoover, you're free to observe, but New Jersey's not the president's domain.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.44,0:46:24.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,林德伯格先生呢？ 我想要聽聽他的意見\N{\rENG}And where is Mr. Lindbergh? I'd like to hear his opinion on the matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.19,0:46:26.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 林德伯格先生在後面 - 您先請\N{\rENG}- Mr. Lindbergh's around back. - After you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.45,0:46:28.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,他一夜沒睡\N{\rENG}He's been up all night.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.28,0:46:31.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,林德伯格先生親自下來見了我\N{\rENG}Mr. Lindbergh himself came down to meet me.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.49,0:46:36.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,他和我握手 表達了他對我們年輕的調查局的感謝和信任\N{\rENG}He shook my hand and expressed his gratitude and faith in our young Bureau.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.29,0:46:39.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,他從五尺高的地方摔下來\N{\rENG}He fell five feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.46,0:46:40.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,誰？\N{\rENG}Who did?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.84,0:46:45.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,綁架犯 手裡還抱著孩子\N{\rENG}The kidnapper, with the child in his arms.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.47,0:46:48.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,這只是推測\N{\rENG}That's speculation, Mr. Hoover.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.34,0:46:53.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,林德伯格先生 倘若這個梯子在 這個人爬上去的時候已經開裂了\N{\rENG}Mr. Lindbergh, sir, if the ladder had split while the person was on their way up...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.18,0:46:55.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,它肯定已經塌了 你看 這是個失算\N{\rENG}...it would have collapsed. You see, it was a miscalculation.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.14,0:47:00.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,它本來可以承受一個成人的重量爬上去 但無法承受一個成人加一個孩子爬下來\N{\rENG}It was meant to bear the weight of a man, but not the weight of a man and child.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.85,0:47:01.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們有別的看法\N{\rENG}We have other theories.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.90,0:47:04.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,要贖金的字條呢？\N{\rENG}Where's the ransom note?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.98,0:47:06.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,在這\N{\rENG}Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.82,0:47:10.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,你就這樣光著手摸這張紙？\N{\rENG}And you are touching that with your bare hands as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.53,0:47:11.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們檢查過了\N{\rENG}We checked.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.74,0:47:15.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒有你那麼喜歡的指紋在上面\N{\rENG}There are none of those finger imprints that you fancy so valuable.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.29,0:47:17.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,把它遞過來吧 施瓦茲科夫先生\N{\rENG}Please hand it over, Mr. Schwarzkopf.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.25,0:47:19.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,我叫科內爾·施瓦茲科夫\N{\rENG}That's Colonel Schwarzkopf.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.38,0:47:25.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,“準備好五萬美元” ready（準備）拼成了R-E-D-Y\N{\rENG}"Have 50,000 dollars ready," spelled R-E-D-Y.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.38,0:47:29.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,“我們會告訴你地點” 拼成了W-E-R-E；“把錢送到...”\N{\rENG}"We will inform you where," spelled W-E-R-E, "to deliver the money"...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.17,0:47:30.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,money（錢）拼成了M-O-N-Y\N{\rENG}...spelled M-O-N-Y.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.68,0:47:34.85,CHT,,0,0,0,,“警告你不許聲張消息或者通知警方”\N{\rENG}"We warn you for making anything public or for notify the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.01,0:47:39.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,“指示的所有信件都要簽字” 拼成了S-I-N-G，“singnature”\N{\rENG}Indication for all letters are signature," S-I-N-G, "singnature."
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.69,0:47:42.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,紙有三個孔\N{\rENG}Three holes.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.86,0:47:45.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,我想要這封信和那個梯子\N{\rENG}I want this letter and the ladder.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.11,0:47:48.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,你沒有這個管轄權 我們已經給你看了你想看的\N{\rENG}No jurisdiction. I've showed what you asked for.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.44,0:47:50.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 你可以走了 - 林德伯格先生 請...\N{\rENG}- It's time for you to go. - Mr. Lindbergh, please...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.03,0:47:54.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,胡佛先生 謝謝你 你也看得到 一切都安排妥當\N{\rENG}Mr. Hoover, thank you. As you can see, we have everything under control.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.58,0:47:56.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝你們\N{\rENG}Thank you, gentlemen.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.54,0:47:58.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝你抽空 林德伯格先生\N{\rENG}Thank you for your time, Mr. Lindbergh.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.04,0:48:01.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,克萊德\N{\rENG}Clyde.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.84,0:48:12.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,克萊德 我很擔心他的孩子\N{\rENG}Clyde, I'm afraid for his boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.34,0:48:15.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,相比我們 他更信任當地警方\N{\rENG}He trusts the local police more than us.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.85,0:48:17.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,他覺得我們都是傻子\N{\rENG}He thinks we're all fools.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.47,0:48:21.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,他也會聽他們的 他會去跟綁架犯談判\N{\rENG}He'll go around them too. He's going to bargain with the kidnappers.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.56,0:48:26.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,胡佛總統今天早上給我打電話 告訴我孩子被綁架了\N{\rENG}President Hoover called me the morning the child was taken...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.77,0:48:29.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,他讓我做我權力以內的任何事 去解決案件\N{\rENG}...and asked me to do whatever was in my power to solve this crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.11,0:48:33.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,但你們是否知道 調查局的所有權力是什麼？\N{\rENG}But do you know what all the power of the Bureau means...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.24,0:48:38.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒有法律保護 沒有槍支 沒有權利來逮捕？\N{\rENG}...without federal laws, without arms, without the ability to make arrests?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.37,0:48:40.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,這什麼都不是\N{\rENG}It means nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.37,0:48:43.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,主席 我強烈建議通過這項林德伯格法案\N{\rENG}Mr. Chairman, I urge passage of the Lindbergh Law...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.12,0:48:46.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,讓綁架成為一項國家級的罪行\N{\rENG}...making kidnapping a federal offense.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.67,0:48:50.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,應當立即把國家所有的指紋 都送來我辦公室\N{\rENG}To immediately deliver all the fingerprints in this country to my office...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.84,0:48:53.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們就可以建立一個中央檔案\N{\rENG}...so that we may create a central file.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.18,0:48:56.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,把我們的探員武裝起來 讓他們有機會戰鬥...\N{\rENG}To help arm our agents so that they have a fighting chance...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.51,0:49:00.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,和那些最危險的 持衝鋒槍的人作戰\N{\rENG}...against the submachine guns of some of the most dangerous characters...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.52,0:49:02.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,美國歷史上最危險的罪犯之一\N{\rENG}...in the history of American criminality.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.64,0:49:06.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,我要敦促你們 為了小林迪這樣做\N{\rENG}And I urge you to do this in the name of Little Lindy.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.23,0:49:09.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,因為連他都可以被綁架 那誰家的孩子還會是安全的？\N{\rENG}Because if he can be taken, then what child is safe?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.69,0:49:15.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,假如我們無法幫助他安全回家 那我們還有什麼用？\N{\rENG}And if we cannot aid in his safe return, then what use are we?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.01,0:49:40.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,從當地機關送來的指紋...\N{\rENG}Every fingerprint from the local authorities...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.31,0:49:44.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,來自全國各地 開始湧來 最終 我們有了這個中央系統\N{\rENG}...across the country began flowing in. Finally, we had a centralized system.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.69,0:49:46.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,怎麼了 愛德格？\N{\rENG}What is it, Edgar?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.65,0:49:50.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,芝加哥送來的最後一批指紋\N{\rENG}The last of the fingerprints came in from Chicago.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.07,0:49:57.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,你知道我們的新總統 跟我安排了一次見面吧\N{\rENG}You know our new president has scheduled a meeting with me, Miss Gandy?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.57,0:50:02.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,你知不知道有謠言說 要重組調查局？\N{\rENG}Do you know that there are talks of reorganizing the Bureau?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.37,0:50:05.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的我聽到了相似的傳言\N{\rENG}Yes, I've heard similar whispers.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.83,0:50:07.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,嗯\N{\rENG}Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.17,0:50:08.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,是嗎？\N{\rENG}Have you?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.96,0:50:15.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,甘迪 你還記不記得 我們給他的妻子建立的那個文件？\N{\rENG}Miss Gandy, do you remember that file we created on his wife?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.26,0:50:16.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,羅斯福夫人？\N{\rENG}Mrs. Roosevelt?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.01,0:50:18.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rENG}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.76,0:50:20.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,你能給我拷貝一份嗎？\N{\rENG}Will you make a copy for me, please?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.76,0:50:23.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的 當然\N{\rENG}Yes, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.27,0:50:27.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝你 甘迪\N{\rENG}Thank you, Miss Gandy.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.76,0:51:03.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,林德伯格是讓一群罪犯來找他兒子\N{\rENG}Lindbergh hired criminals to find his son.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.22,0:51:06.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,可以離開桌子了 加里森調查員 跟我來\N{\rENG}Off the desk now, Agent Garrison, follow me.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.68,0:51:07.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,是\N{\rENG}Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.89,0:51:10.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,他甚至得到了來自阿爾·卡彭的邀請 來幫他付贖金\N{\rENG}He even got an offer from Al Capone to help pay the ransom money...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.15,0:51:15.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,但是最後 他雇了一個怪人 叫約翰·康登的\N{\rENG}...but, in the end, he employed an eccentric by the name of John Condon...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.23,0:51:19.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,這個人在報紙上登廣告 以此跟綁架犯交流\N{\rENG}...who placed a newspaper ad to act as a go-between with the kidnappers.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.65,0:51:22.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,那康登也是個罪犯嗎？\N{\rENG}Now, was Condon a criminal too?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.24,0:51:25.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,他肯定也不是什麼法律的代言人\N{\rENG}He most certainly wasn't an agent of the law, Mr. Garrison.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.79,0:51:27.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,你為什麼要這樣做？\N{\rENG}Why are you doing this?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.46,0:51:30.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,這樣一個母親就能重新找回她的孩子\N{\rENG}So a mother may have her baby again.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.54,0:51:34.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,你也可以知道 美國人民很感謝你...\N{\rENG}And you may know that the American people are grateful...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.84,0:51:37.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,賜予他們膽量和氣魄\N{\rENG}...for the honor bestowed upon them by your pluck and daring.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.13,0:51:42.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,那我們怎麼知道 綁架者與跟你寫這些信的是同一個人？\N{\rENG}And how do we know the kidnapper is the same that wrote the letters that you have?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.60,0:51:47.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,有標記 跟原來的信一樣 不是嗎？\N{\rENG}The symbol, uh, matches the original letter's symbol, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.69,0:51:53.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,怎麼了 林德伯格先生？\N{\rENG}What is it, Mr. Lindbergh?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.69,0:51:59.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,有一次我很輕率地...\N{\rENG}In a moment of thoughtlessness...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.86,0:52:02.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,我把那些標記給了其他人看\N{\rENG}...l showed the symbol to some other men...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.20,0:52:05.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,我也不確定 他們是否值得信任了\N{\rENG}...and I'm not sure that they were trustworthy.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.37,0:52:08.16,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不確定任何人是否值得信任了\N{\rENG}I'm not sure anyone is trustworthy.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.00,0:52:11.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,我會拿你收到的這些信去鑒定\N{\rENG}I will be having your letters analyzed...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.04,0:52:15.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,來確認他們是來自同一個人之手\N{\rENG}...to make sure that they are from the same author.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.21,0:52:19.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,正當林德伯格先生 把自己的信任交給這些惡棍的時候\N{\rENG}And while Mr. Lindbergh placed his faith in hoodlums...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.71,0:52:23.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們開始發展一件 讓罪犯無法戰勝的事\N{\rENG}...we began cultivating the one thing criminals couldn't fight...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.39,0:52:25.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,用世上任何槍都不行\N{\rENG}...with all the guns in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.22,0:52:29.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,先生們 請離開這個房間 清理桌面 現在開始\N{\rENG}Gentlemen, please leave this room. Clear all these tables. Time to go, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.52,0:52:30.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,那我們去哪裡抽煙？\N{\rENG}Where can we smoke, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.85,0:52:32.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,不關我的事 別在我面前\N{\rENG}Not my concern. Out of my sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.60,0:52:35.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 奧斯本先生 告訴我們你的需要 - 明亮的燈光 一個顯微鏡...\N{\rENG}- Mr. Osborne, tell us what you need. - Uh, bright lights, a microscope...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.90,0:52:38.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,度量工具 放大鏡 還有一個投影儀\N{\rENG}...measuring instruments, magnifying glasses. A, uh, projector.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.57,0:52:41.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,你擁有這間調查局的所有資源 不要害怕\N{\rENG}You have the full resources of the Bureau. Don't be shy.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.70,0:52:43.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,每個地區製造商的紙張樣品\N{\rENG}Paper samples from every regional manufacturer.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.99,0:52:47.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,奧斯本先生 這位是托爾森 協助奧斯本先生 不管他有什麼需要\N{\rENG}Mr. Osborne, this is Mr. Tolson. Supply Mr. Osborne whatever he needs...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.78,0:52:51.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,以百分百斷定 這些信出自同一人之手\N{\rENG}...to conclude without a doubt that these letters came from the same author.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.96,0:52:53.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,嗯？\N{\rENG}Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.88,0:52:57.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,先生們 請離開 謝謝\N{\rENG}Gentlemen, please. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.67,0:53:02.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 我們是不是應該告訴檢察官？ - 好讓他第三次拒絕我們？\N{\rENG}- Should we tell the attorney general? - So he can say no a third time?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.05,0:53:06.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 掛個牌子 像這個一樣 - 你想說什麼，“禁止入內”？\N{\rENG}- Just post a sign, like this one. - What would you like it to say, "keep out"?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.97,0:53:09.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,“調查局技術實驗室”\N{\rENG}"The Bureau of investigations Technical Laboratory."
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.72,0:53:13.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,雕刻好 釘在牆上 如果有人想要撤了它 他還得花點力氣\N{\rENG}Have it carved and nailed to the wall. If he wants it gone, he'll have to tear it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.89,0:53:16.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,是時候我們至少有 犯罪分子沒有的東西了\N{\rENG}It's time we at least have one thing the bad guys don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.06,0:53:18.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,裝飾技巧？\N{\rENG}Decorating skills?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.27,0:53:19.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,是科學 克萊德\N{\rENG}Science, Clyde. Science.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.98,0:53:24.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,墨水不同 但筆跡吻合\N{\rENG}Uh, the ink is different, but the handwriting is a match.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.28,0:53:29.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,不管是誰在和康登先生交涉 就是那個寫第一張字條的人\N{\rENG}Whoever Mr. Condon is corresponding with is the person who wrote the original note.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.24,0:53:31.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,或者康登寫了所有的字條\N{\rENG}Or Condon wrote all the notes himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.37,0:53:34.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,林德伯格正計畫讓康登 來送那些贖金\N{\rENG}Lindbergh is planning on using Condon to deliver the ransom.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.16,0:53:36.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 或許已經送去了 - 聯繫內部稅收部門\N{\rENG}- May have already happened. - Call the internal Revenue Service.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.79,0:53:40.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,讓他們去林德伯格家 我要讓所有的鈔票都做好標記\N{\rENG}Get them to Lindbergh's home. I insist that all those bills be marked.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.80,0:53:41.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,是\N{\rENG}Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.05,0:53:44.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,就這樣了嗎 胡佛先生？ 我兩點半還有課\N{\rENG}Ls that all, Mr. Hoover? I have a 2:30 p.m. class to teach.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.05,0:53:47.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,不 你不用去了 你的薪水將會翻倍\N{\rENG}No, you don't. Consider your pay doubled.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.30,0:53:52.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,你現在為國家做事了 奧斯本先生 祝賀你\N{\rENG}You work for your country now, Mr. Osborne. Congratulations.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.73,0:53:56.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,醫生！\N{\rENG}Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.57,0:54:08.16,CHT,,0,0,0,,拿到錢了嗎？\N{\rENG}Have you gotted the money?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.99,0:54:11.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒見到孩子之前 我不能把錢帶來\N{\rENG}I can't bring the money till I see the baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.42,0:54:19.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,我保證沒有員警\N{\rENG}I promise you there's no police.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.75,0:54:22.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,太危險了\N{\rENG}It's too dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.59,0:54:32.18,CHT,,0,0,0,,停！快停！\N{\rENG}Stop! Stop this now!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.27,0:54:35.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒人會傷害你\N{\rENG}No one's gonna harm you.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.14,0:54:37.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果他們抓住我那就會了\N{\rENG}If they catch me, they will.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.06,0:54:40.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,不 他們只想要這個孩子\N{\rENG}No, they only want the child.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.61,0:54:43.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果我被抓 會被判30年 這會毀了我\N{\rENG}They'll give me 30 years if I'm caught. They could burn me.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.15,0:54:45.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,不 不\N{\rENG}No. No.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.78,0:54:46.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,不是我幹的\N{\rENG}I didn't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.03,0:54:48.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,我只是個送信的\N{\rENG}I'm only the messenger.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.24,0:54:50.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,Eh!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.16,0:54:52.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果孩子已經死了呢？\N{\rENG}What if the baby is dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.24,0:54:55.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,孩子死了的話我是不是就完了？\N{\rENG}Would I burn if the baby is dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.54,0:55:00.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果孩子已經死了 那我們還見面幹嘛？\N{\rENG}Why would we be meeting if the baby was dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.21,0:55:03.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,你拿到錢再登一個廣告\N{\rENG}Place another ad in the paper when you have the money.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.88,0:55:14.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果贖金必須支付 我們需要追蹤這些鈔票\N{\rENG}So if a ransom had to be paid, we needed those bills traced.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.39,0:55:18.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們叫來了國稅局的人 出於他的考慮 我們必須強迫他如此\N{\rENG}We brought in the lRS, and, for his own good, we had to force his hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.73,0:55:21.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,我總覺得黃金證明這種東西 早就已經不流通了\N{\rENG}I thought gold notes were going out of circulation, Mr. lrey.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.73,0:55:23.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,這才是我們的希望\N{\rENG}That's our hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.23,0:55:25.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,這會讓這些鈔票更有辨識度\N{\rENG}It'll make these bills more identifiable.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.28,0:55:27.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不需要這些錢 我只想要我兒子回來\N{\rENG}I have no need for the money. I just want my son.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.40,0:55:32.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,這不僅僅關乎您的兒子 林德伯格先生\N{\rENG}This isn't just about your son, Mr. Lindbergh.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.53,0:55:36.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果這些綁架犯逍遙法外 這個國家就沒有一個孩子是安全的了\N{\rENG}If these kidnappers go free, then no child in this country will be safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.58,0:55:41.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,這就是為什麼我已經組成了一支26人的隊伍 由特別探員西斯科帶領\N{\rENG}That's why I've assembled a 26-man team, headed by Special Agent Sisk here.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.54,0:55:45.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,假如他們發現你有參與此事 我會永遠見不到我兒子了吧\N{\rENG}And if they find out you're involved, I may never see my son again.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.55,0:55:49.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,林德伯格先生 我們不會有任何超前的行為\N{\rENG}Mr. Lindbergh, sir, we will not pursue a single lead...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.63,0:55:51.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,直到您的孩子平安回到母親的懷抱\N{\rENG}...until your child is safe in his mother's arms.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.09,0:55:54.85,CHT,,0,0,0,,我向您保證\N{\rENG}You have my word, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.94,0:56:05.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,小查理斯·A·林德伯格的綁架案 是一場悲劇...\N{\rENG}The kidnapping of Charles A. Lindbergh, Jr., was a tragedy...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.11,0:56:08.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,不僅對於科內爾和林德伯格夫人 還有整個國家\N{\rENG}...not only to Colonel and Mrs. Lindbergh, but to the nation.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.86,0:56:11.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,他從家中被綁架這件事 對整個美國都是挑戰\N{\rENG}His abduction from his Hopewell home was a challenge to America.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.11,0:56:14.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,梯子 綁架案的唯一線索 是自己手工造的\N{\rENG}This ladder, the only clue to the kidnapping, was homemade.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.03,0:56:17.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,讓林德伯格案件的一切進展 作為新的力量...\N{\rENG}Let the developments in the Lindbergh case start a new drive...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.12,0:56:21.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,消滅一切骯髒 不僅僅是這次放肆的綁架案\N{\rENG}...to wipe out the stain, not only of that wanton kidnapping...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.16,0:56:24.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,包括所有的綁架和犯罪\N{\rENG}...but of all kidnapping and crimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.80,0:56:28.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,嘿 醫生！\N{\rENG}Hey, doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.21,0:56:32.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,他告訴你六小時之內不要打開\N{\rENG}Give your word not to open for six hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.47,0:56:35.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝\N{\rENG}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.77,0:56:45.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,我跟他談下來2萬\N{\rENG}I talked him out of 20,000 dollars.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.11,0:56:49.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,我選擇讓他高興點 而不是省錢 我不想讓他生氣\N{\rENG}I'd prefer him happy than save the money. I don't want to upset him.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.57,0:56:51.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,孩子在哪裡？\N{\rENG}Where is the baby?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.99,0:56:54.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,我保證六小時之內不打開這個\N{\rENG}I promised not to open this for six hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.74,0:56:57.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,你說你的 我沒有說\N{\rENG}You gave your word, I did not.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.83,0:57:03.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,“孩子在奈麗號船上 是一艘小船 28尺長”\N{\rENG}"The boy is on boat Nelly. It is a small boat, 28 feet long.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.46,0:57:06.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,“有兩個人在船上 他們是無辜的”\N{\rENG}Two persons are on the boat. They are innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.67,0:57:11.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,“船在荷森內克海灘和 伊莉莎白島旁邊的蓋荷鎮之間”\N{\rENG}You'll find the boat between Horseneck's Beach and Gay Head near Elizabeth island."
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.84,0:57:13.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,是在楠塔基特 是吧？\N{\rENG}That's Nantucket, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.85,0:57:19.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,船裡面有什麼？\N{\rENG}What was in the boat?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.22,0:57:20.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,根本就沒有船\N{\rENG}There was no boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.77,0:57:23.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,林德伯格沒有信任我們 他要按自己的方式來\N{\rENG}Lindbergh didn't trust us. He wanted to do things his way.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.60,0:57:27.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,誰能怪他呢 當時沒有人尊重我們調查局\N{\rENG}And who can blame him? No one respected us at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.36,0:57:29.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,胡佛先生  我們一直在找你\N{\rENG}Mr. Hoover, we've been calling.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.23,0:57:30.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,愛德格\N{\rENG}Edgar.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.45,0:57:35.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,該走了 加里森調查員 現在\N{\rENG}Time to go, Agent Garrison. Right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.53,0:57:39.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,總檢察長已經授權了 你的竊聽器\N{\rENG}The Attorney General has authorized your wiretaps.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.87,0:57:41.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,很好 甘迪\N{\rENG}Very good, Miss Gandy.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.54,0:57:46.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,愛德格 你確定要這麼做嗎？ 你要是這麼做了 事情就這麼定了\N{\rENG}Edgar, are you sure about this? Once you do this, Edgar, it's done.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.88,0:57:50.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,我證明我是對的以後 我們可以再次避免國家陷入革命\N{\rENG}When I prove myself correct, we will have saved this country another revolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.84,0:57:52.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,歷史會記住我們的 克萊德\N{\rENG}History will remember that, Clyde.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.67,0:57:53.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,但假如你錯了...\N{\rENG}But if you are wrong...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.05,0:57:57.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,歷史也會記住這是一次 因為小的恩怨產生的非法行為\N{\rENG}...history will remember it as an illegal move over a petty grudge.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.55,0:58:00.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,你覺得我們的名聲是小事嗎 托爾森？\N{\rENG}Do you consider our reputation petty, Mr. Tolson?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.68,0:58:03.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 不 我... - 那就去訂這些電線\N{\rENG}- No, I... - Then order the wires.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.81,0:58:08.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 我們能不能晚飯時候討論一下？ - 在你訂了電線以後\N{\rENG}- Can we discuss this over dinner? - After you've ordered the wires.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.44,0:58:11.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,是\N{\rENG}Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.58,0:58:26.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,局長已經在路上了\N{\rENG}The director's on his way.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.81,0:58:51.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,您請\N{\rENG}- Ahem. - After you.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.80,0:59:15.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,等等\N{\rENG}Wait, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.80,0:59:24.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 去哈威餐館？ - 不 去白宮\N{\rENG}- Harvey's Restaurant, sir? - No, to the White House.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.44,0:59:37.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們正在經歷大蕭條\N{\rENG}We were in the midst of a Great Depression...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.69,0:59:40.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,被史上最嚴重的戰爭 壓得喘不過氣\N{\rENG}...and breaths away from history's worst war.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.66,0:59:44.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們需要更多的權力來保護 但 每次有新的總統上任\N{\rENG}We needed more power to protect, but, as with every new president...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.66,0:59:49.16,CHT,,0,0,0,,調查局的未來 以及我個人的職位 都要被打上問號\N{\rENG}...this Bureau's future and my very job was being drawn into question.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.33,0:59:52.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 總統先生可以見你了 - 好的\N{\rENG}- The president is ready to see you now. - Alrighty.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.18,1:00:03.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,進來吧 請坐 胡佛先生\N{\rENG}Come in. Have a seat, Mr. Hoover.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.51,1:00:09.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,每次都是一樣的戲碼 他們讓我一直等\N{\rENG}It's the same dance each time. They make me wait.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.81,1:00:14.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們想像我會緊張流汗 然後他們就擺明自己才是老大 我是單打獨鬥\N{\rENG}They imagine I'm sweating, that they're gonna show me who's boss, I play along.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.02,1:00:16.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝\N{\rENG}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.82,1:00:18.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,你給他看了那些記錄副本嗎？\N{\rENG}And then did you show him the transcript?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.86,1:00:21.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,不 他不想看 這很特殊\N{\rENG}No. He didn't want to read it. That was unique.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.99,1:00:24.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,他想讓我口頭告訴他\N{\rENG}He wanted me to tell him about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.37,1:00:26.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,那麼你是怎麼說的？\N{\rENG}What, how you came across it?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.24,1:00:30.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,我就直接跟他說 我們不曾想到會抓到羅斯福夫人...\N{\rENG}No, I explained to him up front we never expected to find Mrs. Roosevelt...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.54,1:00:32.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,會在一個知名的共產主義分子的臥室裡\N{\rENG}...in the bedroom of a known communist agitator...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.12,1:00:36.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,聽起來像是很親密\N{\rENG}...much less having what sounded like an intimate moment.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.71,1:00:39.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,我需要他指示該如何繼續調查\N{\rENG}That I needed his advice on how to proceed.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.88,1:00:42.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,我想讓他知道 他還是有盟友的\N{\rENG}I wanted to let him know he had an ally.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.51,1:00:44.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,在他要求你自己辭職之前\N{\rENG}Before he had a chance to ask you to resign.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.68,1:00:45.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,就是這樣\N{\rENG}Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.10,1:00:48.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,我說完以後 他就把文件推到一邊\N{\rENG}When I was finished, he simply pushed the file aside...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.06,1:00:53.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,就像他根本不關心\N{\rENG}...as if he was unconcerned with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.48,1:00:57.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,克萊德 美國的總統害怕了\N{\rENG}Clyde, the President of the United States is afraid.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.48,1:01:00.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,他害怕你？\N{\rENG}What, he's afraid of you?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.23,1:01:04.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,害怕潛在的來自國外的侵略\N{\rENG}Of a potential invasion from abroad.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.99,1:01:07.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,來兩杯你們最好的香檳\N{\rENG}We'll have two glasses of your finest champagne.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.74,1:01:09.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,馬上 胡佛先生\N{\rENG}Of course, Mr. Hoover.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.08,1:01:12.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,你開始喝酒了？\N{\rENG}- Ahem. - You're drinking now?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.75,1:01:14.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,只是慶祝 克萊德\N{\rENG}We're celebrating, Clyde, we're celebrating.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.54,1:01:18.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,你知道 我覺得我可以 任何事都信任你 是嗎？\N{\rENG}You know I feel I could trust you with anything, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.29,1:01:19.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,我很樂意這麼認為\N{\rENG}Well, I'd like to think so.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.30,1:01:24.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,總統簽署了一份密令\N{\rENG}The president signed a secret order...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.13,1:01:27.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,給予我更多的監視權...\N{\rENG}...granting me increased power of surveillance...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:27.60,1:01:32.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,秘密監視共產主義分子和激進者的權利 不需要任何授權\N{\rENG}...secret surveillance of communists and radicals, without warrant.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.06,1:01:34.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,這合法？\N{\rENG}Ls that legal?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.27,1:01:36.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,有時候 你需要過界一些...\N{\rENG}Sometimes you need to bend the rules a little...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.85,1:01:39.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,來保護國家的安全 是吧？\N{\rENG}...in order to keep your country safe, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.44,1:01:43.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,為了保證我沒有聽錯 我還和國務卿赫爾證實了\N{\rENG}And to make sure I hadn't heard it wrong, I clarified this with Secretary of State Hull.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.07,1:01:48.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,他說 我引用一下 “去吧 調查那些口交的傢伙們”\N{\rENG}And he said, and I quote, "You go ahead and investigate those cocksuckers."
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.66,1:01:52.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 好粗俗啊 - 同意\N{\rENG}- Vulgar. - Hmm, agreed.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.12,1:01:56.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,克萊德\N{\rENG}Clyde...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.46,1:01:59.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,我一直想要問你一件事\N{\rENG}...I've been meaning to ask you something.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.17,1:02:01.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,問吧\N{\rENG}Feel free.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.30,1:02:05.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,我需要一個人 理解現在什麼是危在旦夕\N{\rENG}I need someone who understands what's at stake here...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.97,1:02:07.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,你明白嗎？\N{\rENG}...you understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.43,1:02:09.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,一個我可以信任的人\N{\rENG}Someone who I can trust...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.14,1:02:12.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,調查局的副局長\N{\rENG}...an associate director of the Bureau.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.14,1:02:16.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,我知道 你在你現在的位置 只做了差不多12個月\N{\rENG}I know you've only been in your current position for, what, 12 months now.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.77,1:02:18.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,將近18個月了\N{\rENG}Oh, almost 18 now, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.81,1:02:21.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,你沒理解我說的 克萊德\N{\rENG}You're missing my point, Clyde.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.40,1:02:23.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,我需要你做我的二把手\N{\rENG}I want you to be my number-two man.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.20,1:02:29.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,我並不適應那些聚光燈 愛德格\N{\rENG}I'm not much for the spotlight, Edgar.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.49,1:02:34.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,我需要你 克萊德\N{\rENG}I need you, Clyde.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.79,1:02:36.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,你明白嗎？ 我需要你\N{\rENG}Do you understand? I need you.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:39.67,1:02:41.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,只有一個條件\N{\rENG}On one condition.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.25,1:02:45.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,不管這一天是好是壞 不管我們是否同意過...\N{\rENG}Good day or bad, whether we agree or disagree...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.42,1:02:49.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們永遠都要一起吃午飯和晚餐\N{\rENG}...we never miss a lunch or a dinner together.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.18,1:02:52.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,我也不會同意其他的條件\N{\rENG}Well, I would have it no other way.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.19,1:03:04.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,嘿 停車\N{\rENG}Hey, pull over.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.65,1:03:07.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 離玫瑰山只有半英里了 - 等不了了\N{\rENG}- Only a half a mile to Mount Rose. - Can't wait.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.06,1:03:39.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,歐威爾！\N{\rENG}Orville!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.95,1:03:57.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,最終 孩子的屍體被發現...\N{\rENG}In the end, the child's body was found just within sight...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.58,1:03:59.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,就在林德伯格家視野範圍內\N{\rENG}...of Mr. Lindbergh's home.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.08,1:04:02.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,屍體已經變黑\N{\rENG}The body was blackened...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.08,1:04:06.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,左腿膝蓋以下都不見了\N{\rENG}...the left leg missing from the knee down.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.67,1:04:09.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,頭骨上有明顯的骨折\N{\rENG}There was a visible fracture on the skull.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.09,1:04:13.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,他頭上受到了強大的外力擊打 我幾個月前就告訴他了\N{\rENG}He'd suffered a violent blow to the head. I told them months ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:13.43,1:04:17.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,他在爬下去的時候肯定摔了 手裡抱著孩子\N{\rENG}He must've fallen on the way down, with the baby in his arms.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.77,1:04:21.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們都有罪 愛德格\N{\rENG}We are the sinners, Edgar.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.19,1:04:29.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,是我們如此縱容無法無天的行為 讓它們變成窮凶極惡的犯罪\N{\rENG}We tolerated lawlessness in the land until it grew to diabolical proportions.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.78,1:04:33.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們的手上沾滿了孩子的鮮血 愛德格\N{\rENG}The baby's blood is on all our hands, Edgar.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.45,1:04:37.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,你的手上\N{\rENG}On your hands, Edgar.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.79,1:04:45.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,是啊 母親\N{\rENG}Yes, Mother.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.51,1:05:00.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,綁架案六周以後\N{\rENG}Six weeks after the kidnapping...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.52,1:05:02.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,國會通過了林德伯格法案\N{\rENG}...Congress passed the Lindbergh Law...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.52,1:05:05.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,把綁架定為國家級犯罪\N{\rENG}...making kidnapping a federal offense.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.44,1:05:09.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,有了拘捕的權利 以及攜帶槍支的權利\N{\rENG}The right to make arrests followed and the right to bear arms.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.48,1:05:13.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,所以我繼續聚集著 全國最好的科學頭腦\N{\rENG}So I continued collecting the finest scientific minds in the country.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.78,1:05:20.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,他說他是世界上最好的 木材鑒定專家\N{\rENG}He claims to be the world expert on wood analysis.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.54,1:05:24.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,假如你是世界上唯一有某種興趣的人 成為專家很容易\N{\rENG}It's easy to be the expert if you're the only person in the world with any interest.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.58,1:05:26.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,他聲稱從木頭的斷面 他可以鑒定出...\N{\rENG}He does claim he can tell as much from a cut of wood...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:27.08,1:05:29.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 和醫生屍檢獲得的資訊一樣多 - 這樣\N{\rENG}...as a doctor can from an autopsy. - Ah.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.42,1:05:31.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,他有 呃 社交困難\N{\rENG}He has, um, social difficulties.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.01,1:05:34.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,他精神有問題 是吧？\N{\rENG}He is mentally ill, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.34,1:05:37.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,只不過跟你一樣瘋狂罷了\N{\rENG}He's only as mad as you are. Sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.51,1:05:41.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,這本應該只是暫時的 胡佛先生\N{\rENG}This was supposed to be temporary, Mr. Hoover.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.43,1:05:43.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,假如你想要繼續你這福爾摩斯的遊戲...\N{\rENG}If you want your Sherlock Holmes playing time...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.77,1:05:46.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,那你覺得我們還能去哪？\N{\rENG}Where do you suggest we go, sir, where?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.52,1:05:48.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,我建議你去國會解決這個問題\N{\rENG}I suggest you take your case to Congress.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.61,1:05:49.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,很好 那就照你說的\N{\rENG}Fine, sir. Have it your way.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.07,1:05:54.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們就告訴人們 只是因為無法負擔實驗室 我們就不能解決這些案件\N{\rENG}I'll tell people we could not solve the case because we could not afford laboratories...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.15,1:05:58.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,而總檢察長不願意我們佔用他的休息室\N{\rENG}...and the Attorney General wouldn't allow us to use his lounge.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.24,1:06:01.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,行吧 把你的這些科學實驗搬出去\N{\rENG}Fine. Now get your science fair project out of here.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.87,1:06:03.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,是 馬上\N{\rENG}Yes, sir. Right away, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.21,1:06:07.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,繼續工作\N{\rENG}Gentlemen, keep working.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.46,1:06:10.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,托爾森 幫我接到總統的電話\N{\rENG}Mr. Tolson, let's get the president on the phone.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.88,1:06:17.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,惡性犯罪的日益嚴重 像一群狼一樣從一個州遊蕩到另一個州\N{\rENG}The depravations of vicious outlaws, roving from state to state like packs of wolves...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.93,1:06:20.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,成為真正武裝侵蝕美國的力量\N{\rENG}...amounts to an actual armed invasion of America.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.76,1:06:24.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們必須智取這些犯罪分子 不論是國外還是國內的\N{\rENG}We must outsmart and outwit the criminal, foreign and domestic.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.68,1:06:28.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們有化學藥品來製造炸彈 我們就也需要化學藥品來追蹤他們\N{\rENG}They have chemists building bombs. We need chemists tracing their efforts.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.81,1:06:31.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們必須有世界上最先進的力量\N{\rENG}We must have the most advanced force in the world...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.73,1:06:34.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,假如我們想要成為世界上最安全的國家\N{\rENG}...if we are to have the safest nation on earth.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.32,1:06:37.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,先生們 請不要 哪怕就一刻 失去我們的視野和目標\N{\rENG}And, please, gentlemen, let us not for a moment lose sight of our goals:
Dialogue: 0,1:06:38.07,1:06:39.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,保護忠誠的國民\N{\rENG}To protect the honest citizen...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.70,1:06:43.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,告訴犯罪分子 不管他有什麼托詞\N{\rENG}...to teach the criminal that regardless of his subterfuges...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.74,1:06:46.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,不管他如何扭曲  如何在泥濘中蠕動\N{\rENG}...his twisting, his squirming and slimy wriggling...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.50,1:06:49.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒人可以自外於法律...he cannot escape the one inexorable rule of law enforcement...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.96,1:06:51.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,你也一樣\N{\rENG}...that you can't get away with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:52.09,1:06:53.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝\N{\rENG}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.92,1:06:54.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝 胡佛先生\N{\rENG}Thank you, Mr. Hoover.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.09,1:07:01.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,但是你的機構已經是華盛頓 財政支持最多的機構之一了 是嗎？\N{\rENG}But your agency is already one of the most well-funded in Washington, is it not?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:01.18,1:07:02.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的 的確...\N{\rENG}Yes, that is true, sir...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.85,1:07:06.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,但是我們去年的劫車 劫銀行的案件 恢復到了650萬美元的高度\N{\rENG}...but our car and bank robbery recoveries totaled 6.5 million last year...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.93,1:07:09.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們的預算只有200萬\N{\rENG}...and our budget is only, well, two million.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.56,1:07:13.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,不像華盛頓的其他部門 我們看上去還掙了點嘛\N{\rENG}Unlike other departments in Washington, we actually run a profit.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.28,1:07:17.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們不能用數字來 衡量我們的成功...\N{\rENG}We cannot quantify the value of our successes...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.95,1:07:22.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,包括“帥哥佛洛德”（銀行搶劫者） “娃娃臉尼爾森”（銀行搶劫者）“機關槍凱利”（黑幫）這些惡棍\N{\rENG}...with the hoodlums Pretty Boy Floyd, Baby Face Nelson, Machine Gun Kelly...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.20,1:07:24.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,還有其他很多的惡人\N{\rENG}...and other hoodlums of that nature.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.49,1:07:30.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,胡佛先生 你把調查局的經費 花在了廣告方面 這是真的嗎？\N{\rENG}Mr. Hoover, is it true that you spend the Bureau's money on advertising?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.92,1:07:36.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們不允許任何形式的廣告\N{\rENG}We are not permitted to engage in advertising of any kind, sir. No.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.46,1:07:40.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,但你參與了 比如說 廣播節目的製作 還有漫畫書\N{\rENG}But you take part, for instance, in the making of radio shows and comic books.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.14,1:07:43.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,我聽過幾次政府官員的電臺節目\N{\rENG}I've listened to several of these G-Men programs.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:43.80,1:07:48.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,你的照片似乎經常跟他們出現在一起\N{\rENG}Your picture seems to be shown in conjunction with them quite frequently.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.31,1:07:53.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們強調過  拒絕給他們任何支持...\N{\rENG}We declined emphatically to lend any form of endorsement...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.36,1:07:58.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,那些和他們的產品無關的東西 不提供建議 技術 或是任何東西\N{\rENG}...had nothing to do with their production, furnished no advice, technical or otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.24,1:08:01.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,這條廣告說 廣播是...\N{\rENG}Well, the very advertisement says that broadcasts were...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.61,1:08:05.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,“最真實的反映官方記錄中...”\N{\rENG}..."true reflections, as contained in the official records...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.99,1:08:09.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,“根據聯邦調查局的真實案件改編”\N{\rENG}...based on actual cases from the files of the Federal Bureau of investigation...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.91,1:08:11.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,“週六晚上8點檔”\N{\rENG}...Saturday night at 8:00."
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.13,1:08:15.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,胡佛先生 你到底有何資質...\N{\rENG}Mr. Hoover, what are your exact qualifications...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.84,1:08:18.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,處於你現在所在調查局的領導地位？\N{\rENG}...for your position of leadership in this Bureau?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:18.51,1:08:19.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,我的資質？\N{\rENG}My qualifications, sir?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.92,1:08:23.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,在司法部工作了19年 19年\N{\rENG}Nineteen years with the Department of Justice. Nineteen.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:23.97,1:08:25.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,其中12年是調查局局長\N{\rENG}Twelve as director.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.68,1:08:29.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,那段時間 你有沒有親自逮捕犯罪分子？\N{\rENG}In all that time, you ever make an arrest yourself?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:31.02,1:08:35.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,我做了調查 我同時主管好幾件案子\N{\rENG}I have made investigations. I administer several cases at once.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.61,1:08:38.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,這沒有回答我的問題\N{\rENG}Well, that's not what I asked.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.19,1:08:42.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,漫畫書裡有你拿著機關槍 逮捕犯罪分子的情景 這只是編造？\N{\rENG}The comic books show you with a machine gun, making arrests. Ls that just fiction?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.83,1:08:52.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,我負責了幾千次的逮捕\N{\rENG}I am responsible for thousands of arrests, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.58,1:08:56.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,所以你承認那些都是編的\N{\rENG}So you admit it is pure fiction.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.46,1:09:02.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,實際上 不是你把約翰·迪林傑 打倒並抓獲的\N{\rENG}In fact, it wasn't you who hunted down and captured John Dillinger at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:02.51,1:09:05.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,是博維斯探員 是嗎？\N{\rENG}It was Agent Purvis. Ls that correct?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.39,1:09:10.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,我負責了所有的這些調查...\N{\rENG}I was in charge of all of those investigations...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.85,1:09:14.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,但的確 我個人並未做出任何拘捕\N{\rENG}...but, no, sir, I have not personally made an arrest.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.24,1:09:23.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,還有別的問題嗎？\N{\rENG}Any other questions, gentlemen?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.24,1:09:26.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們投票決定吧\N{\rENG}Let's bring it to a vote.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.87,1:09:31.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,把這些拿走\N{\rENG}Put those away.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:36.42,1:09:37.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,事情不太順利啊\N{\rENG}Well, that didn't go well.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.00,1:09:40.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們拚命工作 結果落得被政治攻擊？\N{\rENG}We spend our lives working and we get a political attack?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.92,1:09:44.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,他想要怎樣 案件沒法解決？ 他幹嘛跟我作對？\N{\rENG}What does he expect, crimes to go unsolved? Why is he fighting me?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.59,1:09:46.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,你去開始調查麥克凱勒參議員\N{\rENG}I want you to start a file on Senator McKellar.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:46.84,1:09:48.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,安排四個探員同時調查\N{\rENG}I want four agents on him at all times.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.80,1:09:51.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,我要知道他丟的垃圾裡都有什麼 我要他每天吃晚飯的照片\N{\rENG}I want to know what's in his trash, photograph him at dinner.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:51.93,1:09:55.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,不要上這輛車 你可以走回去\N{\rENG}Don't get in the car. You can walk back.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:55.77,1:09:58.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,愛德格 我們要吃午飯的 我們不論如何都是一起吃午飯的 記得嗎？\N{\rENG}We have lunch. We don't miss lunch, no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.44,1:10:00.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,在裡面的時候  你就那樣離開丟下我一人\N{\rENG}You pulled away from me in there.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.44,1:10:03.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,你給自己作偽證了 愛德格 還是個很容易被識破的謊言\N{\rENG}You perjured yourself, Edgar, and the lie was an easily provable one.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:03.94,1:10:05.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果你還要繼續這些 我都不敢說事情會變得多糟糕\N{\rENG}There's no telling how much worse it could've been.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.11,1:10:09.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,把博維斯探員找出來 馬上把他降職 或者最好是炒了\N{\rENG}Find Agent Purvis. He is to be demoted immediately or, better yet, fired.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.16,1:10:12.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,把抓到約翰·迪林傑的人炒了 這會是重大人力損失\N{\rENG}Firing the man who killed John Dillinger would be a PR disaster.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.00,1:10:15.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,那他就餘生都在辦公桌前度過吧\N{\rENG}Then he is to spend the rest of his career behind a desk.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.41,1:10:19.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果他想保住飯碗 他最好離重要文件遠點 開車\N{\rENG}And if he'd like to keep that job, he'd best stay out of the papers. Go.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.22,1:10:32.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不知道我還能信任誰\N{\rENG}I don't know who I can trust anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.89,1:10:34.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,只有您了\N{\rENG}Only you.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:37.48,1:10:38.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,只有您了 母親\N{\rENG}Only you, Mother.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:39.65,1:10:43.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,你是我唯一擁有的 保佑我安全的人 你知道嗎？\N{\rENG}You're all I have to keep me safe, you understand that?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.19,1:10:46.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,求你了 媽媽 讓我帶你去看醫生\N{\rENG}Please, Mother, let me take you to a doctor.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:46.57,1:10:49.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,簡單地檢查一下沒什麼不好的\N{\rENG}A simple examination isn't unholy, is it?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:51.49,1:10:52.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,媽\N{\rENG}Mother.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:54.83,1:10:55.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,媽 拜託了\N{\rENG}Mother, please.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.83,1:11:01.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,信念 愛德格\N{\rENG}Faith, Edgar.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:01.84,1:11:03.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,信念\N{\rENG}Faith.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.84,1:11:07.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,不要像一朵小花一樣枯萎\N{\rENG}Don't wilt like a little flower.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.34,1:11:09.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,要堅強\N{\rENG}Be strong.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:10.76,1:11:12.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的 母親\N{\rENG}Yes, Mother.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.64,1:11:19.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,我會的\N{\rENG}I will.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.11,1:11:28.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,假如國會更喜歡力量 而不是頭腦和智慧\N{\rENG}if what Congress valued more than wits and brains was muscle...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.32,1:11:31.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果他們更需要的是 一個武裝起來的美國英雄\N{\rENG}...if what they hungered for was an armed American hero...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:31.57,1:11:35.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,那我會冒著生命危險 做到兩者兼備\N{\rENG}...then I was willing to risk my very life and give them both.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:35.54,1:11:36.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,行動\N{\rENG}Move.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.87,1:11:38.16,CHT,,0,0,0,,走\N{\rENG}Go.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:38.33,1:11:39.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,站住！政府探員！\N{\rENG}Hold it, government agents!
Dialogue: 0,1:11:54.51,1:11:56.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,這次逮捕應該是我來！\N{\rENG}The arrest is mine to make!
Dialogue: 0,1:11:57.39,1:11:58.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,閃開\N{\rENG}Move.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:58.56,1:12:01.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,卡佩斯先生 你被逮捕了\N{\rENG}Mr. Karpis, you are under arrest.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.23,1:12:06.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,胡佛親自出馬啊 我要出名了\N{\rENG}Mr. Hoover himself. I'm gonna be famous.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.90,1:12:08.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,把他銬起來\N{\rENG}Put the handcuffs on him.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:13.66,1:12:15.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,不許動 麥漢先生\N{\rENG}Don't move, Mr. Mahan.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.74,1:12:18.16,CHT,,0,0,0,,放倒它\N{\rENG}Blow it down.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.87,1:12:22.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,行動\N{\rENG}Move.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:34.72,1:12:37.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,本內特先生 你被逮捕了\N{\rENG}Mr. Brunette, you are under arrest.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:37.26,1:12:41.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,埃爾文·卡佩斯說他不能被活捉 但我們一槍都沒開就抓住了他\N{\rENG}Alvin Karpis said he couldn't be taken alive, but we took him without firing a shot.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.73,1:12:45.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,這麼跟你說吧 他抖得跟篩子似的 聲音 手 還有膝蓋\N{\rENG}And let me tell you, he shook all over. His voice, his hands, and his knees.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:45.73,1:12:48.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,你還在托雷多逮捕了哈利·坎貝爾 在曼哈頓逮捕了本內特？\N{\rENG}You arrested Harry Campbell in Toledo and Brunette in Manhattan?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.94,1:12:50.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,還有在加州逮捕了威廉·麥漢\N{\rENG}And William Mahan in California.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.65,1:12:53.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,不過我要再次申明 這絕對地...\N{\rENG}But let me clarify without a shadow of a doubt...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:53.32,1:12:55.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,是團隊合作的結果 而不是我個人的成就\N{\rENG}...this was a "we" job, not an "I" job.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:02.71,1:13:05.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,愛德格 看看這個 我們做了這個麥片盒子\N{\rENG}Edgar, look at this. We made the Post Toasties box.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:06.46,1:13:09.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,“梅爾文·博維斯 抓住迪林傑的調查局探員”\N{\rENG}"Melvin Purvis, the FBl agent that caught Dillinger."
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.51,1:13:12.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,聯繫麥片製造商 讓他們知道...\N{\rENG}Write the cereal-maker. Let them know...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.22,1:13:15.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,噢 政府官員的電臺節目\N{\rENG}Oh. "Junior G-Man." Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:15.80,1:13:20.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,告訴他們必須把以後所有的盒子印成 “前調查局探員”\N{\rENG}Tell them they ought to print any further boxes to read "former agent of the FBl."
Dialogue: 0,1:13:21.64,1:13:23.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,坐下 克萊德 我給你念段東西\N{\rENG}Sit down, Clyde. I'm gonna read something.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:27.98,1:13:29.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,“還有8天”\N{\rENG}"Only eight more days.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:29.94,1:13:32.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,“雖然可笑 但最親愛的人的臉 就要消失了”\N{\rENG}Funny how even the dearest face will fade away in time.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:33.15,1:13:34.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,“最清楚地記住了你的眼睛...”\N{\rENG}Most clearly, I remember your eyes...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:35.03,1:13:39.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,“眼神裡有挑逗的笑意 還有那最柔軟的一點...”\N{\rENG}...with a sort of teasing smile in them, and the feeling of that soft spot...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.41,1:13:43.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,“就在你嘴唇的東北角 正對我的雙唇”\N{\rENG}...just northeast of the corner of your mouth against my lips."
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.16,1:13:44.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是什麼？\N{\rENG}What is it?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:44.75,1:13:46.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,是一封來自羅蕾娜·西科克的信\N{\rENG}It's a letter from Lorena Hickok...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:46.54,1:13:50.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,就是那個有口臭的白宮報導員 寫給羅斯福太太的\N{\rENG}...the White House reporter with the bad breath, to Mrs. Roosevelt.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:51.30,1:13:54.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,不會吧 那你要拿這個怎麼辦？\N{\rENG}No. What are you gonna do with it?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:54.34,1:13:56.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,不怎麼樣 我指控過她和男人有外遇...\N{\rENG}Nothing. I accused her of having an affair with a man...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.09,1:14:00.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在這位馬臉老阿姨 要和口臭小姐有一腿了！\N{\rENG}...and Old Horse Face is having an affair with Mrs. Bat Breath!
Dialogue: 0,1:14:01.35,1:14:03.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,一個女人！你相信嗎？\N{\rENG}- A woman! Can you believe it? - Mm.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.19,1:14:11.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,噢 打擾了 胡佛先生 他們要你去實驗室一趟\N{\rENG}Oh, excuse me, Mr. Hoover. They'd like to see you in the laboratory.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:11.53,1:14:14.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,好的 甘迪 告訴他們 我馬上就下去 謝謝\N{\rENG}Yes, Miss Gandy. You tell them I'll be there in one minute. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.03,1:14:16.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們等會兒再處理這個\N{\rENG}We'll get to this later.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:16.82,1:14:21.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,說到馬 克萊德 我這個週末會去德爾瑪律（加州）一趟\N{\rENG}Speaking of horses, Clyde, I'm going to Del Mar this weekend.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.33,1:14:24.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,我在考慮度一個簡短的假期\N{\rENG}I was thinking of taking a quick vacation...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:24.50,1:14:27.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,我想你會不會樂意跟我一起去\N{\rENG}...and, well, I thought you'd like to join me.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:27.83,1:14:30.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,我還從沒看過賽馬比賽呢 愛德格\N{\rENG}Well, I've never been to the horse races, Edgar.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:30.21,1:14:31.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,很有意思的\N{\rENG}Well, it's wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.46,1:14:36.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,就對你說啊 如果我賭輸了 他們會幫我付這錢\N{\rENG}And between me and you, when I lose, the track, they actually cover the losses.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.88,1:14:40.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 那如果你贏了呢？ - 那還是他們付錢\N{\rENG}- So, what happens if you win? - They still pay.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:40.72,1:14:41.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,那這有什麼刺激的？\N{\rENG}Then where's the thrill?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:41.97,1:14:45.85,CHT,,0,0,0,,陽光灑在看臺上 酒店房間 好的服務...\N{\rENG}In the sun that falls on the stands, the hotel rooms, the service...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:46.02,1:14:49.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,還有餐廳 但最重要的是 克萊德 是和你同去的人\N{\rENG}...the restaurants, but, most of all, Clyde, it's the company.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.06,1:14:53.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 和我一起去吧 - 我很樂意\N{\rENG}- Come with me. - I'd love to.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:53.32,1:14:56.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,太好了 我會讓甘迪 安排好一切\N{\rENG}Fantastic. I'll have Miss Gandy make all the arrangements.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:56.65,1:14:59.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,其實我不能現在去 但或許過兩個月 等我存點錢\N{\rENG}Well, I can't go now. But maybe in a couple months after I've saved up.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:00.07,1:15:03.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 費用都我包了 克萊德 - 愛德格 這可不行\N{\rENG}- It's completely covered, Clyde. - Edgar, I can't let you do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:03.58,1:15:07.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,聽著 你為我做了這麼多事 也為了調查局 就當是我謝謝你\N{\rENG}Listen, you've done so much for me, for this Bureau. Consider it a thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:08.00,1:15:10.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不知道我會不會覺得舒服啊\N{\rENG}I don't know that I'd feel comfortable.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:11.34,1:15:14.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,這樣告訴你吧 我會定一個套間 有相鄰的臥室\N{\rENG}I'll get a suite with adjoining rooms...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:14.38,1:15:17.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,而不是兩個人分開訂房間 這樣就節省多了\N{\rENG}...rather than having us stay separate. That'll be savings enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:18.34,1:15:19.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,成交\N{\rENG}Deal.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:20.18,1:15:21.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,有什麼新發現嗎 科勒先生？\N{\rENG}What do you have for me, Mr. Koehler?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.10,1:15:25.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,你能看到 這裡有幾種木頭\N{\rENG}Well, as you can see, ahem, there are several kinds of wood here.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:25.60,1:15:29.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,松木 樺木 冷杉 還有 如果你仔細看還能看到...\N{\rENG}Pine, birch, fir, and, if you look closely, you will see...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:30.10,1:15:31.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 謝謝 - 托爾森先生\N{\rENG}- Thank you. - Mr. Tolson.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.44,1:15:35.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,每種木材都有自己獨特的內部紋理 年輪和梔...\N{\rENG}That each has its own internal markings, rings and knots...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:35.28,1:15:39.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,還有獨特的外在紋理 是機器打磨原木的時候形成的\N{\rENG}...and its own external markings from the machinery used to mill the raw timber...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.28,1:15:42.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,這些說明了製造梯子的工具\N{\rENG}...and these that mark the tools used to build the ladder.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:42.87,1:15:46.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,問題是 這些能如何幫我們找到 綁架犯呢 科勒先生？\N{\rENG}The question is, how does this help us identify the kidnappers, Mr. Koehler?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:47.12,1:15:48.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,我需要更多經費\N{\rENG}I need more money, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:48.91,1:15:51.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 更多經費？為了幹嘛？ - 郵資\N{\rENG}- More money, sir, for what? - Postage.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:51.58,1:15:54.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,我需要給東岸的每家廠子寫信\N{\rENG}I need to write every mill on the East Coast...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:54.25,1:15:57.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,看他們的刀片切口是否和這個吻合\N{\rENG}...and see if their blades match these marks.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:57.80,1:15:59.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,嗯\N{\rENG}Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:59.63,1:16:02.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,把每個廠家的資訊寫進報告 並把追蹤的所有線索畫成地圖\N{\rENG}I want a report from each mill and a map tracking all leads.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:02.97,1:16:06.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,我回到紐約以後 我要你有點料可以報告\N{\rENG}By the time I get back from New York, I want something to report.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:06.47,1:16:07.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,日安\N{\rENG}Good day.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:16.65,1:16:18.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,就像他們之前的共產主義激進分子一樣\N{\rENG}Just like the communist radicals before them...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:18.99,1:16:20.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,黑幫也沒落了\N{\rENG}...the gangster fell from favor.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:20.65,1:16:24.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在終於 孩子們夢想 成為聯邦調查局探員\N{\rENG}Now, finally, children dreamed of joining the FBl.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:33.08,1:16:35.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,站起來 站起來\N{\rENG}On your feet. On your feet.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:39.92,1:16:40.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,喂？\N{\rENG}Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:41.76,1:16:43.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,他在洗澡 可以留個言嗎？\N{\rENG}He's taking his shower. Any message?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:44.09,1:16:46.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,那裡根本不能洗澡\N{\rENG}There ain't any shower there, copper.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.69,1:17:00.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,鄧波兒小姐！\N{\rENG}Miss Temple!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:01.03,1:17:04.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,胡佛先生 我在想 你願不願意加入我的警力組\N{\rENG}Mr. Hoover, I was wondering if you would join my police force.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:04.91,1:17:06.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,當然了 鄧波兒小姐\N{\rENG}Why, yes, Miss Temple.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:06.45,1:17:10.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,假如你願意變成一名體面的女特工 再親一親我\N{\rENG}If you agree to be an honorary G-Woman, and give me one little kiss.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:11.50,1:17:14.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不知道你的妻子會不會允許了\N{\rENG}I don't know if your wife would approve, Mr. Hoover.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.63,1:17:17.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,但你看 我還和我媽媽住在一起\N{\rENG}But, you see, I still live with my mother.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:18.88,1:17:21.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,噢 好吧\N{\rENG}Oh. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:21.63,1:17:23.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 看這邊！ - 真漂亮\N{\rENG}- Look this way! - That's real spiffy.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.05,1:17:26.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,微笑一個 謝謝\N{\rENG}Nice smile. Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.31,1:17:31.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,先生 我們需要一個說明...\N{\rENG}Excuse me, sir. Can we get a statement?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:31.39,1:17:32.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,您喜歡這部電影嗎？\N{\rENG}How'd you like the picture?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.02,1:17:36.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,這邊請\N{\rENG}This way, Mr. Hoover!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:36.40,1:17:37.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,您先請 母親\N{\rENG}After you, Mother.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.41,1:17:52.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們去俱樂部嗎？\N{\rENG}Should we go to the club?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:52.91,1:17:55.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,等我們把媽媽送回賓館\N{\rENG}After we drop Mother off at the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:15.64,1:18:18.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,你們和阿妮塔·科爾比（演員）一桌\N{\rENG}I have you at a table with Anita Colby.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.06,1:18:22.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,樂拉·羅傑斯和她的女兒金吉爾（演員） 也問了她們能不能一起\N{\rENG}Lela Rogers and her daughter Ginger have asked if they can join.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:22.53,1:18:24.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,多多益善\N{\rENG}As long as it's near the front.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:24.24,1:18:27.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,羅傑斯小姐 很高興見到你 這應該就是你的母親了\N{\rENG}Miss Rogers, pleasure to meet you. This must be your mother.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:27.45,1:18:28.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,你好\N{\rENG}Hello.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:28.62,1:18:31.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是J·愛德格·胡佛 這位是克萊德·托爾森 阿妮塔 很高興見到你\N{\rENG}J. Edgar Hoover. This is Clyde Tolson. Anita, good to see you.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:40.21,1:18:42.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,子彈是從後腦勺射入...\N{\rENG}The bullet entered the back of the head...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:42.30,1:18:44.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,從前面大概臉頰的地方穿出\N{\rENG}...and exited through the front near his cheek.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:44.92,1:18:48.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,大多數人沒有認識到的是 其實流血很少\N{\rENG}The thing that most people don't realize is that there is little blood.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:48.47,1:18:52.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,子彈產生的熱量 會把入射產生的傷口密封起來\N{\rENG}The heat from the bullet actually seals the wound as it enters...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:52.30,1:18:57.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,所以其實犯罪現場比你們電影中 描繪的要正常多了\N{\rENG}...so the crime scene is far more peaceful than is depicted in your moving pictures.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.27,1:19:00.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,還有小林迪 您親眼看到這個孩子了嗎？\N{\rENG}And little Lindy. Did you see the child with your own eyes?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:01.48,1:19:03.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,有一些案件的細節...\N{\rENG}Those are details I wouldn't disclose...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:03.69,1:19:06.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,最好還是不要透露給 你們這些如此優雅的女人\N{\rENG}...with a refined group of women such as yourselves.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:06.53,1:19:12.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,我可不能讓你們傷心流淚 但我向你們保證 我們仍舊在查案\N{\rENG}I couldn't bear to make you shed a tear. But I assure you this, we are on the case.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:12.58,1:19:15.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,我在巴黎見到了林德伯格一家 都差點認不出了\N{\rENG}I saw the Lindberghs in Paris. I hardly recognized them.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.83,1:19:16.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,嗯\N{\rENG}Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.00,1:19:20.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,只有正義才能讓他們 重新找回生活的意義\N{\rENG}Only justice can bring reason back to their lives.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.67,1:19:25.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,我可以跟你們說說已經找到的機密線索 你們要發誓保密\N{\rENG}But I might share one confidential clue with you, if you swear to secrecy.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:26.72,1:19:27.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,當然\N{\rENG}Of course.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:28.01,1:19:30.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,贖金中金色標記的鈔票已經浮出水面\N{\rENG}The gold notes from the ransom money have surfaced.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:30.64,1:19:32.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,猜猜是在哪裡？\N{\rENG}And can you guess where?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:32.51,1:19:34.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,拜託 告訴我們吧\N{\rENG}Tell us. Please, Mr. Hoover.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:34.18,1:19:36.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,在布朗克斯（紐約） 出現了三次\N{\rENG}In the Bronx, on three occasions.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:36.56,1:19:38.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,每個店主都說...\N{\rENG}And each one of the shop owners claim...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.60,1:19:42.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,鈔票都來自一個 有尖下巴和德國口音的男人\N{\rENG}...they received them from a man with a pointed chin and a German accent.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:45.36,1:19:48.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,聽我說 胡佛先生\N{\rENG}Take my word for it, Mr. Hoover.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:48.36,1:19:51.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,就算全世界都仰慕 沒有愛 還是會少了一塊\N{\rENG}All the admiration in the world can't fill the spot love goes.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.36,1:19:52.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,嗯\N{\rENG}Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:52.57,1:19:54.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,或者說 可以溫暖你的床\N{\rENG}Or keep your bed warm.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:56.70,1:19:58.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是國家的人 科爾比小姐\N{\rENG}I serve my country, Miss Colby.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:58.75,1:20:01.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,國家對我的贊許 已經是無上的榮譽\N{\rENG}The nation's admiration is more than enough for me. Heh.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:02.46,1:20:05.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,但不管如何 你的床鋪還是冰冷\N{\rENG}But it likely makes for a cold bed.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:06.71,1:20:10.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,胡佛先生 您是否考慮和我跳一支舞？\N{\rENG}Mr. Hoover, would it be out of the question to bother you for a dance?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:10.34,1:20:12.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是什麼意思？\N{\rENG}Oh, uh, how do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:13.47,1:20:15.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,只是跳支舞\N{\rENG}Well, simply a dance.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:15.60,1:20:17.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,你會跳舞的吧？\N{\rENG}You do dance, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.47,1:20:20.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,呃 這倒是我還未掌握的技能\N{\rENG}Well, that is a skill that, um, I haven't yet mastered.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:21.19,1:20:24.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,已經不早了 是嗎 托爾森？\N{\rENG}And the night is getting long, isn't it, Mr. Tolson? Mr. Tolson?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:24.48,1:20:27.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒有比現在更好的了 這是我最愛的歌 來吧\N{\rENG}No time like the present. It's my favorite song, come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:27.36,1:20:29.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們該走了 我們還有很多工作要做\N{\rENG}It's time we leave. Uh, we have a great deal of work.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:30.03,1:20:32.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們...我們... 我們明天還有很多工作\N{\rENG}We... We... We have a great deal of work tomorrow...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:32.41,1:20:36.16,CHT,,0,0,0,,恐怕沒有時間跳舞了 我們很忙的\N{\rENG}...and I'm afraid we don't have time to dance. We're very busy, aren't we?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:36.33,1:20:37.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rENG}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:37.79,1:20:40.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,我真誠地道歉\N{\rENG}And my sincere apologies. I...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.25,1:20:42.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,托爾森 我們現在走吧 非常感謝你們\N{\rENG}Right now, Mr. Tolson. Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:42.37,1:20:43.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,晚安\N{\rENG}- Good evening. - Ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:44.00,1:20:45.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,晚安\N{\rENG}Good night.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:49.30,1:20:50.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不...\N{\rENG}I don't...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:51.26,1:20:52.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,我...\N{\rENG}I...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.47,1:20:55.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不喜歡跳舞 母親\N{\rENG}I don't... I don't like to... I don't like to dance, Mother.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:55.43,1:20:58.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 我不喜歡跳... - 愛德格 去照照鏡子\N{\rENG}- I don't like to da... - Edgar, go look in the mirror.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:58.56,1:21:01.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,按照醫生教的方法說話 小飛毛腿\N{\rENG}Talk the way the doctor taught you to. Be my little Speedy.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:12.78,1:21:14.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,我可以說...說...\N{\rENG}I can spit my words out with... With...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:16.37,1:21:19.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,我可以準確地 清晰地 用詞準確地說話\N{\rENG}I can spit my words out with precision, diction, and clarity.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:19.95,1:21:24.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,我可以準確地... 清晰地 用詞準確地說話\N{\rENG}I can sp... Spit my words out with precision, diction, and clarity.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.42,1:21:32.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,我工作嫺熟 出眾 做了了不起的事\N{\rENG}I'm a proficient, remarkable lad, capable of remarkable feats.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:32.55,1:21:35.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,我... 媽 我不喜歡跳舞\N{\rENG}I'm a profic... Mother. Mother, I don't like to dance.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.64,1:21:39.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,應該說我不喜歡和女人跳舞\N{\rENG}Mostly I don't like to dance with women.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:39.56,1:21:41.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,我覺得是時候讓你知道這個了\N{\rENG}I think it's time you knew this.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:41.68,1:21:44.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,我覺得這很丟人 我不喜歡丟人\N{\rENG}And I find it humiliating and I refuse to be humiliated.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:44.48,1:21:46.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,愛德格 別說了\N{\rENG}Edgar, stop.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:47.98,1:21:49.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,你還記得巴頓·品克斯嗎？\N{\rENG}Do you remember Barton Pincus?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:51.19,1:21:52.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,記得\N{\rENG}Yes, Mother.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:52.94,1:21:54.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,他的父親是鐘錶匠\N{\rENG}His father was a watchmaker.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:55.66,1:21:58.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,他比我小10歲 你叫他...\N{\rENG}He was 10 years younger than me and you used to call him...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:00.79,1:22:03.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,博迪還是達菲 之類的吧\N{\rENG}...Birdy or Daffy or something to that effect.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:04.00,1:22:06.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,那你還記得達菲最後怎樣了嗎？\N{\rENG}And do you remember what happened to Daffy?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.67,1:22:10.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,在學校發現他 穿了裙子 戴著有花的帽子以後？\N{\rENG}After the school custodian discovered him in a hoop skirt and flower bonnet?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:13.01,1:22:15.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,他被迫站在學校外面...\N{\rENG}He was made to stand outside in front of the school...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.68,1:22:18.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,穿著裙子 戴著花帽子 作為懲罰\N{\rENG}...wearing the bonnet and skirt as punishment.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.55,1:22:22.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,你就沒想過 我們為什麼叫他達菲？\N{\rENG}Did you ever wonder why we called him Daffy?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:23.22,1:22:26.85,CHT,,0,0,0,,因為他奇怪的行為吧 我猜\N{\rENG}For his odd behavior, I believe.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:28.06,1:22:30.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,那是“水仙花”的略稱\N{\rENG}It's short for "daffodil," Edgar.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:32.53,1:22:34.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,你還記得這個娘炮最後怎樣了嗎？\N{\rENG}Do you remember what happened to Daffodil Pincus?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:36.61,1:22:38.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的 他...\N{\rENG}Yes, Mother. He...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:39.20,1:22:41.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,六周之後 他開槍自盡\N{\rENG}He shot himself six weeks after.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:41.24,1:22:42.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,就是這樣\N{\rENG}That's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:43.20,1:22:47.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,我每天都感謝上帝 我的兒子們不用遭受如此折磨\N{\rENG}And I thank God every day that my own sons don't suffer from his condition.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.21,1:22:49.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,愛德格\N{\rENG}Edgar.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:51.42,1:22:54.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,我寧願要個死人 也不願要個娘炮的兒子\N{\rENG}I'd rather have a dead son than a daffodil for a son.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:59.39,1:23:02.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在 我來教你怎麼跳舞\N{\rENG}And now, I'm gonna teach you to dance.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:06.77,1:23:08.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,是\N{\rENG}Yes, Mother.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:42.97,1:23:45.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 把它拿到這裡來 - 是\N{\rENG}- Bring this right over here, please. - Sure, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:46.27,1:23:49.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,好 你是什麼時候接到這單的？\N{\rENG}All right. Now, when did you get this shipment?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:50.48,1:23:54.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,有陣子了 我想應該是1931年11月\N{\rENG}It's a long while back. I'm thinking, uh, November 1931.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:55.82,1:23:57.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,綁架案的3個月前\N{\rENG}Three months before the kidnapping.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:59.32,1:24:00.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,好的 謝謝\N{\rENG}All right. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:00.91,1:24:04.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,伐木場是現金交易的 沒有留下任何收據或者名字\N{\rENG}The lumberyard is a cash business, there aren't any receipts or names.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:04.53,1:24:07.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,至少告訴我們 在犯案之前他都在哪裡買東西\N{\rENG}It tells us where he was shopping before we were looking.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:07.58,1:24:10.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,給我指一指 那些贖金鈔票都出現在什麼地方\N{\rENG}Show me the addresses of where the ransom bills have shown up.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:10.62,1:24:13.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,456號西三街\N{\rENG}It's 456 West Third.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:13.63,1:24:16.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,還有476號西三街\N{\rENG}And 476 West Third.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:17.30,1:24:18.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,還有下面這條街這裡\N{\rENG}And down the street right here.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.30,1:24:24.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們知道要找的人是誰了\N{\rENG}We knew who we were looking for.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:24.80,1:24:27.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,他是在這一片生活工作了很長時間的人\N{\rENG}Someone who'd done business in this neighborhood for years.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:28.14,1:24:29.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,應該還在那裡\N{\rENG}Someone who was still there.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:29.60,1:24:31.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,他身高普通 有藍眼睛\N{\rENG}He was average height, blue eyes.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.90,1:24:33.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,高顴骨 尖下巴\N{\rENG}High cheekbones and a pointy chin.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:33.98,1:24:38.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的 尖下巴 還有口音 像是...\N{\rENG}Yes, sir, a pointed chin and an accent, like a...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:38.32,1:24:39.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,德國口音 大概？\N{\rENG}German accent, maybe?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:40.15,1:24:42.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,一個有高顴骨的德國人\N{\rENG}A German with big cheekbones.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:43.66,1:24:46.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,我...會給他惹麻煩嗎？\N{\rENG}Am I, uh, going to get him in some kind of trouble?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.45,1:24:50.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,他沒幹壞事就不會 我們是聯邦調查局的 我們是好人\N{\rENG}Not if he didn't do anything wrong. We're the FBl, son. We're the good guys.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:52.50,1:24:54.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是沃爾特·賴爾存的錢\N{\rENG}It was deposited by Walter Lyle.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:55.00,1:24:59.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,他在列克星敦大道和127街路口 開了個加油站\N{\rENG}He manages the gas station up on Lexington and 127th.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:59.34,1:25:00.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,你是沃爾特·賴爾？\N{\rENG}Walter Lyle?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:01.42,1:25:03.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,你還記得用這個付錢的男人嗎？\N{\rENG}You remember the man that paid with this?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:03.30,1:25:05.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,我記得 他買了89分錢的汽油\N{\rENG}Yes, I remember him. He bought 89 cents worth of gas.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:05.93,1:25:08.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,他用這個付錢的？\N{\rENG}And he paid with this bill?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:08.85,1:25:11.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的 但我不認識他 那之後就沒有見過\N{\rENG}Yes, sir. But I don't know him. I haven't seen him since.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:12.27,1:25:15.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果他再來 你能認出來嗎？\N{\rENG}You would remember him if he came in again?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:15.19,1:25:18.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,能啊 他是德國人吧 我想 我是說 有那種口音 還有尖下巴\N{\rENG}Yeah, he was German, I think, I mean, with an accent and pointed chin.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:18.69,1:25:21.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 還有高顴骨 是嗎？ - 是啊 我覺得這鈔票挺好笑的\N{\rENG}- High cheekbones, right? - Yeah. I looked at the bill funny.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:21.53,1:25:24.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,他跟我拍胸脯說 他家裡還有這一樣的一百多張\N{\rENG}He assured me he had a hundred more like it at home.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.20,1:25:25.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,你跟他聊了什麼？\N{\rENG}You had a conversation with him?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.49,1:25:27.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒有 就這些了\N{\rENG}No, that was it.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:28.58,1:25:29.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝 賴爾先生\N{\rENG}Thank you, Mr. Lyle.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:29.79,1:25:32.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,我有記下車牌號\N{\rENG}I wrote down the license plate number.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:33.37,1:25:35.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,就是寫在鈔票邊上的那個號碼\N{\rENG}That's the writing along the edge of the bill.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:38.13,1:25:39.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們走\N{\rENG}Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:45.89,1:25:48.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,甘迪 叫上托爾森\N{\rENG}Miss Gandy, get Mr. Tolson.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:57.06,1:25:58.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,西斯科探員\N{\rENG}Agent Sisk.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:58.40,1:26:02.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,紐約機動車辦公室 說這是一輛1930年的藍色道奇轎車\N{\rENG}The New York Motor Vehicles Bureau describes it as a blue 1930 Dodge sedan.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.28,1:26:04.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,車主是一個德國出生的木匠\N{\rENG}The owner is a carpenter born in Germany...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:04.40,1:26:08.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,住在布朗克斯的東222街1279號\N{\rENG}...lives at 1279 East 222nd Street in the Bronx.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.91,1:26:10.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,名字叫布魯諾·理查·哈普特曼\N{\rENG}His name is Bruno Richard Hauptmann.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.13,1:26:23.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,行動\N{\rENG}Let's move.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:23.38,1:26:25.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,1934年9月19日...\N{\rENG}On September 19th, 1934...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:25.76,1:26:28.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,就在我們抓到這個 美國頭號通緝犯之前\N{\rENG}...before we could arrest the most wanted man in America...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:28.76,1:26:33.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,他被當地員警要求停車 因為車尾燈壞了\N{\rENG}...he'd been pulled over by a local cop for a broken tail light.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.18,1:26:34.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,真不敢相信\N{\rENG}Can't believe this.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:36.85,1:26:38.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,停車\N{\rENG}Pull over.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:46.61,1:26:47.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,聯邦調查局！ 舉起手來！\N{\rENG}FBl, put your hands up!
Dialogue: 0,1:26:48.03,1:26:49.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 舉起手來！ - 有問題嗎？\N{\rENG}- Put them up! - Ls there a problem?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:50.07,1:26:52.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,下車！\N{\rENG}Get out of the car!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:02.50,1:27:03.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,布魯諾·哈普特曼\N{\rENG}Bruno Hauptmann...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:03.71,1:27:07.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,你因涉嫌綁架及謀殺小查理斯·林德伯格 而被逮捕\N{\rENG}...you are under arrest for the kidnapping and murder of Charles Lindbergh, Jr.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:07.80,1:27:09.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,把他銬起來\N{\rENG}Cuff him, boys.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.31,1:27:17.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們終於抓到了他\N{\rENG}We finally had him.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:17.48,1:27:20.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們需要將他定罪 但不像以前的那些審判\N{\rENG}Now we had to convict, but unlike trials of the past...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:20.81,1:27:26.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們有法醫 專家證人 還有證據\N{\rENG}...we now had forensics, expert witnesses, and facts.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:30.32,1:27:31.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們需要起個標題 加里森調查員\N{\rENG}We need a title, Agent Garrison.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:32.95,1:27:34.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,馬上就好\N{\rENG}Right away, Mr. Hoover.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:36.37,1:27:38.16,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們正忙呢 甘迪\N{\rENG}We are working, Miss Gandy.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:38.33,1:27:39.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,磁帶送來了\N{\rENG}The tape came in.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:40.50,1:27:42.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,拿到我的私密辦公室去\N{\rENG}Bring it to my private office.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:43.84,1:27:45.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,這些就可以了 加里森調查員\N{\rENG}That'll be all for now, Agent Garrison.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:03.27,1:28:05.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,我只是想說...\N{\rENG}I just have to say...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.15,1:28:09.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,你坐在那個酒吧對面的時候太美了\N{\rENG}...you looked so beautiful sitting across that bar.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.74,1:28:11.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,我看到你在盯著我\N{\rENG}I saw you watching me.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:11.70,1:28:13.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,我得承認...\N{\rENG}I have to admit I was watching you...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:13.74,1:28:15.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,我看你好長時間了\N{\rENG}...for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:19.62,1:28:20.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,慢一點\N{\rENG}Slow down a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:21.12,1:28:22.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,好\N{\rENG}All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:24.42,1:28:26.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,我來把這脫了\N{\rENG}Let me take this off.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:26.67,1:28:28.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,轉過去\N{\rENG}Turn around.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:30.72,1:28:31.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,行嗎？\N{\rENG}You got it?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:54.20,1:28:56.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,甘迪 我跟你說了不能打擾\N{\rENG}Miss Gandy, I told you I am not to be disturbed.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.74,1:28:58.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,對不起 胡佛先生\N{\rENG}I'm sorry. Mr. Hoover?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:58.54,1:29:02.16,CHT,,0,0,0,,是緊急事件 珊科林探員從達拉斯來電\N{\rENG}Yes, it's urgent. I have Agent Shanklin on the line from Dallas.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.33,1:29:03.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,對不起 胡佛先生\N{\rENG}My apologies, Mr. Hoover.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:04.08,1:29:05.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,是我讓甘迪小姐讓我通話\N{\rENG}I told Miss Gandy to put me through.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:05.79,1:29:08.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,什麼事 探員？\N{\rENG}What is it, Agent Shanklin?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:08.55,1:29:11.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,總統被槍殺了\N{\rENG}Sir, the president has been shot.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:13.63,1:29:15.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,還有誰知道這件事？\N{\rENG}Who else knows about this?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.18,1:29:18.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,還沒有人 我想你應該在媒體之前知道\N{\rENG}No one, sir. I thought you should know before the press reports it.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:19.77,1:29:22.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 謝謝  - 不用\N{\rENG}- Thank you, Agent Shanklin. - Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:29.53,1:29:31.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,噢 感覺真棒\N{\rENG}Oh, that feels so good.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:58.05,1:30:00.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,馬上把我接到羅伯特·甘迺迪\N{\rENG}Get me Robert Kennedy immediately.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:07.19,1:30:08.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,胡佛先生？\N{\rENG}Mr. Hoover?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:09.11,1:30:12.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,甘迺迪先生 總統剛剛被槍殺了\N{\rENG}Mr. Kennedy, the president has been shot.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:14.20,1:30:15.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,什麼？\N{\rENG}What?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:15.78,1:30:17.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,胡佛先生？什麼？\N{\rENG}Mr. Hoover? What?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:20.49,1:30:21.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,胡佛先生？\N{\rENG}Mr. Hoover?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:32.84,1:30:34.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在領先的是“冷山”...\N{\rENG}It's Frosty Mountain in front...
Dialogue: 0,1:30:35.05,1:30:36.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,領先一個半身位\N{\rENG}...by a length and a half.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:36.30,1:30:38.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,“爵士”在第三位 落後六個身位\N{\rENG}That's Jazz third by six.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:38.85,1:30:43.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,“巴掌傑克”第四位 “大明星梅瑞爾”落後四分之三個身位\N{\rENG}Slapjack's fourth, final head. Popstar Merell three quarters.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:43.56,1:30:48.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,開始衝刺 “冷山”在左邊 領先一個半身位\N{\rENG}Turning for home, Frosty Mountain under the left by a fraction and a length and a half.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:48.52,1:30:51.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,五號 要追上了\N{\rENG}Number five. He's gaining on them.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:53.03,1:30:54.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在還是“冷山”領先\N{\rENG}It's Frosty Mountain, now.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:56.15,1:30:58.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不確定我是不是押了他\N{\rENG}I'm not sure if I bet on that one.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:58.53,1:31:01.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,啊 我們又輸了 克萊德\N{\rENG}Ah. We lost again, Clyde.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:01.91,1:31:04.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,“德克斯托”落後半個身位\N{\rENG}Dextro back by a half-length on the rail.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:04.50,1:31:07.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,“德克斯托”開始啟動了 芬尼利抽打了他\N{\rENG}Dextro now making his move. Findlay gives him the whip.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:07.75,1:31:09.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,來了 來了\N{\rENG}Oh, there he goes, there he goes!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:09.67,1:31:11.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,加油 德克斯托 加油！\N{\rENG}Come on, Dextro, come on, Dextro!
Dialogue: 0,1:31:56.51,1:31:58.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,你看到他的鞋子了嗎？\N{\rENG}- Did you see his shoes? - Ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:59.13,1:32:00.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,德斯·阿納茲？（音樂家 演員）\N{\rENG}Desi Arnaz?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:00.38,1:32:03.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,你是說那雙上面有很醜帶扣的 鱷魚皮鞋？\N{\rENG}You mean the crocodile ones with the horrible buckles across the top?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:04.05,1:32:05.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,我一點都沒注意到\N{\rENG}No, I didn't notice them one bit.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:05.77,1:32:08.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,你不覺得他們有那麼多錢 就不該對時尚敏感點嗎\N{\rENG}You'd think with their money they'd have a bit of fashion sense...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:08.60,1:32:10.85,CHT,,0,0,0,,或者至少雇個對時尚敏感的人\N{\rENG}Ha, ha. - ...or at least pay someone to have it.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:11.02,1:32:12.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,噢 還有他那個人造一樣的老婆\N{\rENG}Oh, and his faux-ginger wife.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:12.77,1:32:17.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,她走進來的時候 我都覺得會有獵人 一槍把她的帽子給轟了\N{\rENG}When she walked in, I thought a hunter was gonna pull a rifle on that hat of hers.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:18.74,1:32:20.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,就像這樣 你看 就像...\N{\rENG}It was like this, you see, like...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:20.74,1:32:22.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,哈哈 是啊 那些羽毛\N{\rENG}Ha-ha-ha. That's right, with the feathers.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:26.54,1:32:29.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,你知道嗎 我真的很在乎你 克萊德 真的\N{\rENG}You know, I care so very much for you, Clyde. I do.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:31.83,1:32:34.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,我也愛你 愛德格\N{\rENG}And I love you, Edgar.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:42.39,1:32:43.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,你還好嗎？\N{\rENG}ls everything okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:43.89,1:32:45.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,我沒事\N{\rENG}Yes, yes, I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:45.80,1:32:47.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,我沒事\N{\rENG}I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:50.48,1:32:53.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,我一直想問你一件事 克萊德\N{\rENG}I've been meaning to ask you something, Clyde.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:53.98,1:32:54.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,問吧\N{\rENG}Anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:57.32,1:33:01.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,你覺得那個女演員  桃樂絲·拉莫爾怎樣？\N{\rENG}What do you think of Dorothy Lamour, the actress?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:01.65,1:33:03.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,和魯迪·瓦力在斯托克俱樂部的那個？\N{\rENG}With Rudy Vallee at the Stork Club?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:03.45,1:33:05.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的 就是她\N{\rENG}Yes. That's the one.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:05.49,1:33:08.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,對我來說是太女性化了吧 但是...\N{\rENG}She's a little camp for me, but, heh...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:11.71,1:33:14.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是在想 要她跟我一起\N{\rENG}Well, I've been thinking of taking her up on a proposal is all.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:16.17,1:33:17.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,吃晚餐？\N{\rENG}For dinner?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:17.80,1:33:19.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,不 不 不是晚餐\N{\rENG}No, no, not dinner.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:20.67,1:33:22.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們已經一起吃過晚餐好幾次了\N{\rENG}We've been to dinner several times now.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:24.01,1:33:25.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,什麼時候？\N{\rENG}When?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:26.93,1:33:29.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,噢 在紐約 我週末去那裡的時候\N{\rENG}Oh, in New York, when I've gone up on the weekends.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:32.52,1:33:33.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,我知道了\N{\rENG}I see.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:36.06,1:33:40.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,我想...我想要說的是... 克萊德...是...\N{\rENG}I suppose what I'm... What I'm trying to say here, Clyde, is, well...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:43.40,1:33:45.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,我覺得是時候有個胡佛夫人了\N{\rENG}...l think it may be time for a Mrs. Hoover.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:53.66,1:33:56.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,你不喜歡她嗎？ 是不是？\N{\rENG}What, you don't like her? Ls that it?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:57.71,1:33:59.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,你別讓我這麼難堪 愛德格\N{\rENG}Don't you make a fool of me, Edgar.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:00.00,1:34:03.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,我沒有 我沒有想讓你難堪\N{\rENG}I'm not, Clyde, I'm not making a fool of you.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:05.30,1:34:08.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,你們...你們有做過了嗎？\N{\rENG}Have you...? Have you become physical?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:10.81,1:34:12.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,有\N{\rENG}Yes, we have.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:13.06,1:34:14.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,怎麼了 克萊德？\N{\rENG}What is it, Clyde?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:14.48,1:34:19.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,你想讓我一直過不了完整的生活？ 這是你想要的嗎？\N{\rENG}Do you want me to be half a person? Remain incomplete, is that what you want?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:20.52,1:34:22.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,我對你來說 只算是半吊子？\N{\rENG}ls that what I am to you, incompletion?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:23.28,1:34:25.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,克萊德 給我馬上把這杯子撿起來！\N{\rENG}Clyde, pick that glass up immediately!
Dialogue: 0,1:34:25.24,1:34:27.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,不我不會！我沒理由這樣做！\N{\rENG}No, I will not! I have no reason to!
Dialogue: 0,1:34:27.99,1:34:30.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,我拒絕！來啊 炒了我\N{\rENG}I refuse! So, go on, fire me.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:30.91,1:34:32.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,快啊 現在就炒了我！\N{\rENG}Do it. Now!
Dialogue: 0,1:34:32.37,1:34:34.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,你冷靜一下 這行為太愚蠢了\N{\rENG}Get a hold of yourself. You're acting like a fool!
Dialogue: 0,1:34:35.08,1:34:36.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,住手！\N{\rENG}- Agh! - Stop this!
Dialogue: 0,1:34:37.08,1:34:39.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,克萊德！你沒穿鞋子 天哪！\N{\rENG}Clyde! You have no shoes on, for God's sakes!
Dialogue: 0,1:34:39.75,1:34:42.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,不 我不會 我不要聽你說了！\N{\rENG}No. No, I will not! I won't even listen to you!
Dialogue: 0,1:34:42.59,1:34:45.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,你永遠不能對我發號施令了！ 你沒有這個權利！\N{\rENG}You will never tell me what to do! You just lost that right!
Dialogue: 0,1:34:45.59,1:34:47.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 住口！ - 我看透你了！\N{\rENG}- Stop it! - I see right through you!
Dialogue: 0,1:34:47.51,1:34:50.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,你就是個膽小的 沒良心的 差勁的小人！\N{\rENG}You're a scared, heartless, horrible little man!
Dialogue: 0,1:34:50.93,1:34:52.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,你竟敢...\N{\rENG}- Unh! Don't you dare! - Unh!
Dialogue: 0,1:35:30.51,1:35:32.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,你以後膽敢再這樣做\N{\rENG}Don't you ever do that again.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:34.14,1:35:35.18,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不會了\N{\rENG}I won't.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:37.64,1:35:39.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,克萊...\N{\rENG}Cly...
Dialogue: 0,1:35:40.98,1:35:42.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,克萊德 你去哪？\N{\rENG}Clyde, where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:43.11,1:35:46.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,克萊德 求你了 不要留下我！\N{\rENG}Clyde, please. Clyde, don't leave me!
Dialogue: 0,1:35:46.74,1:35:47.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,克萊德 求你了\N{\rENG}Clyde, please.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:48.07,1:35:49.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,克萊德 對不起！\N{\rENG}Clyde, I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,1:35:49.99,1:35:51.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,克萊德 不要離開我！\N{\rENG}Clyde, please don't leave me!
Dialogue: 0,1:35:51.99,1:35:53.16,CHT,,0,0,0,,克萊德 求求你了！\N{\rENG}Clyde, I'm begging you!
Dialogue: 0,1:35:53.33,1:35:57.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,我求你了 克萊德！ 克萊德 拜託了\N{\rENG}I'm begging you, Clyde! Clyde, please.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:58.00,1:36:00.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,不管怎樣...\N{\rENG}After all...
Dialogue: 0,1:36:03.75,1:36:09.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,不管怎樣 我們還有一天的賽馬要看\N{\rENG}After all, we have another day of races.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:17.10,1:36:20.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,你以後要是再提起任何女性朋友...\N{\rENG}If you ever mention a lady friend again...
Dialogue: 0,1:36:20.77,1:36:23.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,那我就再也不會出現在你身邊\N{\rENG}...it will be the last time that you share my company.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:35.95,1:36:37.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,我愛你 克萊德\N{\rENG}Love you, Clyde.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:39.66,1:36:40.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,我愛你\N{\rENG}Love you.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:45.21,1:36:47.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,米特爾看上去挺有希望\N{\rENG}Mr. Meter looks promising.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:02.56,1:37:04.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,怎麼了 克萊德？\N{\rENG}- Unh. Ugh. - What is it, Clyde?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:05.06,1:37:06.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,克萊德？\N{\rENG}Clyde?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:06.77,1:37:08.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,快去叫醫生\N{\rENG}Someone get a doctor.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:08.32,1:37:09.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,克萊德\N{\rENG}Clyde.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:09.65,1:37:13.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,快去叫醫生！ 快去叫醫生！\N{\rENG}Someone get a doctor now! Someone get a doctor!
Dialogue: 0,1:37:13.74,1:37:16.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,克萊德 看著我 看著我\N{\rENG}Clyde, look at me. Look at me.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:16.83,1:37:19.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,快點去叫醫生啊！\N{\rENG}Someone get a doctor now!
Dialogue: 0,1:37:19.58,1:37:21.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,急救！\N{\rENG}Help!
Dialogue: 0,1:37:21.25,1:37:23.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,他的身體機能大部分都能恢復...\N{\rENG}He'll recover most of his function...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:23.25,1:37:26.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,但經歷如此一次中風 會限制他的工作時間\N{\rENG}...but a stroke like this, it will limit the hours he can work...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:26.42,1:37:28.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,以及他可以處理的信息量\N{\rENG}...the information he can process.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:28.17,1:37:29.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,你沒事吧 胡佛先生？\N{\rENG}Are you okay, Mr. Hoover?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:30.59,1:37:34.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,我沒事 我只是... 我週六在院子裡和狗玩了一會兒\N{\rENG}Yes, I'm fine. I just... I was playing with my dog in the yard on Saturday.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:34.26,1:37:36.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,可能只是脫水了\N{\rENG}Perhaps it's dehydration.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:37.10,1:37:40.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,或許是原因 但您也減少一些工作時間可能更明智\N{\rENG}That could do it, but it may be wise to reduce your hours as well.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:40.39,1:37:42.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,在您這個年紀 休息很重要\N{\rENG}At your age, it's important to take leave.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:43.48,1:37:46.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,甘迪 讓我們單獨談談\N{\rENG}Miss Gandy, please, give us some privacy.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:51.78,1:37:55.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,這麼跟你說吧 你要是膽敢再在我的同事面前說我的不是...\N{\rENG}Let me tell you, if you ever denigrate me in front of my staff again...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:55.36,1:37:58.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,我會讓你前途盡毀 明白了嗎？\N{\rENG}...I'll have you railroaded out of your profession. Understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:59.45,1:38:00.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,我很抱歉\N{\rENG}I apologize, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:01.45,1:38:02.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,跟我說說\N{\rENG}Tell me something.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:03.29,1:38:05.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,有什麼東西可以補充能量嗎？\N{\rENG}What do you have for energy?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:05.29,1:38:08.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們有節食的藥物 可以有所幫助\N{\rENG}We have diet medications which tend to give a boost.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:08.79,1:38:12.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,所以如果我減掉點體重 就會有更多能量？\N{\rENG}So I could lose a few pounds and have more energy as well?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:12.46,1:38:15.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,不要擔心您的體重 那是結實的重量\N{\rENG}Wouldn't worry about your weight, sir. It's solid weight.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:15.51,1:38:16.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,嗯\N{\rENG}Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:17.47,1:38:18.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,安排一下日常的檢查\N{\rENG}Schedule a daily visit.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:20.51,1:38:21.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,是\N{\rENG}Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:30.48,1:38:34.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們要把諾貝爾和平獎頒給馬丁·路德·金了 你相信嗎？\N{\rENG}They're giving King the Nobel Prize. Can you believe it?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:34.32,1:38:37.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,這些敗類和激進分子 已經在國際上都被捧起來了\N{\rENG}The degenerates and radicals are being lifted up internationally.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:37.49,1:38:40.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,就像1920年的情況又回來了\N{\rENG}It's like it's 1920 all over again.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:40.99,1:38:42.16,CHT,,0,0,0,,別\N{\rENG}Don't.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:43.00,1:38:45.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,當他發現 我們有這卷錄音帶...\N{\rENG}When he finds out that we have this audiotape...
Dialogue: 0,1:38:45.79,1:38:48.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們知道他真正是怎樣一個人...\N{\rENG}...that we know the truth about his character...
Dialogue: 0,1:38:48.17,1:38:51.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,他肯定要拒絕領獎 克萊德 相信我\N{\rENG}...he's going to decline the award, Clyde, believe me.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:51.96,1:38:54.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,詹森總統...\N{\rENG}President Johnson...
Dialogue: 0,1:38:54.21,1:38:55.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,等等\N{\rENG}Wait.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:55.84,1:38:57.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 克萊德 - 等等\N{\rENG}- Clyde. - Wait.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:57.18,1:39:01.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,你得學著簡潔一點說話 我好像都要聽不懂你了\N{\rENG}You're gonna have to learn to enunciate. I can't seem to understand you.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:01.26,1:39:05.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在的問題是 我們沒有合法的手段\N{\rENG}We have no legal tools.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:05.43,1:39:08.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,你看 我們的法律還沒跟上...\N{\rENG}You see, our laws have not kept pace...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:08.19,1:39:10.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,今天這些犯罪分子不斷進步的戰術\N{\rENG}...with the improved tactics of today's criminals.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:11.02,1:39:12.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,我來幫你\N{\rENG}I'm gonna do this for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:13.07,1:39:15.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,你怎麼想？\N{\rENG}What's your idea?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:15.53,1:39:18.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們有在媒體的朋友 對吧？\N{\rENG}Well, we have friends in the press, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:18.36,1:39:21.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們捏造故事 讓他們...\N{\rENG}We plant stories with them to ensure...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:21.45,1:39:25.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,這些可疑的激進分子的行為 全部暴露出來\N{\rENG}...that the activities of suspected radicals see the light of day.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:26.00,1:39:27.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們會追蹤消息來源\N{\rENG}They'll trace it.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:28.50,1:39:30.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,除非都是真的\N{\rENG}Well, only if it's true.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:31.00,1:39:33.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,你看 這就叫反間諜 克萊德\N{\rENG}See, it's called counterintelligence, Clyde.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:33.17,1:39:36.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,故事越是被捏造 影響力就越戲劇化\N{\rENG}The more untrue the story, the more dramatic the impact.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:36.67,1:39:39.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在 我要把這個賓館錄音帶...\N{\rENG}Now, I'm going to send the hotel recording...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:39.84,1:39:44.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,和一封私人信件一起 在諾貝爾獎頒獎前一天寄給他\N{\rENG}...along with a personal letter the day before he gets the Nobel Prize.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:44.39,1:39:48.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果他接受了這個獎 我們就直接把錄音帶發到媒體\N{\rENG}And if he accepts the award, we'll send the tape straight to the press.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:50.02,1:39:54.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,你確定你想要捲入 這次的監視？\N{\rENG}Are you sure that you want to be involved with that kind of surveillance?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:55.07,1:39:57.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,這就是為什麼這封信 不會是我寫的\N{\rENG}Well, that's why the letter won't be from me.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:57.78,1:40:00.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,會是捏造成 他自己手下寫的\N{\rENG}It'll be a fictitious letter from one of his own.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:01.74,1:40:07.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,那就不允許任何的翻錯了 我不確定我們能...\N{\rENG}Then there can be no room for error. I'm not sure that we could ensu...
Dialogue: 0,1:40:07.50,1:40:11.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,我聽不懂你在說什麼了 克萊德\N{\rENG}I cannot understand what you're saying, Clyde. Please.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:11.25,1:40:14.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,你要學著說話有點底氣\N{\rENG}Come on now. Learn to speak up.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:18.22,1:40:22.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,聽著 我要你明天來辦公室 這次沒得商量\N{\rENG}Now, listen, I'm gonna need you in the office tomorrow. No time to relent.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:25.22,1:40:26.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不行\N{\rENG}I can't.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:27.73,1:40:29.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,你當然行\N{\rENG}Yes, you can.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:29.81,1:40:31.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,吃吧\N{\rENG}Now eat.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:32.60,1:40:36.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,你會看到這麼長時間以後 她終於能把我的雞蛋做好了\N{\rENG}You'd think after all this time she'd be able to cook my egg correctly.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:38.11,1:40:40.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,這注射的都是什麼？\N{\rENG}What exactly are in these shots?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:40.45,1:40:41.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,只是維他命...\N{\rENG}Oh, it's just vitamins...
Dialogue: 0,1:40:41.86,1:40:43.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,還有一些提神的\N{\rENG}...a little extra pick-me-up.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:56.34,1:40:57.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,“看看你的內心”\N{\rENG}"Look into your heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:57.92,1:41:02.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,“你知道你自己是個大騙子 對我們所有黑人都有責任”\N{\rENG}You know you are a complete fraud and a great liability to all of us Negroes."
Dialogue: 0,1:41:02.93,1:41:06.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,我說的是“我們” 甘迪 “我們” 不是 “我”\N{\rENG}I said "us," Miss Gandy, "us," not "the."
Dialogue: 0,1:41:06.80,1:41:08.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,您現在是黑人了？\N{\rENG}You're a Negro now, sir?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:08.43,1:41:11.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,把我說的每個字都寫下來 明白了嗎？\N{\rENG}Write every word as I say it, is that understood?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:11.48,1:41:14.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,“這個國家的白人騙子已經夠多了...”\N{\rENG}Now, "White people in this country have enough frauds of their own...
Dialogue: 0,1:41:15.15,1:41:17.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,“但他們這次沒有...”\N{\rENG}...but they do not have one at this time...
Dialogue: 0,1:41:17.32,1:41:19.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,“沒有任何人能和你相比”\N{\rENG}...that is anywhere near your equal.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:19.40,1:41:22.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,- “我要重申...” - 這是做什麼用的？\N{\rENG}- I repeat..." - Sir, what is this exercise?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:22.49,1:41:26.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,甘迪 我在口述的時候沒時間回答問題 快寫\N{\rENG}Miss Gandy, I am not going to entertain questions during my dictation, now write.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:27.79,1:41:32.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,“我要重申 你是一個大騙子 充滿罪惡 狠毒的人”\N{\rENG}"I repeat, you are a colossal fraud and an evil, vicious one, at that!
Dialogue: 0,1:41:32.92,1:41:36.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,“你並不信仰上帝 你並不信仰任何道德準則！”\N{\rENG}You do not believe in God. You do not believe in any personal moral principles!"
Dialogue: 0,1:41:36.92,1:41:39.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,我能不能問問這封信要寄給誰...\N{\rENG}Sir, may I ask who this will be addressed to...
Dialogue: 0,1:41:39.38,1:41:41.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,問題不是寄給誰 甘迪 不是寄給誰\N{\rENG}The question is not to whom, Miss Gandy, not to whom...
Dialogue: 0,1:41:42.09,1:41:45.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,而是誰寄的 並且絕對不是從這裡寄出的 明白了嗎？\N{\rENG}...but from whom and it is not from this office, is that understood?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:45.51,1:41:47.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,“你其實不是一個領導人...”\N{\rENG}"You have turned out to be not a leader...
Dialogue: 0,1:41:47.93,1:41:51.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,“而是一個放蕩的 變態的 道德低下的人”\N{\rENG}...but a dissolute, abnormal, moral imbecile.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:51.60,1:41:54.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,“只有一件事你能做了 你也知道怎麼做”\N{\rENG}There's only one thing left to do and you know what that is.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:54.52,1:41:57.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,“只有這條出路 你最好接受...”\N{\rENG}There's but one way out, and you better take it...
Dialogue: 0,1:41:57.19,1:42:02.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,“在你這些骯髒的 變態的 欺詐的行為 暴露在這個國家之前”\N{\rENG}...before your filthy, abnormal, fraudulent self is bared to this nation."
Dialogue: 0,1:42:02.44,1:42:04.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,都記下來了嗎？\N{\rENG}Did you get everything?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:04.91,1:42:07.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 愛德格 - 打出來\N{\rENG}- Edgar. - Type it up.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:08.24,1:42:09.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,打出來\N{\rENG}Type it up.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:15.21,1:42:18.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,我瞭解到你在我們人事部門工作 是嗎？\N{\rENG}I understand that you work for our PR department, is that correct?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:19.04,1:42:20.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的現在兩年了\N{\rENG}For two years now, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:20.92,1:42:24.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,那你應該熟悉我早期的工作...\N{\rENG}Then you are familiar with my earlier work...
Dialogue: 0,1:42:24.26,1:42:27.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,對抗愛德華·克拉克 還有他的3K黨 是吧？\N{\rENG}...against Edward Clarke and his Ku Klux Klan, are you not?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:27.89,1:42:29.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rENG}Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:29.22,1:42:32.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,他因為違反販賣白奴法 的暴力行為而被捕...\N{\rENG}He was arrested for a violation of the white slave traffic act...
Dialogue: 0,1:42:32.39,1:42:35.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,因為他穿越州界 跟一個白人女人有婚外情\N{\rENG}...for crossing state lines to have an affair with a white woman.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:35.94,1:42:36.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,是這樣嗎？\N{\rENG}Ls that correct, sir?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:37.15,1:42:41.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的 那是那時候我處理過的最高的法律了\N{\rENG}That is correct. It was the strongest law at my disposal at the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:41.40,1:42:45.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,你要知道 我非常為那件事自豪\N{\rENG}I'll have you know that I'm very proud of that work.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:45.57,1:42:48.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,甘迪小姐告訴我 您上次停在了布魯諾·哈普特曼的逮捕這裡\N{\rENG}Miss Gandy told me that you stopped with Bruno Hauptmann's arrest.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:49.12,1:42:52.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 您想要從那裡開始嗎？ - 是的 就從那裡\N{\rENG}- Would you like to start there? - Yes, yes, I think we shall.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:56.42,1:42:58.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,哈普特曼被送去庭審\N{\rENG}Mr. Hauptmann was brought to trial...
Dialogue: 0,1:42:58.38,1:43:00.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,時間是1935年1月1日\N{\rENG}...on January 2nd, 1935.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:01.92,1:43:06.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,H. L. 門肯（記者）稱 這是基督復活以來最大的新聞\N{\rENG}H.L. Mencken called this the biggest story since the resurrection.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:06.43,1:43:10.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,從現在的情況看 可能還要更大\N{\rENG}From the looks of things, this may be bigger.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:10.22,1:43:12.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,你們看 沒有兩把鋸子會形成一樣的斷面\N{\rENG}Well, you see, no two saws make the same markings.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:12.81,1:43:16.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,布魯諾·哈普特曼工具箱中的鋸子 留下的鋸痕...\N{\rENG}This saw from Bruno Hauptmann's tool chest makes markings identical...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:16.60,1:43:19.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,和犯罪現場留下的梯子的痕跡一樣\N{\rENG}...to those found on the ladder used in the crime.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:19.56,1:43:21.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,比較贖金字條和哈普特曼的筆跡...\N{\rENG}In the ransom note and Mr. Hauptmann's writings...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:22.15,1:43:27.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,他把“anything（任何事）”寫成“anyding” 把“good（好）”寫成“gut”\N{\rENG}...he wrote the word "anyding" for "anything", uh, "gut" for "good"...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:28.03,1:43:32.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,把“boat（船）”寫成“boad” 並且注意這些寫反了的大寫的“N”\N{\rENG}..."boad" for "boat," and notice the inverted capital N's.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:32.70,1:43:35.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,還有這些看上去像“J”的“Y”\N{\rENG}And the Y's that look like J's.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:35.87,1:43:37.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,林德伯格先生 你說你聽到了聲音...\N{\rENG}Mr. Lindbergh, you said you heard a voice...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:38.12,1:43:39.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,在那天晚上的典禮上\N{\rENG}...in the cemetery that night.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:39.63,1:43:41.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的 非常清楚\N{\rENG}Yes, very clearly.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:42.04,1:43:44.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,一個說話聲 我非常肯定...\N{\rENG}A voice, to the best of my belief...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:44.80,1:43:48.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,是用一個外國口音叫康登醫生\N{\rENG}...calling Dr. Condon in a foreign accent.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:48.63,1:43:49.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,“嘿 醫生”\N{\rENG}"Hey, doctor."
Dialogue: 0,1:43:49.80,1:43:50.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,從那個時候...\N{\rENG}Since that time...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:51.01,1:43:52.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,你有沒有聽過一樣的聲音？\N{\rENG}...have you heard the same voice?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:52.97,1:43:54.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,我有\N{\rENG}Yes, I have.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:54.64,1:43:57.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,那天晚上的典禮你聽到的聲音是誰的...\N{\rENG}Whose voice was it that you heard in the cemetery that night...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:57.81,1:43:59.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,說道“嘿 醫生”？\N{\rENG}...saying, "Hey, doctor"?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:59.81,1:44:01.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,那是哈普特曼的聲音\N{\rENG}That was Hauptmann's voice.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:04.15,1:44:05.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,但他到底是不是單獨行動的？\N{\rENG}But did he act alone?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:07.28,1:44:11.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,他從未承認 但這些反社會的人什麼時候承認過？\N{\rENG}He never confessed, but what sociopath ever does?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:11.37,1:44:13.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,證據確鑿\N{\rENG}The evidence was clear.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:13.28,1:44:18.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,他被控訴犯有一級謀殺 同時犯下重大盜竊\N{\rENG}He was indicted for murder in the first degree while perpetrating a burglary.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:18.71,1:44:22.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,在新澤西 這是死罪\N{\rENG}In New Jersey, that is punishable by death.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:22.17,1:44:23.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,哈普特曼先生\N{\rENG}Mr. Hauptmann...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:23.54,1:44:26.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,今天 在這個法庭 你有機會...\N{\rENG}...you've had an opportunity in this courtroom today...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:26.17,1:44:28.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,說出所有真相\N{\rENG}...to tell the whole truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:28.38,1:44:29.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,你有說過真相嗎？\N{\rENG}Have you told the truth?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:29.97,1:44:32.18,CHT,,0,0,0,,我已經說過了\N{\rENG}I told the truth already.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:32.34,1:44:33.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,還有那些...\N{\rENG}And the statements...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:33.60,1:44:36.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,對弗萊律師的陳述 你對他說的都是真的嗎？\N{\rENG}...to District Attorney Foley. Did you tell him the truth?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:36.97,1:44:38.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,某種程度來說\N{\rENG}To a certain extent.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:38.43,1:44:42.85,CHT,,0,0,0,,那從某種程度來說 你沒說出真相 是不是？\N{\rENG}To a certain extent you didn't tell him the truth. Ls that right?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:45.19,1:44:49.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,這塊板子是從你的衣櫥找到的 寫了“S-204”\N{\rENG}This board that was found in your closet, S-204...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:50.11,1:44:52.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,寫了這些數字\N{\rENG}...has these numbers written on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:53.03,1:44:54.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在有點模糊了是不是？\N{\rENG}It's a little blurred now, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:55.03,1:44:56.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,看上去是\N{\rENG}Looks like it.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:56.49,1:44:59.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,這之間還有幾個字 看上去像“迪凱特”和“賽德維克”\N{\rENG}Between are some words. It looks like Decatur and Sedgwick.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:59.45,1:45:00.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,看見沒有？\N{\rENG}You see that?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:02.29,1:45:05.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,你知道這是什麼意思吧？ 那裡的地址？\N{\rENG}You know what that means, don't you? That address on there?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:06.04,1:45:07.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,不大清楚\N{\rENG}Not exactly.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:08.59,1:45:11.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是不是康登醫生的住址和電話...\N{\rENG}It is the address and telephone number of Dr. Condon...
Dialogue: 0,1:45:11.72,1:45:13.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,付了贖金的人..\N{\rENG}...the man who paid the ransom...
Dialogue: 0,1:45:13.38,1:45:17.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,你的字跡 在你的衣櫥裡找到\N{\rENG}...written in your writing, found on a board in your closet.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:17.47,1:45:20.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,胡佛先生 醫生來看你了\N{\rENG}Mr. Hoover, the doctor's here to see you.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:20.85,1:45:22.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,在馬丁·路德·金的歷史性演講以後...\N{\rENG}Following Dr. King's historic speech...
Dialogue: 0,1:45:23.15,1:45:26.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,很多人說那一天重新喚醒了 這個國家的良知\N{\rENG}...many said that day brought about a new awakening in the conscience of the nation.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:27.15,1:45:29.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,而其他人則稱這是國家的恥辱\N{\rENG}Others called it a national disgrace.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:29.74,1:45:34.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,在人與人互相殘殺的歷史長河裡 這是充滿希望的一天\N{\rENG}In the long history of man's cruelty to man, this was a day of hope.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:34.57,1:45:35.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,我有一個夢想...\N{\rENG}I have a dream...
Dialogue: 0,1:45:36.99,1:45:39.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,就是有一天...\N{\rENG}...that one day...
Dialogue: 0,1:45:39.62,1:45:43.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,這個國家會站起來\N{\rENG}...this nation will rise up...
Dialogue: 0,1:45:43.50,1:45:46.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,發掘信條的真正含義\N{\rENG}...and live out the true meaning of its creeds.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:47.09,1:45:51.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,一個人留下的東西由故事的結尾決定 歐文斯探員\N{\rENG}A man's legacy is determined by where the story ends, Agent Owens.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:51.80,1:45:54.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,今晚好好想想 明天做決定\N{\rENG}Let's think about that tonight and make a decision tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:55.47,1:45:56.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是關乎個人的遺產？\N{\rENG}Ls this about a man's legacy?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:58.43,1:46:00.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,還是整個機構的名譽？\N{\rENG}Or an institution's reputation?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:01.43,1:46:03.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,這兩者是相關的\N{\rENG}The two are connected, Agent Owens.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:03.44,1:46:05.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,前者引出了後者 反之亦然\N{\rENG}One invented the other and vice versa.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:06.10,1:46:07.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,日安\N{\rENG}Good day to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:09.40,1:46:10.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,是\N{\rENG}Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:11.11,1:46:14.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們陪審團 判定被告 布魯諾·理查·哈普特曼...\N{\rENG}We the jury find the defendant, Bruno Richard Hauptmann...
Dialogue: 0,1:46:14.65,1:46:16.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,犯有一級謀殺罪\N{\rENG}...guilty of murder in the first degree.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:27.79,1:46:30.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,法官大人 我請求立即宣判\N{\rENG}Your Honor, I ask for immediate sentencing.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:33.80,1:46:37.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,根據州法律\N{\rENG}According to the law of this state...
Dialogue: 0,1:46:37.59,1:46:40.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,我判決布魯諾·哈普特曼死刑\N{\rENG}...l rule that Mr. Bruno Hauptmann suffer death...
Dialogue: 0,1:46:41.06,1:46:46.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,此時此地 一切依據法律\N{\rENG}...at the time and place and in the manner provided by law.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:54.82,1:46:56.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,哈普特曼被判死刑了！\N{\rENG}It's death for Hauptmann!
Dialogue: 0,1:47:02.16,1:47:03.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,世紀大審判...\N{\rENG}The trial of the century...
Dialogue: 0,1:47:03.66,1:47:08.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,犯罪分子伏法 聯邦調查局成為了公眾的英雄\N{\rENG}...the criminal shamed, the FBl cemented as the public hero.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:08.63,1:47:11.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,這就是我們的結尾 探員\N{\rENG}That's our, that's our ending, agent.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:13.51,1:47:15.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,但他是不是單獨犯案的？\N{\rENG}But did he do it alone?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:15.55,1:47:18.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,當時是不是他本人帶走了孩子？ 你怎麼能確定？\N{\rENG}Is he the one who actually took the child? How can you be sure?
Dialogue: 0,1:47:19.72,1:47:23.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,鐵證如山 我們發現了...\N{\rENG}Well, the mountain of evidence we discovered, uncovered...
Dialogue: 0,1:47:23.81,1:47:26.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,揭開了真相 確認了一切 你不能有什麼爭議了\N{\rENG}...confirmed, and clarified, you cannot dispute it.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:26.85,1:47:29.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 但是克拉倫斯·達洛懷疑過 - 當然\N{\rENG}- Clarence Darrow did. - Of course. Heh.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:30.19,1:47:32.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,當然 歐文斯探員 他懷疑過\N{\rENG}Of course, Agent Owens. That's what he does.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:32.36,1:47:34.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,羅斯福夫人發佈了一項聲明 質疑了他的罪行\N{\rENG}Mrs. Roosevelt issued a statement questioning his guilt.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:35.07,1:47:40.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,說到非美國人的行為呢 她自己有的是東西要遮掩\N{\rENG}Well, she has enough to hide on her own when it comes to un-American activities.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:42.74,1:47:46.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果您覺得這個作為結尾合適 我會努力做好\N{\rENG}Well, if you're comfortable with it as an ending, I'll do my best with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:47.12,1:47:50.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,是 好的\N{\rENG}Yes. Yes, I am.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:50.83,1:47:52.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,告辭\N{\rENG}Sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:56.92,1:47:58.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,和我一起看這個\N{\rENG}Watch this with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:58.22,1:48:01.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,他昨晚收到了我的信和錄音帶\N{\rENG}He received my letter and the audio tape last night.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:01.22,1:48:03.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,詹森總統..\N{\rENG}President Johnson affixes his signature...
Dialogue: 0,1:48:03.39,1:48:04.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,用了100多支筆簽名\N{\rENG}...using more than 100 pens.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:04.64,1:48:07.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,又一份令人垂涎的紀念品 會頒發給諾貝爾獎得主...\N{\rENG}One of the coveted souvenirs goes to the Nobel prize-winner...
Dialogue: 0,1:48:07.77,1:48:10.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,...馬丁·路德·金 一位盡心盡責的領導人...\N{\rENG}...Martin Luther King, a dedicated leader...
Dialogue: 0,1:48:10.19,1:48:12.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,說吧 克萊德\N{\rENG}Go on, say it, Clyde.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:13.36,1:48:17.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,愛德格 這很有風險 在這些負面報導之後\N{\rENG}It just seems so risky, Edgar, over a couple negative articles.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:18.53,1:48:21.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,他故意讓周圍圍繞著一群共產主義分子...\N{\rENG}He's deliberately surrounded himself with communists...
Dialogue: 0,1:48:21.24,1:48:25.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,有了這些他正在集合的力量 他現在正是我們國家內部最大的威脅\N{\rENG}...and, with the power he's gathering, he's now our greatest domestic threat.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:25.20,1:48:30.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,代表諾貝爾獎委員會...\N{\rENG}On behalf of the Nobel Committee...
Dialogue: 0,1:48:30.75,1:48:34.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,- 我們把這個... - 他會拒絕這個獎的 克萊德\N{\rENG}...we hand over to you the insignia... - He's going to decline the award, Clyde.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:34.75,1:48:37.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,他知道我們手裡的東西可以毀了他\N{\rENG}He knows what we have can ruin him.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:37.42,1:48:42.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,這項諾貝爾獎 證書 和金牌\N{\rENG}- -Of the Nobel Peace Prize, the diploma and the gold medal.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:47.31,1:48:49.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,毫無疑問\N{\rENG}There's no question about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:49.89,1:48:51.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,他完了\N{\rENG}He's done.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:55.07,1:48:58.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,我接受這項諾貝爾和平獎...\N{\rENG}I accept the Nobel Prize for Peace...
Dialogue: 0,1:49:01.28,1:49:06.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,此刻美國有2200萬黑人\N{\rENG}...at a moment when 22 million Negroes of the United States...
Dialogue: 0,1:49:08.62,1:49:09.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,正在...\N{\rENG}...are enga...
Dialogue: 0,1:49:27.97,1:49:31.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,抱歉打擾了 您的下一個約見的人到了\N{\rENG}- Sorry to interrupt, sir. - Your next appointment is here.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:32.14,1:49:34.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,甘迪 讓醫生先進來\N{\rENG}The doctor first, Miss Gandy.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:34.65,1:49:36.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的 當然\N{\rENG}Yes, of course.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:38.32,1:49:42.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,讓他幾分鐘後進來 謝謝\N{\rENG}Send him in in a few minutes. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:41.94,1:51:44.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,要堅強 愛德格\N{\rENG}Stay strong, Edgar.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:15.31,1:52:17.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,你要堅強 愛德格\N{\rENG}You stay strong, Edgar.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:18.60,1:52:20.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,要堅強\N{\rENG}Stay strong. Unh!
Dialogue: 0,1:52:45.42,1:52:47.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,遊行隊伍正在向前...\N{\rENG}The parade as it makes its way...
Dialogue: 0,1:52:47.46,1:52:49.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,去往國會大廈的就職儀式\N{\rENG}...to the Capitol Building for the inauguration.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:52.51,1:52:56.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,可以看到羅斯福軍樂隊 正在帶路\N{\rENG}You can see the Roosevelt High Marching Band leading the way.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:59.27,1:53:03.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,汽車隊伍正在沿著賓夕法尼亞大道前進\N{\rENG}The motorcade is making progress down Pennsylvania Avenue...
Dialogue: 0,1:53:05.06,1:53:08.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,載著我們的第37任總統\N{\rENG}...carrying our 37th president.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:14.20,1:53:16.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,理查·米爾豪斯·尼克森向群眾招手\N{\rENG}Richard Milhous Nixon waves to the crowd.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:17.04,1:53:20.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的 總統和他的夫人...\N{\rENG}Yep, there's the president and his wife Pat...
Dialogue: 0,1:53:20.58,1:53:22.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,高興地揮手\N{\rENG}...happily waving.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:58.08,1:54:00.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,當道德敗壞...\N{\rENG}When morals decline...
Dialogue: 0,1:54:01.20,1:54:03.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,好人不做任何事...\N{\rENG}...and good men do nothing...
Dialogue: 0,1:54:04.54,1:54:06.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,罪惡就會興盛\N{\rENG}...evil flourishes.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:09.92,1:54:14.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,每個公民都有義務瞭解這些\N{\rENG}Every citizen has a duty to learn of this that threatens his home...
Dialogue: 0,1:54:16.09,1:54:17.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,威脅到他們的家園和孩子\N{\rENG}...his children.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:21.60,1:54:25.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,一個沒興趣也不願意 從過去吸取教訓的社會\N{\rENG}A society uninterested and unwilling to learn from the past...
Dialogue: 0,1:54:26.73,1:54:27.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,註定會隕滅\N{\rENG}...is doomed.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:31.99,1:54:33.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們永遠不能忘記歷史\N{\rENG}We must never forget our history.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:39.74,1:54:42.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們永遠不能放鬆警惕\N{\rENG}We must never lower our guard.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:49.17,1:54:55.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,甚至今天 仍舊有組織 把美國作為他們的頭號目標\N{\rENG}Even today, there are organizations that have America as their prime target.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:55.43,1:54:59.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們會毀掉每個人的平安和幸福\N{\rENG}They would destroy the safety and the happiness of every individual...
Dialogue: 0,1:54:59.89,1:55:03.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,把我們推入無法無天的深淵\N{\rENG}...and thrust us into a condition of lawlessness...
Dialogue: 0,1:55:03.47,1:55:07.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,超乎想像的無恥\N{\rENG}...immorality that passes the imagination.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:08.98,1:55:11.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,總統先生可以見您了 胡佛先生\N{\rENG}The president will see you now, Mr. Hoover.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:11.98,1:55:13.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,好的\N{\rENG}Alrighty.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:24.62,1:55:26.16,CHT,,0,0,0,,愛德格 進來\N{\rENG}Edgar, come in.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:37.47,1:55:40.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,噢 我很抱歉 胡佛先生\N{\rENG}Oh, I am so sorry, Mr. Hoover.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:40.51,1:55:42.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,你一直不接電話\N{\rENG}You weren't answering your telephone.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:43.77,1:55:46.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,你和一位要退休的探員有會議\N{\rENG}You had a photo session with a retiring agent.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:46.60,1:55:48.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,他就要走了\N{\rENG}He's leaving now.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:49.02,1:55:50.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,克萊德呢？\N{\rENG}Where's Clyde?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:52.86,1:55:56.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,他今天不太舒服\N{\rENG}It's a bad day for him, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:00.03,1:56:03.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,你能不能幫我們安排一下晚餐？\N{\rENG}Will you...? Will you schedule a dinner for us, please...
Dialogue: 0,1:56:04.04,1:56:06.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,就在我們轉角的餐廳 老地方\N{\rENG}...in our old corner booth?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:07.37,1:56:09.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,恐怕他今天真的太累了\N{\rENG}I'm afraid he's too tired today, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:10.04,1:56:12.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,或許你願意去他家裡吃？\N{\rENG}Perhaps you'd like to dine at his house?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:12.38,1:56:14.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,我想他喜歡這樣\N{\rENG}I think he'd like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:16.13,1:56:17.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,好\N{\rENG}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:18.22,1:56:20.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,好的 謝謝你 甘迪\N{\rENG}Yes, thank you, Miss Gandy.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:26.77,1:56:27.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,海倫？\N{\rENG}Helen?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:32.06,1:56:33.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,嗯？\N{\rENG}Yes?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:36.07,1:56:38.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是不是毀了一切我所愛的？\N{\rENG}Do I kill everything that I love?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:42.07,1:56:44.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,他還沒有離開 愛德格\N{\rENG}He's not gone yet, Edgar.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:48.58,1:56:50.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,還有我們親手建立的一切？\N{\rENG}And everything that we've built?
Dialogue: 0,1:56:51.58,1:56:52.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,不\N{\rENG}No.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:53.17,1:56:56.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,調查局比開始只有我們的時候 要強大多了\N{\rENG}The Bureau is stronger than just you and me now.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:58.21,1:57:01.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,您的部下很可靠 他們保證著國家的安全\N{\rENG}Your child is sure and keeps this country safe.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:08.47,1:57:09.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,海倫 假如...\N{\rENG}Helen, if any...
Dialogue: 0,1:57:10.35,1:57:14.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,假如我出了什麼事  我需要你做點事 你明白嗎？\N{\rENG}if anything ever happens to me, I need you to do something for me, do you understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:57:16.48,1:57:17.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,當然\N{\rENG}Of course.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:19.61,1:57:22.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,尼克森 他會追查一切\N{\rENG}Nixon, he's gonna come for it all.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:24.20,1:57:26.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,他會毀了我和我的調查局\N{\rENG}He'll crucify me and my Bureau.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:28.49,1:57:34.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,我擔心假如我不在 會發生些什麼事\N{\rENG}I'm afraid of what will happen if I'm not here to protect it, Miss Gandy.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:34.63,1:57:36.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,您的機密文件？\N{\rENG}Your private files, sir?
Dialogue: 0,1:57:39.09,1:57:42.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒有人會找到這些檔\N{\rENG}Then no one will ever find them.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:45.30,1:57:46.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝你 海倫\N{\rENG}Thank you, Helen.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:57.65,1:58:00.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,不管他們給你施加多少壓力？\N{\rENG}No matter what kind of pressure they put on?
Dialogue: 0,1:58:01.36,1:58:03.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,不管多少？\N{\rENG}No matter how much?
Dialogue: 0,1:58:03.36,1:58:04.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的 愛德格\N{\rENG}Yes, Edgar.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:05.99,1:58:08.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,不管施加多少壓力\N{\rENG}No matter how much pressure.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:10.50,1:58:12.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,我向你保證\N{\rENG}I promise you.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:14.17,1:58:15.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝你 海倫\N{\rENG}Thank you, Helen.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:27.76,1:58:31.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,尼克森有沒有讓你辭職？\N{\rENG}Well, did Nixon ask for your resignation?
Dialogue: 0,1:58:31.27,1:58:35.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,不 他想要知道 我們掌握了他的什麼檔\N{\rENG}No, he wanted to know what we had in the files on him.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:36.35,1:58:37.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,你說了什麼？\N{\rENG}What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,1:58:38.52,1:58:41.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,我說“什麼檔？”\N{\rENG}I said, "What files, sir?"
Dialogue: 0,1:58:41.53,1:58:43.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,但是他知道\N{\rENG}But he knows.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:43.86,1:58:48.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,他想讓我們擴大我們的竊聽範圍 包括新聞報導員 克萊德\N{\rENG}He wants us to expand our wiretaps to include news reporters now, Clyde.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:49.95,1:58:53.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們不能那樣做 尤其是現在\N{\rENG}We can't do that, especially not now.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:53.45,1:58:55.16,CHT,,0,0,0,,問題就在這 克萊德\N{\rENG}That's the problem, Clyde.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:55.33,1:59:00.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果我不答應他做這些暗地裡的事 他會成立自己的私人集權\N{\rENG}If I don't agree to do his black bag jobs, he'll create his own private force.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:00.67,1:59:03.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,噢 那是違法的\N{\rENG}Oh, that's illegal.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:03.55,1:59:09.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,是啊 他雖然沒有直說 但我可以從他眼神裡看出來\N{\rENG}Yes, well, he didn't say it outright, but I saw it in his eyes.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:09.39,1:59:11.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,他不會受任何人控制 克萊德\N{\rENG}He won't be controlled, Clyde.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:11.56,1:59:15.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,他是個威脅 他會為了權力做任何事\N{\rENG}He's a menace who'll do anything to hold on to power.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:16.73,1:59:18.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,是啊 我知道了\N{\rENG}Right. I see.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:19.56,1:59:23.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,是啊 你看 我從不跟他玩這些 這就是問題所在\N{\rENG}Yes. See, I never played his game, that's the problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:24.07,1:59:26.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,假如我做的某些事情 看上去有些過界...\N{\rENG}And if to some what I did seemed like rule-bending...
Dialogue: 0,1:59:26.70,1:59:30.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,或許他們需要找出 他們都做了些什麼...\N{\rENG}...then perhaps they need to figure out what it is they did...
Dialogue: 0,1:59:30.28,1:59:33.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,來讓他們感到被勒索或是恐嚇\N{\rENG}...that made them feel blackmailed or intimidated.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:34.25,1:59:36.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,我想的不是這個\N{\rENG}I wasn't thinking that.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:37.50,1:59:41.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,那是什麼？你在想什麼？\N{\rENG}Then what? What were you thinking?
Dialogue: 0,1:59:42.59,1:59:46.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,我在想 或許是時候我們該退休了\N{\rENG}I was thinking it might be time for us to retire.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:47.43,1:59:48.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,閉嘴 克萊德\N{\rENG}Shut up, Clyde.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:50.72,1:59:53.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,你有很偉大的成就 愛德格\N{\rENG}You built a great thing, Edgar.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:54.35,1:59:57.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果你現在就收手 你會得到嘉獎\N{\rENG}And if you stop now, you'll be celebrated.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:58.52,2:00:00.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是你一直想要的 不是嗎？\N{\rENG}That's what you've always wanted, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,2:00:00.77,2:00:03.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,整個國家長久的崇拜？\N{\rENG}Our country's lasting adoration?
Dialogue: 0,2:00:03.61,2:00:06.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在就是你獲得這些的機會\N{\rENG}Well, there's a chance you could have it.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:06.94,2:00:10.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,是啊 是啊 我憑什麼不呢？\N{\rENG}Yes. Yes, and why wouldn't I? Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,2:00:10.53,2:00:12.16,CHT,,0,0,0,,我憑什麼不呢 克萊德？\N{\rENG}Why wouldn't I, Clyde?
Dialogue: 0,2:00:12.33,2:00:15.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,我保衛國家不受布爾什維克侵略\N{\rENG}I saved this country from a Bolshevik invasion...
Dialogue: 0,2:00:16.04,2:00:19.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,掃除了激進分子 逮捕了“機關槍凱利”\N{\rENG}...rid this country of radicals, captured Machine Gun Kelly...
Dialogue: 0,2:00:20.12,2:00:23.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,殺了迪林傑 抓住了卡佩斯 還把布魯諾·哈普特曼定罪了\N{\rENG}...killed Dillinger, captured Karpis, convicted Bruno Hauptmann.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:23.75,2:00:27.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在 我還有最後一口氣 想要保衛這個國家...\N{\rENG}And now, with my last breath when I try to help save this country again...
Dialogue: 0,2:00:27.51,2:00:30.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,結果卻被強制要求退休？\N{\rENG}...I'm rewarded with a forced retirement?
Dialogue: 0,2:00:30.18,2:00:32.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不會被打倒的 你這建議其實讓我...\N{\rENG}I will not go down, and the fact that you suggest that...
Dialogue: 0,2:00:33.14,2:00:35.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,懷疑你的忠心\N{\rENG}...makes me question your very loyalty.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:36.56,2:00:38.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,我的忠心 愛德格？\N{\rENG}My loyalty, Edgar?
Dialogue: 0,2:00:38.77,2:00:41.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,是啊 你的忠心 克萊德\N{\rENG}Yes, your loyalty, Clyde.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:42.27,2:00:45.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,我讀過你的手稿了 愛德格\N{\rENG}I read your manuscript, Edgar.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:46.15,2:00:48.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,你並沒有逮捕卡佩斯\N{\rENG}You didn't arrest Karpis.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:48.65,2:00:52.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,你和我一樣清楚 那條街上沒有白馬\N{\rENG}And you know as well as I do there was no white horse in the street...
Dialogue: 0,2:00:53.82,2:00:56.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,後座也沒有槍\N{\rENG}...no gun in the back seat.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:56.99,2:01:01.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,也不是你殺了迪林傑的 是博維斯探員\N{\rENG}And you didn't kill Dillinger. Agent Purvis did.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:02.00,2:01:05.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,但你把所有的榮譽據為己有\N{\rENG}But you kept all the glory for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:06.21,2:01:10.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,“機關槍凱利”也從未說過 “不要開槍 官老爺們”\N{\rENG}And Machine Gun Kelly never said, "Don't shoot, G-Men."
Dialogue: 0,2:01:11.51,2:01:16.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,你編造了這些 來賣出漫畫書 愛德格\N{\rENG}You made that up to sell comic books, Edgar.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:17.52,2:01:22.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,至於本世紀最大的犯罪案件\N{\rENG}And when we went to the scene of the greatest crime of the century...
Dialogue: 0,2:01:22.90,2:01:26.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,林德伯格先生根本沒有出來 和你握手\N{\rENG}...Mr. Lindbergh didn't come out and shake your hand...
Dialogue: 0,2:01:27.11,2:01:31.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,也沒有表達他對調查局的信任\N{\rENG}...and express his faith in the FBl.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:31.74,2:01:38.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,他說你是挑剔的傢伙 拒絕再次和你見面\N{\rENG}He called you a fussy little man, and he refused to even meet you.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:40.37,2:01:43.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,也不是你逮捕了哈普特曼\N{\rENG}And you didn't arrest Hauptmann.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:44.17,2:01:46.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,是西斯科探員\N{\rENG}Agent Sisk did.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:46.63,2:01:51.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,你甚至都不在現場 愛德格 只有那張照片\N{\rENG}You weren't even at the scene, Edgar. Only the photo op.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:51.30,2:01:55.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,愛德格 你寫的大多數都是誇大其詞\N{\rENG}Edgar, most of what you wrote is exaggeration...
Dialogue: 0,2:01:55.51,2:02:00.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,很多是明顯的謊言 我甚至都不知道你是否意識到這一點\N{\rENG}...some of it blatant lies, and I don't even know if you realize it anymore.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:02.77,2:02:04.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,愛德格\N{\rENG}Edgar...
Dialogue: 0,2:02:05.06,2:02:09.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,你可以對所有人說話 對全世界\N{\rENG}...you can lie to everyone else, the whole world...
Dialogue: 0,2:02:09.23,2:02:12.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,看在你自己份上 看在調查局的份上\N{\rENG}...for your own sake, for the sake of the Bureau...
Dialogue: 0,2:02:13.61,2:02:15.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,但你騙不了我\N{\rENG}...but you cannot lie to me.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:19.24,2:02:22.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,我就不應該給你這份工作 克萊德\N{\rENG}I should've never given you your job, Clyde.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:24.42,2:02:25.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,你知道嗎？\N{\rENG}You know that?
Dialogue: 0,2:02:27.92,2:02:30.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,你根本不符合要求\N{\rENG}You weren't even qualified.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:33.30,2:02:36.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,你記得那天你進來面試嗎？\N{\rENG}You remember the day you came in for your interview?
Dialogue: 0,2:02:37.47,2:02:39.18,CHT,,0,0,0,,我記得\N{\rENG}I do.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:41.27,2:02:45.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,你來到我的辦公室 幫我整理好了窗戶\N{\rENG}You walked into my office and you fixed my window...
Dialogue: 0,2:02:45.81,2:02:48.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,你拿了我的手帕\N{\rENG}...you picked up my handkerchief.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:48.94,2:02:50.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,你把它遞給我的\N{\rENG}You handed it to me.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:52.99,2:02:55.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,你記不記得為什麼我會出汗？\N{\rENG}You remember why I was sweating, Clyde?
Dialogue: 0,2:02:57.20,2:02:59.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,因為你剛剛鍛煉過\N{\rENG}It's because you were exercising.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:01.95,2:03:03.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,不 我...\N{\rENG}No, I was...
Dialogue: 0,2:03:04.50,2:03:06.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,我出汗是因為我...\N{\rENG}I was sweating because I...
Dialogue: 0,2:03:07.29,2:03:09.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,那一刻我知道...\N{\rENG}I knew at that very moment...
Dialogue: 0,2:03:11.30,2:03:13.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,那一刻我清楚地知道...\N{\rENG}I knew at that very moment that I...
Dialogue: 0,2:03:15.13,2:03:16.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,我需要你\N{\rENG}I needed you.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:18.30,2:03:21.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,我這輩子從未需要過其他任何人\N{\rENG}And I've never needed anyone else in my entire life.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:24.06,2:03:25.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,從未像你這樣\N{\rENG}Not like that.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:27.52,2:03:29.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,所以我開始出汗\N{\rENG}So I began to perspire.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:30.86,2:03:32.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,我知道\N{\rENG}I know.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:34.99,2:03:37.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,愛德格 你沒事吧？\N{\rENG}Edgar, are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,2:03:38.49,2:03:39.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,是 這是...\N{\rENG}Yes, yes, it's...
Dialogue: 0,2:03:40.95,2:03:45.16,CHT,,0,0,0,,只是消化不良 克萊德\N{\rENG}It's just indigestion, Clyde.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:48.75,2:03:52.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們明天出去吃晚飯吧？ 我們的老地方\N{\rENG}Let's go to dinner tomorrow night, shall we? Our old corner booth.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:54.59,2:03:56.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,或許吧如果我感覺好些了\N{\rENG}Perhaps if I feel better.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:56.34,2:03:58.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,好\N{\rENG}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:58.26,2:03:59.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,你必須...\N{\rENG}And you must...
Dialogue: 0,2:03:59.68,2:04:04.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,你必須... 我們還有很重要的事情要商量\N{\rENG}You must... We have a great many things to discuss.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:04.64,2:04:08.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在在調查局 我沒有任何人可以信任\N{\rENG}And now I can't trust anyone else at the Bureau right now.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:10.02,2:04:11.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,只能靠你了\N{\rENG}Can only depend on you.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:31.50,2:04:33.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝你 愛德格\N{\rENG}Thank you, Edgar.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:48.43,2:04:49.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,晚安 克萊德\N{\rENG}Good night, Clyde.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:51.52,2:04:53.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,晚安 愛德格\N{\rENG}Good night, Edgar.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:19.05,2:05:20.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,歡迎回家 胡佛先生\N{\rENG}Welcome home, Mr. Hoover.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:20.76,2:05:21.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝 安妮\N{\rENG}Oh, thank you, Annie.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:21.97,2:05:24.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,波佐 波佐 好孩子 過來\N{\rENG}Bozo, Bozo, G-Boy, come here.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:24.80,2:05:27.85,CHT,,0,0,0,,民主的本質...\N{\rENG}The very essence of our democracy...
Dialogue: 0,2:05:28.18,2:05:32.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,紮根於對於獨立的信仰\N{\rENG}...is rooted in a belief in the worth of the individual.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:33.27,2:05:38.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,生命的意義已經超越任何人造系統\N{\rENG}That life has meaning that transcends any man-made system...
Dialogue: 0,2:05:38.78,2:05:42.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,愛是世上最偉大的力量\N{\rENG}...that love is the greatest force on earth...
Dialogue: 0,2:05:44.11,2:05:46.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,比仇恨要持久得多\N{\rENG}...far more enduring than hatred...
Dialogue: 0,2:05:47.83,2:05:51.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,或是人類那些非自然的種群\N{\rENG}...or the unnatural divisions of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:02.47,2:06:03.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,喂？\N{\rENG}Yes?
Dialogue: 0,2:06:04.34,2:06:07.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是胡佛先生家的安妮\N{\rENG}This is Annie from Mr. Hoover's residence.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:07.97,2:06:10.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,胡佛先生去世了\N{\rENG}Mr. Hoover has passed.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:39.34,2:06:40.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,- Yeah? - Sir.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:44.17,2:06:46.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,上帝啊\N{\rENG}Jesus Christ.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:47.18,2:06:49.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,那個老不死的\N{\rENG}That old cocksucker.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:49.60,2:06:52.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,我要準備一個演講 要上電視\N{\rENG}I'll get a speech prepared. We should go on television.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:52.43,2:06:53.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,還不行\N{\rENG}Not yet.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:54.10,2:06:58.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,先封鎖他的辦公室 換掉鎖 做你應該做的\N{\rENG}First seal off his office, change his locks, do whatever you have to do.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:58.56,2:07:01.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,我得把那些該死的檔找出來\N{\rENG}I want those fucking files.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:02.03,2:07:03.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,是\N{\rENG}Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:12.04,2:07:13.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,真好\N{\rENG}Oh, good.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:14.54,2:07:16.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,進來吧\N{\rENG}Come in.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:21.92,2:07:24.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,他在樓上\N{\rENG}He's upstairs.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:28.51,2:09:32.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,女士們先生們 這於我個人也是極大的損失...\N{\rENG}Ladies and gentlemen, it is with a profound sense of personal loss...
Dialogue: 0,2:09:33.01,2:09:36.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,我已得知 J·愛德格·胡佛先生去世了\N{\rENG}...that I learned of the death of J. Edgar Hoover.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:36.68,2:09:40.85,CHT,,0,0,0,,這位了不起的公僕 為國家工作了48年\N{\rENG}This truly remarkable man has served his country for 48 years...
Dialogue: 0,2:09:41.02,2:09:43.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,作為聯邦調查局的局長 歷經8任總統\N{\rENG}...under eight presidents, as director of the FBl...
Dialogue: 0,2:09:43.85,2:09:49.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,用他無與倫比的奉獻精神 能力 以及巨大貢獻\N{\rENG}...with unparalleled devotion and ability and dedication.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:49.86,2:09:54.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,25年以來 從我第一次以新人國會議員 的身份來到華盛頓\N{\rENG}For 25 years, from the time I came to Washington as a freshman congressman...
Dialogue: 0,2:09:55.07,2:09:59.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,他就是我最親密的朋友和顧問之一\N{\rENG}...he has been one of my closest personal friends and advisors.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:59.54,2:10:03.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,我認為 每個美國人  都欠了胡佛先生很多\N{\rENG}And every American, in my opinion, owes J. Edgar Hoover a great debt...
Dialogue: 0,2:10:03.62,2:10:08.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,他把聯邦調查局 建立成了最好的法律執行機構\N{\rENG}...for building the FBl into the finest law enforcement organization...
Dialogue: 0,2:10:08.21,2:10:10.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,在全世界的範圍來說\N{\rENG}...in the entire world.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:11.96,2:10:16.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,我已下令所有的政府機構 都要下半旗致哀\N{\rENG}I've ordered that all the flags of the government buildings be flown at half mast...
Dialogue: 0,2:10:17.05,2:10:19.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,但我要說 這樣做 為了愛德格·胡佛\N{\rENG}...but I will say that, in doing so, that Edgar Hoover...
Dialogue: 0,2:10:19.89,2:10:24.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,因為有了他頑強的勇氣 和極其險惡的攻擊作鬥爭\N{\rENG}...because of his indomitable courage against sometimes very vicious attack...
Dialogue: 0,2:10:24.77,2:10:31.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,他已經保證 聯邦調查局的旗幟會一直高高飄揚\N{\rENG}...has made certain that the flag of the FBl will always fly high.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:31.24,2:10:38.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,聯邦調查局是美國永恆的豐碑\N{\rENG}The FBl is the eternal monument honoring this great American.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:40.24,2:10:42.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,“即使這最親密的臉龐..”\N{\rENG}Funny how even the dearest face...
Dialogue: 0,2:10:42.25,2:10:44.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,“會隨著時間的流逝而消失...”\N{\rENG}...will fade away in time...
Dialogue: 0,2:10:45.29,2:10:50.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,“我清楚地記得 你的眼睛裡有挑逗的笑容”\N{\rENG}...but most clearly I remember your eyes with a sort of teasing smile in them...
Dialogue: 0,2:10:50.67,2:10:53.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,“還有那最溫柔的地方...”\N{\rENG}...and the feeling of that soft spot...
Dialogue: 0,2:10:53.59,2:10:56.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,“是東北方位之於你溫柔的嘴角”\N{\rENG}...just northeast of the corner of your mouth.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:00.50,2:11:06.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,胡佛的“私人機密檔案”從未被人知曉 只有一些沒有歸檔的資料透露出線索
Dialogue: 0,2:11:07.50,2:11:11.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,克萊德·托爾森繼承了胡佛的房產 搬進了他家 接受了覆於他棺木的美國國旗
Dialogue: 0,2:11:13.50,2:11:15.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,克萊德·托爾森的葬在離胡佛 在國會墓地的墓碑幾碼遠的地方

